# RDFS Schema for Business: Pharmaceuticals

@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix ind: <http://datamodel.lakehouse.org/business/pharmaceuticals#> .

# --- Root Business Class ---
ind:Business rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label 'Business' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Root class for all business entities' .

# --- Specific Business: Pharmaceuticals ---
ind:Pharmaceuticals rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Business ;
    rdfs:label 'Pharmaceuticals' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Pharmaceuticals is a research-intensive industry focused on discovering, developing, and manufacturing medicines, vaccines, and consumer health products to treat and prevent diseases across therapeutic areas including oncology, immunology, and rare diseases.' .

# --- Domain Classes ---
ind:Discovery rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Discovery' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns all data generated during drug discovery and target identification, including high-throughput screening (HTS) results, structure-activity relationship (SAR) analysis, mechanism of action (MOA) studies, hit-to-lead progression, molecular targets, and early-stage compound optimization under GLP. Manages research data from electronic lab notebooks (ELN) in IDBS/Dotmatics, assay results, and compound libraries. Authoritative source for NCE (New Chemical Entity) and NBE (New Biological Entity) research data entering the development pipeline.' .

ind:Clinical rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Clinical' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages end-to-end clinical trial design, execution, and data management across all phases (I-IV). Covers investigational sites, principal investigators, trial protocols, case report forms (CRF), electronic data capture (EDC) from Medidata Rave, CTMS records from Oracle/Siebel, eTMF in Veeva Vault, and GCP-compliant execution. Includes patient enrollment, randomization, blinding, and intent-to-treat (ITT) analysis. Authoritative source for clinical efficacy and safety endpoints including ORR, PFS, OS, and QoL metrics. Supports IND/NDA/BLA/MAA submissions.' .

ind:Regulatory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages all regulatory submissions, approvals, and compliance management including IND, NDA, BLA, MAA, and eCTD dossiers. Tracks interactions with FDA, EMA, PMDA, MHRA, and NMPA health authorities. Manages regulatory milestones, pre-approval inspections (PAI), REMS programs, post-approval commitments, drug master files (DMF), label management, and regulatory correspondence. Integrates with Veeva Vault RIM and RIMS for submission tracking and lifecycle management.' .

ind:Manufacturing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Manufacturing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages production of drug substances (DS) and drug products (DP) including API production, formulation, fill-finish, and packaging under cGMP. Covers manufacturing execution system (MES) data, batch records, critical process parameters (CPP), critical quality attributes (CQA), equipment scheduling, and production schedules. Includes CMO and CDMO oversight. Integrates with SAP PP/QM and MES systems. Supports QbD principles and PAT implementation per 21 CFR Parts 210/211.' .

ind:Quality rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Quality' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Controls quality management system (QMS) including quality control testing, quality assurance oversight, CAPA (corrective and preventive action), deviation management, OOS (out of specification) investigations, OOT (out of trend) analysis, change controls, SOPs, and audit findings. Manages LIMS data, stability studies, method validation, and certificate of analysis (CoA) issuance. Integrates with MasterControl/TrackWise and SAP QM. Implements QbD and PAT principles across GMP, GLP, and GCP quality oversight.' .

ind:Supply rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Supply' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages end-to-end pharmaceutical supply chain planning and execution including demand forecasting, inventory management, cold-chain logistics, GDP (Good Distribution Practice) compliance, and distribution network management. Covers raw materials, API, excipients, packaging components, and finished goods across manufacturing sites, distribution centers, and third-party logistics providers. Integrates with Kinaxis RapidResponse/Blue Yonder and SAP MM/WM/SD. Tracks SKU, NDC, and lot/batch traceability for both commercial and clinical trial supply chains.' .

ind:Pharmacovigilance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Pharmacovigilance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns all post-market safety surveillance and adverse event management. Collects, processes, and reports individual case safety reports (ICSR), serious adverse events (SAE), suspected unexpected serious adverse reactions (SUSAR), periodic safety update reports (PSUR), risk management plans (RMP), and signal detection records. Integrates with Argus Safety/Oracle AERS. Supports mandatory regulatory reporting to FDA, EMA, and other health authorities per PV regulations.' .

ind:Product rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authoritative catalog and lifecycle management for all pharmaceutical products including branded drugs, generics, biosimilars, vaccines, and consumer health products. Manages product hierarchies, drug substance/drug product definitions, finished dosage forms (FDF), SKUs, NDC codes, ATC classifications, international nonproprietary names (INN), USAN, formulations, strengths, dosage forms, packaging configurations, and regulatory identifiers. Serves as the master product catalog referenced by manufacturing, commercial, regulatory, and supply chain domains.' .

ind:Patient rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Patient' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Single source of truth for patient and clinical trial participant master data including demographics, enrollment status, informed consent, medical history, longitudinal treatment records, and patient-reported outcomes. Manages patient registries, patient support programs, adherence monitoring, and copay assistance programs. Ensures HIPAA and GDPR compliance for protected health information (PHI). Authoritative source for patient identity across clinical trials, pharmacovigilance, and market access programs.' .

ind:Commercial rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Commercial' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Handles commercial operations including sales force management, healthcare professional (HCP) engagement, key opinion leader (KOL) relationships, promotional materials (Veeva PromoMats), territory management, product launch activities, sample distribution, and speaker programs. Integrates with Veeva CRM and Salesforce Health Cloud. Manages compliance with promotional regulations, PhRMA code, and Sunshine Act transparency reporting. Supports brand performance tracking and P&L reporting by brand.' .

ind:Medical rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Medical' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages medical affairs activities including medical science liaisons (MSL), medical information services, publication planning, investigator-initiated trials (IIT), investigator-sponsored studies (ISS), and health economics and outcomes research (HEOR). Manages real-world evidence (RWE) and real-world data (RWD) generation, medical education programs, scientific communications, and KOL relationship management. Integrates with Veeva MedComms. Bridges clinical development and commercial operations.' .

ind:Market rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Market' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Coordinates market access, pricing, reimbursement, and payer relations. Manages formulary positioning, health technology assessment (HTA) submissions, value dossiers, contracting with payers, pharmacy benefit managers (PBM), and group purchasing organizations (GPO). Tracks reimbursement policies, coverage decisions, patient access programs, copay assistance, and gross-to-net revenue management. Owns RWE and RWD assets used for payer negotiations.' .

ind:Hcp rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Hcp' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Healthcare professional and healthcare organization master data including physicians, pharmacists, hospitals, clinics, and key opinion leaders (KOL). Manages HCP credentials, specialties, prescribing patterns, affiliations, and engagement history. Ensures compliance with Sunshine Act transparency reporting and anti-kickback regulations. Authoritative source for HCP identity and relationship data used across commercial, medical affairs, and clinical operations.' .

ind:Intellectual rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Intellectual' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SSOT for intellectual property portfolio including patents (NCE, NBE, formulations, processes), patent expiry timelines, exclusivity periods (orphan drug, data exclusivity, pediatric), trademark registrations, drug master files, freedom-to-operate analyses, and licensing agreements. Supports lifecycle management decisions, generic/biosimilar entry defense strategies, and coordination with legal counsel on patent litigation.' .

ind:Finance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Finance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Owns enterprise financial data including general ledger, accounts payable, accounts receivable, cost accounting, budgeting, R&D capitalization, COGS by product, royalty accounting, and SOX-compliant financial reporting. Integrates with SAP FI/CO modules. Supports P&L by therapeutic area, brand, and geography, return on investment (ROI) for R&D programs, and capital expenditure tracking.' .

ind:Procurement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Procurement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages strategic sourcing and procurement of raw materials (APIs, excipients), packaging materials, laboratory supplies, and services. Covers supplier qualification, vendor master data, purchase orders, contracts, supplier performance, and GMP vendor audits. Coordinates with CRO, CMO, and CDMO partners. Integrates with SAP MM and Ariba. Ensures compliance with supplier quality agreements and GDP requirements.' .

ind:Workforce rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Workforce' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages human resources data including employee master data, organizational structure, talent acquisition, performance management, compensation, benefits, payroll, and training. Tracks GCP, GMP, and GLP training records for regulated personnel, certifications, competencies, and role-based access for quality-critical functions. Supports workforce planning and audit readiness for FDA/EMA inspections.' .

ind:Masterdata rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Masterdata' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Governs enterprise master data including organization hierarchy, chart of accounts, vendor master, material master, geographic reference data, units of measure, and code sets (ATC, NDC). Serves as the cross-domain reference layer ensuring consistent identifiers across SAP S/4HANA, Veeva, LIMS, and other operational systems. Supports MDM governance, data stewardship, and data quality management.' .

ind:Compliance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmaceuticals ;
    rdfs:label 'Compliance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages enterprise-wide GxP compliance programs, regulatory inspection readiness, SOX controls, data integrity (ALCOA+), and cross-functional compliance monitoring including 21 CFR Part 11, EU Annex 11, and GDPR obligations' .

# --- Data Product Classes (Tables) ---
ind:MslProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Msl Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for Medical Science Liaisons (MSLs) including territory assignments, therapeutic area expertise, credentials, certification status, and engagement capacity. Tracks MSL headcount, seniority, and scientific specialization across regions. Serves as the authoritative identity record for field medical personnel distinct from commercial sales representatives.' .

ind:MslEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Msl Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of individual MSL interactions with healthcare professionals (HCPs), KOLs, and investigators. Captures interaction type (proactive scientific exchange, reactive medical inquiry response, advisory board, congress interaction), therapeutic area discussed, product or pipeline asset referenced, channel (face-to-face, virtual, phone), duration, outcome classification (insight captured, follow-up required, no action), and compliance attestation. Sourced from Veeva MedComms CRM activity records. Supports MSL productivity metrics, KOL coverage analysis, and field medical impact reporting.' .

ind:MedicalKolProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Medical Kol Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for Key Opinion Leaders (KOLs) and emerging thought leaders relevant to the companys therapeutic areas. Captures academic affiliations, H-index and publication metrics, therapeutic area expertise, clinical trial participation history, advisory board memberships, congress speaking engagements, influence tier classification (global, regional, national, local), digital influence score, conflict-of-interest disclosure status, aggregate transparency reporting totals (Sunshine Act/Open Payments, EFPIA disclosure), fair market value tier assignment, and engagement history summary. Distinct from the HCP domains general practitioner master — this entity specifically tracks scientific influence, thought leadership metrics, medical affairs relationship depth, and cumulative HCP payment/transfer-of-value data for transparency compliance and strategic engagement planning.' .

ind:Inquiry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Inquiry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of unsolicited medical information requests received from HCPs, patients, caregivers, or payers. Captures inquiry source, channel (phone, email, web portal, congress), product or compound referenced, therapeutic area, inquiry category (safety, efficacy, dosing, off-label), response provided, response date, and regulatory compliance flags. Sourced from Veeva MedComms medical information service workflows.' .

ind:IitSubmission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Iit Submission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the full Investigator-Initiated Trial (IIT) and Investigator-Sponsored Study (ISS) lifecycle from initial submission through funding approval, grant disbursement, study execution, and closeout. Captures submission details (investigator identity, institution, study design, therapeutic area, compound requested, scientific rationale, review committee decision, approval status), complete grant financials (grant amount, disbursement schedule, milestone-based payment triggers, compound supply commitments, budget amendments), reporting obligations, publication rights agreements, study start/end dates, interim milestone tracking, and final closeout status including financial reconciliation. Single source of truth for all IIT/ISS program management and associated funding.' .

ind:MedicalPublication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Medical Publication' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the full scientific publication lifecycle from strategic planning through manuscript development, submission, and post-publication tracking. Captures strategic planning elements (target journals/congresses, authorship strategy, data disclosure timelines aligned with regulatory milestones, medical writing resource allocation, approval workflow, publication plan by compound/therapeutic area) and execution tracking (publication type, journal/congress name, authors, therapeutic area, compound referenced, submission date, acceptance date, publication date, publication status from planned through published, impact factor, citation metrics). Supports integrated publication planning, scientific communication tracking, evidence dissemination measurement, and publication gap analysis across medical affairs and clinical development.' .

ind:MedicalHeorStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Medical Heor Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all evidence generation studies conducted or sponsored by medical affairs, encompassing Health Economics and Outcomes Research (HEOR), Real-World Evidence (RWE), and Real-World Data (RWD) studies. Captures study type (cost-effectiveness, budget impact, quality of life, burden of disease, retrospective cohort, prospective registry, claims analysis, EHR study), study design, therapeutic area, data sources (claims, EHR, registry, survey), target audience (payer, regulator, HCP), regulatory use intent (label expansion, post-marketing commitment, payer submission), IRB/ethics approval status, patient population, primary and secondary endpoints, study status, key findings, and publication linkage. Single source of truth for ALL medical affairs-sponsored evidence generation activities including both economic modeling and real-world data studies. Supports market access, payer engagement, regulatory submissions, and scientific communication.' .

ind:MedEducationProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Med Education Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for medical education programs including continuing medical education (CME), disease awareness programs, scientific symposia, and speaker bureau programs. Captures program definition (type, therapeutic area, target audience, accreditation status, faculty roster, budget, compliance review) and attendance records (attendee identity, attendance date, format, accreditation credits earned, post-program survey responses, follow-up engagement triggered). Enables measurement of medical education reach, scientific impact, and HCP engagement effectiveness.' .

ind:MedicalAdvisoryBoard rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Medical Advisory Board' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for scientific and medical advisory boards convened by the company. Captures board definition (type, therapeutic area focus, strategic objectives, member roster, chairperson, meeting cadence, FMV compensation structure) and individual meeting instances (meeting date, location/platform, agenda topics, attendee list, quorum status, key scientific insights captured, action items, minutes approval status). Tracks advisory board governance, compliance with fair market value requirements, and transparency reporting obligations for HCP honoraria.' .

ind:Content rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Content' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all approved medical and scientific content assets including standard response letters (SRLs), medical information letters, slide decks, scientific dossiers, disease backgrounders, clinical evidence summaries, and scientific communication platforms (evidence-based messaging frameworks that define core scientific narratives, key messages, and approved claims per therapeutic area and compound). Captures content type, therapeutic area, compound referenced, key scientific messages, supporting evidence references, approved claims, platform hierarchy (disease-level, compound-level, indication-level), approval status, version number, effective date, expiry date, and regulatory/medical/legal review outcome. Serves as the authoritative source for consistent scientific communication across MSL interactions, publications, medical education, and medical information responses. Sourced from Veeva MedComms content management workflows.' .

ind:CongressEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Congress Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for medical and scientific congresses, conferences, and symposia. Captures congress definition (name, organizer, therapeutic area focus, location, dates, strategic importance tier, abstract submission deadlines) and company participation activities (oral presentations, posters, symposia, satellite meetings, booth presence, presenting authors/MSLs, abstract titles, compounds featured, attendance counts, post-congress follow-up actions). Enables medical affairs congress planning, resource allocation, and scientific communication output tracking.' .

ind:AffairsPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Affairs Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Strategic medical affairs plan for a therapeutic area, product, or compound over a defined planning cycle (annual or multi-year). Captures strategic objectives, evidence generation priorities, publication milestones, KOL engagement targets, MSL deployment strategy, medical education initiatives, HEOR priorities, and budget allocation. Serves as the master planning document bridging clinical development and commercial launch readiness.' .

ind:NamedPatientRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Named Patient Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of compassionate use, expanded access, and named patient program (NPP) requests for investigational or pre-approval compounds. Captures requesting physician, patient demographics (anonymized per GDPR/HIPAA), indication, compound requested, dosage regimen, regulatory pathway used (FDA expanded access, EMA compassionate use, hospital exemption, Article 83), ethics committee approval status, supply fulfillment status, treatment duration, outcome reporting, and safety monitoring obligations including expedited ICSR reporting requirements. Bridges medical affairs, regulatory, pharmacovigilance, and supply chain.' .

ind:Grant rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Grant' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for independent medical education grants and charitable contributions to medical societies, academic institutions, and patient advocacy organizations. Captures grant type (IME grant, charitable donation, sponsorship), recipient organization, therapeutic area, grant amount, grant purpose, compliance review status, fair market value assessment, and reporting obligations. Distinct from iit_grant which covers investigator-initiated research funding.' .

ind:EvidenceGap rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Evidence Gap' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record tracking identified evidence gaps in the scientific knowledge base for a compound or therapeutic area. Captures gap description, gap type (clinical efficacy, clinical safety, health economic, real-world effectiveness, mechanistic/biomarker, patient-reported outcomes), source of gap identification (payer feedback, regulatory request, publication gap analysis, advisory board insight), therapeutic area, compound, priority tier, proposed study type to address the gap, responsible medical affairs function, target resolution timeline, and current status. Drives evidence generation strategy, HEOR/RWE study prioritization, and integrated evidence planning.' .

ind:Patent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Patent' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master record for all pharmaceutical patents owned or licensed by the company. Captures patent number, title, filing/grant/expiry dates, patent family reference, jurisdiction, patent type (composition of matter, method of use, formulation, process, polymorph, salt form), covered compound (INN/USAN), therapeutic area, legal status, and assignee. Also serves as the anchor for trade secrets and know-how records via asset classification. SSOT for the IP portfolio — anchors lifecycle management, LOE planning, litigation defense, and generic/biosimilar entry strategy.' .

ind:PatentClaim rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Patent Claim' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual claims within a granted or pending patent, capturing claim number, claim type (independent, dependent), claim text, claim scope classification (broad, narrow, genus, species), and validity status. Critical for freedom-to-operate analyses, infringement assessments, and generic/biosimilar entry defense strategies. Each claim has its own legal standing and may be challenged independently during inter partes review (IPR) or opposition proceedings.' .

ind:PatentFamily rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Patent Family' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Groups related patents and patent applications filed across multiple jurisdictions that share a common priority application. Tracks the priority application number, priority date, PCT application number, family type (simple, extended, INPADOC), and member count. Enables portfolio-level analysis of global IP coverage for a given invention and supports lifecycle management across jurisdictions.' .

ind:ExclusivityPeriod rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Exclusivity Period' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks all regulatory exclusivity periods granted to pharmaceutical products, distinct from patent protection. Covers orphan drug exclusivity (7 years US / 10 years EU), data exclusivity (5 years NCE / 3 years new indication), pediatric exclusivity extension (6 months), new chemical entity exclusivity, biologics exclusivity (12 years US), and REMS exclusivity. Captures exclusivity type, granting authority (FDA, EMA, PMDA), start date, expiry date, product reference, and associated NDA/BLA/MAA number. Critical for lifecycle management and generic/biosimilar entry defense.' .

ind:Trademark rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Trademark' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all pharmaceutical trademark registrations including brand names, logos, trade dress, and slogans. Captures trademark name, registration number, filing date, registration date, expiry/renewal date, jurisdiction, Nice classification, goods and services description, trademark type (word mark, figurative, combined), owner entity, and current status (pending, registered, opposed, cancelled). Supports brand protection strategy and commercial launch activities.' .

ind:DrugMasterFile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Drug Master File' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for Drug Master Files (DMFs) submitted to regulatory authorities. Covers Type I-V DMFs (manufacturing site, drug substance/API, packaging, excipient, reference information). Captures DMF number, type, holder, submission/amendment dates, regulatory authority, active status, and associated substance. Supports CMC submissions and third-party API/excipient qualification for regulatory filings.' .

ind:LicensingAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Licensing Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all IP licensing agreements (in-licensing, out-licensing, cross-licensing, co-development, collaboration) including deal terms, milestone obligations, and milestone payment tracking. Captures agreement type, parties, licensed assets, territory, field of use, exclusivity scope, royalty structure, milestone events (regulatory filing, IND submission, phase completion, NDA approval, first commercial sale, sales thresholds), milestone descriptions, trigger events, milestone due dates, achieved dates, milestone payment amounts, currency, payment status, responsible party, sublicensing rights, and termination conditions. Supports deal management, milestone tracking, revenue recognition (ASC 606), royalty accounting, and partner relationship management.' .

ind:RoyaltyPayment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Royalty Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of royalty payments made or received under licensing agreements. Captures payment date, payment direction (inbound/outbound), royalty basis (net sales, units sold), royalty rate applied, calculation period, gross sales, net sales, deductions, royalty amount, currency, payment status, and reconciliation status. Supports financial reporting, royalty audits, and compliance with licensing agreement terms.' .

ind:FtoAnalysis rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Fto Analysis' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Freedom-to-Operate (FTO) analysis and competitive IP watch records. Covers FTO assessments determining whether a product, process, or technology can be commercialized without infringing third-party IP rights, plus ongoing monitoring of competitor IP activities (patent filings, ANDA/505(b)(2) submissions, biosimilar applications, patent challenges). Captures analysis title, scope, requestor, conducting attorney or firm, analysis date, product or technology assessed, jurisdictions covered, identified blocking patents, risk level, recommended actions, final opinion, watch type, competitor identity, filing dates, reference numbers, technology area, affected products, and threat assessment. Supports go/no-go decisions for product development, commercial launch, and proactive IP defense strategy.' .

ind:PatentLitigation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Patent Litigation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks active and historical patent litigation cases including Paragraph IV ANDA challenges, inter partes review (IPR) petitions, post-grant review (PGR), patent infringement suits, and declaratory judgment actions. Captures case number, court or tribunal, case type, filing date, parties (plaintiff, defendant), asserted patents, accused products, litigation status, key milestones, outside counsel, estimated liability, and outcome. Critical for generic/biosimilar entry defense strategy and legal budget management.' .

ind:PatentProsecution rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Patent Prosecution' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks patent application prosecution workflow from filing through grant or abandonment, including all annuity and maintenance fee payment obligations across all jurisdictions. Captures application number, prosecution stage, patent office, examiner, office actions received, response deadlines, prosecution attorney, prosecution strategy, and complete annuity/maintenance fee history (fee year, due dates, amounts, currencies, payment status, paying agents, confirmation receipts, grace periods, surcharge amounts). Failure to pay annuities results in patent lapse. Supports docketing, deadline management, fee compliance, cost tracking, portfolio maintenance operations, and annuity budget forecasting.' .

ind:SpcFiling rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Spc Filing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Supplementary Protection Certificate (SPC) filings that extend patent protection for pharmaceutical products beyond the standard patent term to compensate for time lost during regulatory approval. Captures SPC application number, filing date, granting authority (national patent office), basic patent reference, marketing authorization number, product covered, SPC duration, expiry date, and status. Relevant primarily in EU, UK, and other jurisdictions offering SPC protection.' .

ind:PatentTermExtension rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Patent Term Extension' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all patent term extension and supplementary protection mechanisms across global jurisdictions that compensate for regulatory review time lost during drug approval. Covers US Hatch-Waxman Patent Term Extension (PTE), EU/UK Supplementary Protection Certificates (SPC), Japanese patent term extension, and equivalent national mechanisms. Captures application number, mechanism type (PTE, SPC, national equivalent), filing date, patent reference, product reference, marketing authorization reference, regulatory review period, calculated/granted extension duration, adjusted expiry date, granting authority, decision status, SPC-specific fields (basic patent, product definition per Article 1(b)), and pediatric extension eligibility. Single source of truth for all patent term adjustments — critical for accurate LOE date calculation across all markets.' .

ind:IpWatch rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Ip Watch' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Competitive intelligence records tracking third-party IP activities that may threaten the company\'s portfolio. Monitors competitor patent filings, ANDA/505(b)(2) submissions, biosimilar applications (aBLA), and patent challenges. Captures watch type, competitor, filing date, reference number, technology area, affected products, risk assessment, and recommended response. Supports proactive IP defense and early warning for generic/biosimilar entry.' .

ind:IpValuation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Ip Valuation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Financial valuation records for IP assets including patents, trademarks, trade secrets, and know-how portfolios. Used for balance sheet reporting (IAS 38 intangible asset recognition), M&A due diligence, licensing negotiations, tax transfer pricing, and impairment testing. Captures valuation date, valuation method (income approach/DCF, market approach, cost approach, relief-from-royalty), IP asset reference, valuation currency, fair market value, useful economic life, amortization method, carrying value, discount rate, and valuation firm. Supports R&D capitalization decisions and SOX-compliant financial reporting.' .

ind:InventionDisclosure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Invention Disclosure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Internal invention disclosure records submitted by R&D scientists and engineers as the first step in the patent filing process. Captures disclosure number, title, inventors, submission date, business unit, technology area, compound or process described, novelty assessment, commercial relevance assessment, IP committee review status, recommended action (file patent, maintain as trade secret, publish defensively, abandon), and decision date. Bridges R&D innovation with IP prosecution workflow.' .

ind:OrangeBookListing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Orange Book Listing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of patents and exclusivities listed in the FDA Orange Book (Approved Drug Products with Therapeutic Equivalence Evaluations) for each NDA/ANDA product. Captures NDA number, product name, active ingredient, dosage form, strength, listed patent number, patent expiry date, exclusivity code, exclusivity expiry date, and listing status. Directly governs generic entry timelines and Paragraph IV challenge eligibility. Analogous listings for EU (Article 10 reference) and other markets are also captured.' .

ind:AnnuityFee rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Annuity Fee' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks patent annuity (maintenance fee) payment obligations and payment history across all jurisdictions for the patent portfolio. Captures patent reference, jurisdiction, fee year, due date, fee amount, currency, payment date, payment status (paid, overdue, waived, lapsed), paying agent, and confirmation receipt number. Failure to pay annuities results in patent lapse, making this a critical operational record for portfolio maintenance.' .

ind:IpAgreementMilestone rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Ip Agreement Milestone' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks milestone events and payment obligations under licensing, co-development, and collaboration agreements tied to IP assets. Captures milestone type (regulatory filing, IND submission, Phase I completion, NDA approval, first commercial sale, sales threshold), milestone description, trigger event, due date, achieved date, milestone payment amount, currency, payment status, and responsible party. Supports deal management, revenue recognition, and partner relationship management.' .

ind:Submission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Submission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record and single source of truth for all regulatory submissions (filing events) to health authorities including original applications, supplements, amendments, responses to information requests, and annual reports. Each submission represents a discrete eCTD sequence filed under a parent application. Tracks submission type, sequence number, dossier format (eCTD), submission date, target agency, eCTD lifecycle operation (new, replace, append, delete), submission medium, validation status, regulatory pathway, priority designation, and current lifecycle status. Includes document-level composition tracking with CTD module/section assignment (Modules 1-5), individual document metadata (title, type, version, author, status, file format, checksum), version control, and dossier completeness assessment aligned with ICH M4 (CTD structure) and M8 (eCTD technical specification). SSOT for regulatory submission identity, lifecycle, sequence tracking, dossier content, and document inventory in Veeva Vault RIM.' .

ind:HealthAuthority rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Health Authority' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for all global health authority agencies with which the company interacts, including FDA, EMA, PMDA, MHRA, NMPA, WHO, and national competent authorities. Captures agency name, acronym, jurisdiction, country/region, agency type, contact details, submission portal URL, accepted dossier formats, and applicable regulatory frameworks. Enables consistent agency identification across all regulatory activities.' .

ind:Application rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Application' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for a regulatory application (IND, NDA, BLA, MAA, ANDA, 510k) representing the formal dossier filed with a health authority for a specific drug product. Tracks application number assigned by the agency, application type, applicant entity, lead product, therapeutic indication, regulatory pathway, orphan designation status, priority review status, PDUFA/action date, and overall approval status. One application may have multiple submissions (original + supplements).' .

ind:SubmissionSequence rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Submission Sequence' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks individual eCTD submission sequences within a regulatory application, representing each discrete filing event (original submission, amendment, response to information request, annual report, supplement). Captures sequence number, submission date, submission type (original, class I/II supplement, CBE, PAS), eCTD lifecycle operation (new, replace, append), submission medium, and validation status. Aligns with ICH M8 eCTD technical specification.' .

ind:Milestone rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Milestone' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks key regulatory milestones and target dates for submissions and applications, including IND filing date, End-of-Phase 2 meeting, NDA/BLA filing date, PDUFA date, advisory committee meeting, complete response letter (CRL) receipt, approval date, and post-approval commitment due dates. Captures planned vs. actual dates, milestone type, responsible owner, and completion status. Critical for regulatory project management and timeline tracking.' .

ind:Approval rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Approval' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records formal regulatory approvals and marketing authorizations granted by health authorities for drug products. Captures approval date, approval type (full, accelerated, conditional, provisional), approved indication, approved dosage form and strength, approved patient population, approval conditions, post-approval commitments, and approval certificate reference. SSOT for product approval status across all markets. Links to application and health authority.' .

ind:HaInteraction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Ha Interaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Single source of truth for ALL formal interactions and communications with health authorities including Type A/B/C meetings (FDA), scientific advice (EMA), pre-submission meetings, advisory committee meetings, and all written correspondence (information requests, complete response letters, deficiency letters, acknowledgment letters, approval letters, agency queries, and general regulatory correspondence). Captures interaction type, format (in-person, teleconference, written), direction (inbound/outbound), dates, participants, discussion topics, agreed outcomes, response deadlines, follow-up actions, correspondence tracking numbers, document references, and response timeline compliance. Consolidates both meeting-based and written communications into a single chronological record per application. SSOT for all health authority communications — no separate correspondence product exists. Sourced from Veeva Vault RIM correspondence and meeting modules.' .

ind:Correspondence rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Correspondence' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manages all formal written correspondence exchanged with health authorities including information requests (IR), complete response letters (CRL), deficiency letters, acknowledgment letters, approval letters, and agency queries. Captures correspondence type, direction (inbound/outbound), receipt or send date, response due date, response date, subject matter, associated submission or application, and document reference in Veeva Vault. Tracks response timelines for compliance with agency deadlines.' .

ind:Dmf rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Dmf' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Drug Master File (DMF) registry tracking all DMFs filed with health authorities for APIs, excipients, packaging materials, and manufacturing sites. Captures DMF number, DMF type (Type I-V), holder name, subject of DMF, filing date, last annual update date, authorization letters issued, and associated products referencing the DMF. Supports CMC regulatory strategy and third-party supplier qualification. Aligns with 21 CFR 314.420 and EMA DMF guidelines.' .

ind:Label rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Label' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Single source of truth for approved product labeling (prescribing information, package insert, patient information leaflet, SmPC) and complete change history across all markets and languages. Tracks current label version, effective date, approval date, market/country, language, label type, content sections, and lifecycle status. Maintains full amendment history including change reason (safety update, new indication, dosage modification, black box warning), change type (agency-initiated, company-initiated), regulatory basis, affected sections, submission reference, and implementation status across markets. SSOT for both current approved labeling and all historical label changes — no separate label change product exists. Integrates with Veeva Vault PromoMats and RIM.' .

ind:LabelChange rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Label Change' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks all label changes and labeling amendments including the reason for change, change type (safety update, new indication, dosage modification, black box warning addition), regulatory basis, submission reference, effective date, and implementation status across markets. Captures the specific sections modified, change description, and whether the change was agency-initiated or company-initiated. Critical for pharmacovigilance-driven label updates and post-approval lifecycle management.' .

ind:Rems rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Rems' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Risk Evaluation and Mitigation Strategy (REMS) program master record for products requiring FDA-mandated risk management programs. Captures REMS program name, associated NDA/BLA, REMS elements (medication guide, communication plan, ETASU), program approval date, assessment schedule, enrollment requirements, certified pharmacy/prescriber requirements, and program status. Tracks REMS modifications and assessment submission history. Specific to FDA-regulated products under 21 CFR 314.520.' .

ind:PostApprovalCommitment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Post Approval Commitment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Single source of truth for all post-approval commitments, post-marketing requirements (PMR/PMC), and their granular fulfillment actions. Tracks commitment type (PMR, PMC, Phase IV study, label update, stability study), description, due dates, agency-assigned tracking number, and individual action-level tasks (protocol submission, interim reports, final study reports) with responsible functions, deliverable types, due dates, completion dates, and status. Monitors compliance with FDA PMR/PMC requirements under FDAAA and EMA post-authorization measures. Provides both executive-level commitment status and operational task-level progress tracking in a single entity. SSOT for all regulatory obligation tracking — no separate action-level product exists.' .

ind:Pai rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Pai' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Pre-Approval Inspection (PAI) record tracking FDA and other agency inspections of manufacturing facilities conducted as part of NDA/BLA review. Captures inspection type (PAI, GMP, for-cause), facility inspected, inspection dates, lead investigator, inspection outcome (VAI, NAI, OAI), observations (483 items), response due date, and final classification. Links to the associated application and manufacturing site. Critical for approval readiness tracking.' .

ind:Strategy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Strategy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Documents the regulatory strategy for each drug development program, capturing the planned regulatory pathway, target product profile (TPP), key regulatory risks, agency engagement plan, global filing sequence, priority markets, expedited program designations pursued (Breakthrough, Fast Track, PRIME, Sakigake), competitive landscape considerations, and strategic rationale. Serves as the authoritative regulatory plan linking development programs to submission plans and commercial launch timelines. Managed within Veeva Vault RIM.' .

ind:DossierDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Dossier Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks individual documents within an eCTD dossier organized by CTD module and section (Module 1-5). Captures document title, CTD section code, document type, version, author, creation date, approval date, document status, file format, file size, checksum, and Veeva Vault document ID. Supports dossier compilation, completeness review, and submission readiness assessment. Aligns with ICH CTD structure (M4) and eCTD technical specification (M8).' .

ind:Designation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Designation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks special regulatory designations and expedited program grants for drug products including FDA Breakthrough Therapy, Fast Track, Accelerated Approval, Priority Review, Orphan Drug Designation (ODD), Rare Pediatric Disease, EMA PRIME, and PMDA Sakigake. Captures designation type, granting agency, request date, grant date, expiry date, associated product and indication, and designation-specific benefits and obligations. Critical for regulatory strategy and commercial planning.' .

ind:Variation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Variation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks post-approval variations and supplements to marketing authorizations including Type IA, IB, and II variations (EMA), CBE-0, CBE-30, and PAS supplements (FDA), and equivalent changes in other markets. Captures variation type, change description, affected CTD sections, submission date, approval date, implementation date, and regulatory basis. Manages the lifecycle of approved product changes across global markets. Sourced from Veeva Vault RIM variation management module.' .

ind:ProductRegistration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Product Registration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Single source of truth for country-level product registration master tracking the marketing authorization status, complete renewal lifecycle, and maintenance calendar of each drug product in each country/market. Captures registration number, country, registration holder, registration date, expiry date, approved indication, approved dosage forms and strengths, local brand name, and registration status (active, suspended, withdrawn, expired). Includes complete renewal tracking: renewal type (5-year, annual, sunset clause), renewal due dates, submission dates, approval dates, fee payment status, and renewal outcomes. Manages the renewal calendar across all markets to prevent registration lapse. SSOT for global product registration footprint, renewal compliance, and commercial continuity — no separate renewal product exists.' .

ind:Renewal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Renewal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks marketing authorization renewal activities required to maintain product registrations in force. Captures renewal type (5-year renewal, annual renewal, sunset clause), renewal due date, submission date, approval date, renewal fee payment status, and renewal outcome. Manages the renewal calendar across all markets to prevent registration lapse. Links to product_registration and submission records. Critical for commercial continuity and supply chain planning.' .

ind:CommitmentAction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Commitment Action' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular action-level tracking for post-approval commitments and regulatory obligations, capturing individual tasks required to fulfill a commitment (e.g., protocol submission, interim report, final study report, label update). Tracks action description, due date, responsible function, completion date, deliverable type, and submission reference. Provides operational visibility into commitment fulfillment progress at the task level, complementing the higher-level post_approval_commitment record.' .

ind:MolecularTarget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Molecular Target' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for biological molecular targets identified during drug discovery, including proteins, enzymes, receptors, ion channels, and nucleic acids. Captures target class, gene name, UniProt/Ensembl identifiers, mechanism of action (MOA), therapeutic area relevance, target validation status, druggability assessment, and disease association. Authoritative SSOT for all target identification data entering the discovery pipeline from IDBS/Dotmatics ELN.' .

ind:Compound rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Compound' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all chemical and biological compounds in the discovery compound library, including NCEs (New Chemical Entities) and NBEs (New Biological Entities). Captures compound identity (IUPAC name, INN/USAN, registration number, CAS number), structural representation (molecular formula, molecular weight, SMILES, InChI), compound class (small molecule, biologic, peptide, ADC), source (synthesized, purchased, natural product), physicochemical properties (purity, physical state, storage conditions), and library membership. Authoritative SSOT for compound identity and structure across the discovery domain.' .

ind:Assay rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Assay' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for biological and biochemical assays used in drug discovery screening and profiling. Captures assay name, assay type (biochemical, cell-based, phenotypic, ADME, toxicity), assay format (HTS, dose-response, selectivity), target association, assay technology platform (HTRF, AlphaScreen, SPR, NMR), assay validation status, GLP compliance flag, detection method, assay protocol reference, throughput capacity, and responsible scientist. Sourced from IDBS/Dotmatics ELN.' .

ind:HtsCampaign rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Hts Campaign' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for High-Throughput Screening (HTS) campaigns executed against compound libraries. Captures campaign name, target or assay being screened, compound library used, screening format (primary, confirmatory, counter-screen), campaign status, start and end dates, number of compounds screened, hit rate, assay window (Z-prime factor), screening technology platform, CRO involvement flag, and campaign owner. Central operational entity for HTS execution tracking.' .

ind:ScreeningResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Screening Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing individual compound screening results from HTS campaigns, dose-response assays, and selectivity panels. Captures compound, assay, and campaign references, plate/well position, raw signal, percent inhibition/activation, potency values (IC50/EC50/Ki), Hill slope, curve fit quality (R-squared), result classification (active, inactive, inconclusive, toxic, hit, confirmed hit, false positive), selectivity score, replicate number, run date, and data quality flags. Includes hit-to-lead eligibility determination. Distinct from in_vitro_study: screening_result covers primary and confirmatory screening at scale; in_vitro_study covers deeper mechanistic follow-up on selected compounds.' .

ind:SarStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Sar Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for Structure-Activity Relationship (SAR) studies conducted to understand how structural modifications to a compound affect its biological activity. Captures study name, lead series identifier, target identifier, SAR hypothesis, key structural features analyzed, number of analogs synthesized, potency range observed, selectivity findings, ADME impact, study status, lead scientist, and ELN notebook reference from IDBS/Dotmatics. Core entity for medicinal chemistry optimization.' .

ind:LeadSeries rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Lead Series' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for chemical lead series progressing through hit-to-lead and lead optimization stages. Captures series name, scaffold/chemotype description, originating HTS campaign, primary target, series status (hit-to-lead, lead optimization, deprioritized, nominated), best-in-class compound identifier, potency benchmark, selectivity profile, ADME profile summary, IP landscape assessment, therapeutic area, program code, and stage-gate progression history with decision rationale. Central entity for tracking medicinal chemistry progression and compound governance decisions from hit confirmation through candidate nomination.' .

ind:CompoundSynthesis rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Compound Synthesis' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the synthesis of individual compounds by medicinal chemistry teams. Captures compound identifier, synthesis route identifier, synthetic method, reagents used, reaction conditions (temperature, solvent, catalyst), yield percentage, purity by HPLC/NMR, batch number, synthesis date, synthesizing chemist, ELN experiment reference from IDBS/Dotmatics, and GLP compliance flag. Tracks the manufacturing provenance of discovery compounds.' .

ind:AdmeProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Adme Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing ADME (Absorption, Distribution, Metabolism, Excretion) profiling results for compounds under evaluation. Captures compound identifier, assay panel used, solubility value, permeability (Caco-2/PAMPA), plasma protein binding, microsomal stability (human/rat liver microsomes), CYP inhibition profile, P-glycoprotein substrate flag, blood-brain barrier penetration, half-life, clearance rate, bioavailability estimate, assay date, and ADME scientist. Critical for compound progression decisions.' .

ind:Project rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Project' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for drug discovery research projects organized around one or more therapeutic targets or disease indications. Captures project name, project code, therapeutic area, disease indication (ICD-10/MeSH reference), primary and secondary target identifiers (supporting multi-target programs), project phase (target identification, target validation, hit identification, hit-to-lead, lead optimization, candidate nomination), project status, start date, projected candidate nomination date, project leader, team members, budget allocation, strategic priority tier, external collaboration references, and portfolio governance decisions. Top-level organizational entity for the discovery domain providing project-centric views of all discovery activities.' .

ind:TargetValidationStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Target Validation Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for studies conducted to validate a molecular target\'s role in disease and its suitability for drug intervention. Captures target identifier, validation method (genetic knockdown/knockout, overexpression, chemical probe, patient genetics), model system used (cell line, animal model, patient-derived), validation evidence level (strong, moderate, weak), disease linkage evidence, publication references, study outcome, validation scientist, and study completion date. Supports go/no-go decisions on target investment.' .

ind:InVitroStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'In Vitro Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for in vitro mechanistic and safety studies conducted on selected compounds post-screening, including mechanism of action confirmation, pathway modulation, cell viability, and early cytotoxicity assessments. Captures study type, biological system (cell line, primary cells, organoids), compound and concentration range, endpoint measured, result values, cytotoxicity flag, protocol reference, GLP compliance flag, study date, and responsible scientist. Distinct from screening_result: in_vitro_study covers hypothesis-driven follow-up studies on prioritized compounds rather than high-throughput screening at scale.' .

ind:InVivoStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'In Vivo Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for in vivo animal studies conducted during discovery to assess compound efficacy, PK/PD relationships, and early tolerability. Captures study type (efficacy, PK, PD, tolerability), animal species and strain, study design (dose, route, frequency, duration), compound identifier, dose levels, PK parameters (Cmax, AUC, t1/2, Vd, CL), efficacy endpoints, tolerability observations, study status, GLP compliance flag, IACUC protocol number, study director, and study completion date.' .

ind:CandidateNomination rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Candidate Nomination' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the formal nomination of a development candidate (DC) compound for progression from discovery into preclinical development. Captures nominated compound identifier, lead series identifier, discovery project identifier, nomination date, therapeutic area, target, proposed indication, key efficacy data summary, key safety data summary, ADME/PK profile summary, IP status, CMC feasibility assessment, nomination decision (approved, deferred, rejected), decision committee, and handoff date to preclinical team. Critical milestone event linking discovery to clinical development pipeline.' .

ind:ComputationalModel rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Computational Model' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for computational and in silico models supporting drug discovery decisions. Covers QSAR, molecular docking, virtual screening, pharmacophore models, PK/PD models, ADMET prediction, and AI/ML property prediction. Captures model name, type, target or property predicted, algorithm, training dataset, performance metrics (AUC, RMSE, enrichment factor), PK/PD parameters (Emax, EC50, Hill coefficient, compartment structure) where applicable, validation status, software platform, model owner, and deployment status. Supports computational chemistry, pharmacometrics, and AI-driven compound design.' .

ind:Trial rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each clinical trial (study) conducted by Pharmaceuticals, covering all phases (I–IV). Captures investigational product, therapeutic area, phase, study design (randomized, blinded, open-label), primary and secondary endpoints (ORR, PFS, OS, QoL), IND/CTA reference numbers, EudraCT/NCT identifiers, sponsor, CRO partner, planned vs. actual start/end dates, GCP compliance status, regulatory submission references (IND, NDA, BLA, MAA), overall trial lifecycle state, and key operational milestones (FPFV, LPLV, database lock, CSR completion, interim analysis dates) with planned vs. actual tracking and variance commentary. Authoritative SSOT for all trial-level metadata and timeline milestones consumed by regulatory submissions and eTMF in Veeva Vault.' .

ind:Protocol rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Protocol' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal clinical trial protocol document master, representing each approved version of the study protocol. Tracks protocol number, version, amendment history and rationale, approval date, IRB/IEC approval reference, study objectives (primary, secondary, exploratory), inclusion/exclusion criteria, dosing regimen, visit schedule (schedule of assessments), randomization design (scheme type, stratification factors, allocation ratio, blinding method), statistical analysis plan reference, sample size justification, and GCP compliance attestation. Linked to the parent trial and managed in Veeva Vault eTMF. Each amendment creates a new versioned protocol record with change justification.' .

ind:InvestigationalSite rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Investigational Site' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each clinical investigational site (hospital, clinic, research center) participating in one or more trials. Captures site name, address, country, site number, IRB/IEC of record, site activation milestones (feasibility, selection, SIV, FPFV target), site closure date, enrollment capacity, GCP inspection history, site status (selected, activated, enrolling, on-hold, closed), regulatory authority jurisdiction, and CRA assignment for site initiation and ongoing oversight. Serves as the geographic and operational anchor for site-level enrollment, monitoring, and IMP accountability activities.' .

ind:PrincipalInvestigator rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Principal Investigator' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each Principal Investigator (PI) and sub-investigator responsible for conducting a clinical trial at a site. Captures investigator name, medical license number, specialty, GCP training certification date, CV reference, financial disclosure status, delegation log reference, and regulatory authority registration. Distinct from the HCP domain (which covers commercial HCP engagement) — this entity is specifically scoped to GCP-regulated trial conduct roles.' .

ind:ClinicalEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Clinical Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing each subject\'s complete enrollment and randomization journey within a clinical trial. Tracks screening number, subject number, enrollment date, informed consent confirmation, eligibility assessment (inclusion/exclusion criteria verification), screen failure reason, randomization date, randomization code, treatment arm assignment, stratification factors, blinding status, allocation ratio, block size reference, unblinding event details (if applicable), and enrollment/randomization status (screened, screen-failed, enrolled, randomized, withdrawn, completed). Supports ITT, modified ITT, and per-protocol population definitions. Authoritative SSOT for all subject-level randomization data including scheme parameters and individual assignments. Sourced from Medidata Rave RTSM (Randomization and Trial Supply Management) and Oracle CTMS.' .

ind:Visit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Visit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for each scheduled or unscheduled patient visit within a clinical trial, as captured in the EDC (Medidata Rave). Tracks visit number, visit name per protocol schedule of assessments, planned visit date, actual visit date, visit window compliance, visit type (screening, treatment, follow-up, end-of-study), visit status, and deviations noted. Forms the backbone of the clinical data collection timeline.' .

ind:CrfForm rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Crf Form' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each Case Report Form (CRF) design used in a trial, representing the electronic data capture instrument definition in Medidata Rave. Captures form name, form OID, associated visit, data domain (SDTM domain mapping), version, validation rules, completion requirements, and approval status. Distinct from CRF data (captured in subject_observation) — this is the instrument definition, not the collected data.' .

ind:SubjectObservation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Subject Observation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core transactional table capturing all clinical data collected per subject per visit per CRF form in the EDC (Medidata Rave). Stores data point value, unit, SDTM variable mapping, collection date, data entry date, query status, source data verification (SDV) status, and audit trail reference. Represents the atomic unit of clinical trial data — the foundation for efficacy and safety endpoint derivation (ORR, PFS, OS, QoL) and CDISC SDTM/ADaM dataset generation.' .

ind:TrialAdverseEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Adverse Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for each Adverse Event (AE) reported by a subject during a clinical trial, as captured in the EDC and CTMS. Captures AE term (MedDRA coded), onset date, resolution date, severity grade (CTCAE), seriousness flag (SAE), causality assessment, action taken (dose modification, discontinuation), outcome, and SAE/SUSAR reporting status. Distinct from the pharmacovigilance domain\'s ICSR — this is the trial-level AE record feeding into safety reporting workflows.' .

ind:TrialConsent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Consent' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing each informed consent event for a trial subject, including consent form version, consent date, re-consent date (if protocol amended), subject signature confirmation, legally authorized representative details (if applicable), consent withdrawal date, and IRB/IEC approval reference for the consent version used. Ensures GCP-compliant documentation of subject autonomy and regulatory traceability.' .

ind:InvestigationalProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Investigational Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each investigational medicinal product (IMP) and comparator used in clinical trials, including drug substance name (INN/USAN), formulation, dosage form, strength, route of administration, manufacturer, batch/lot number, expiry date, storage conditions (cold-chain requirements), blinding configuration (matching placebo details), IND/IMPD reference, dispensation tracking (quantity dispensed, return, destruction), and accountability log reference. Distinct from the commercial product catalog (owned by the product domain) — this entity is scoped to GCP-regulated IMP accountability, trial supply management, and regulatory compliance per ICH E6 R2 section 8.' .

ind:TrialEndpoint rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Endpoint' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the formal assessment of primary and secondary clinical endpoints for each subject at defined timepoints. Captures endpoint name (ORR, PFS, OS, QoL, DOR), assessment date, assessment method (RECIST, BICR, investigator assessment), result value, unit, response category, and adjudication committee review status. Feeds directly into efficacy analyses for NDA/BLA/MAA submissions.' .

ind:LabResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Lab Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for each central or local laboratory test result collected during a clinical trial. Captures lab test name (LOINC coded), specimen type, collection date, result value, unit, reference range, normal/abnormal flag, clinically significant flag, out-of-range flag, and laboratory accreditation reference. Sourced from central lab data transfers into Medidata Rave. Distinct from manufacturing LIMS results — this is trial-specific clinical lab data.' .

ind:TrialMilestone rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Milestone' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record tracking key operational milestones for each clinical trial, including FPFV (First Patient First Visit), LPLV (Last Patient Last Visit), database lock date, CSR completion date, regulatory submission date, and interim analysis dates. Captures planned vs. actual dates, milestone status, responsible function, and variance commentary. Supports portfolio-level trial timeline management and regulatory commitment tracking.' .

ind:Icsr rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Icsr' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual Case Safety Report — the primary transactional record in pharmacovigilance. Captures all adverse event/adverse drug reaction reports from healthcare professionals, patients, literature, clinical trials, and spontaneous sources. Stores case identifiers (worldwide unique case ID), report type (spontaneous, literature, clinical trial, solicited, SAE), source channel, seriousness criteria, listedness assessment, causality assessment, narrative, regulatory clock start date, case processing status, and submission compliance. For literature-sourced cases, stores publication reference (PMID/DOI). For clinical trial cases, stores reconciliation status with EDC, dechallenge/rechallenge results, and site details. Includes version history tracking (initial, follow-up, nullification) with full audit trail per ICH E2B and 21 CFR Part 314. Includes de-identified patient demographics (age, sex, weight, medical history) per GDPR/HIPAA. Includes intake triage, minimum criteria validation, duplicate assessment outcome, and case assignment. SSOT for all individual safety cases. Supports regional requirements for FDA (MedWatch), EMA (EudraVigilance), PMDA (J-ICSR), NMPA, and TGA reporting. SLA-critical: 7-day and 15-day regulatory reporting deadlines.' .

ind:PvAdverseReaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pv Adverse Reaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Granular adverse event record linked to an ICSR. Captures the specific event term (MedDRA coded at PT, HLT, HLGT, SOC levels with version tracking), verbatim reporter term, onset date, resolution date, outcome (recovered, not recovered, fatal, unknown), seriousness criteria, severity grade (CTCAE where applicable), and listedness determination against reference safety information. Includes coding metadata: auto-coded vs manual review, coding date. One ICSR may contain multiple adverse events. Supports signal detection aggregation by MedDRA term and regulatory line listing generation.' .

ind:Susar rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Susar' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Suspected Unexpected Serious Adverse Reaction record for clinical trial expedited reporting. Captures SUSARs identified from clinical trial ICSRs meeting expedited criteria: unexpected (not in IB/RSI), serious, and at least possibly causally related. Stores parent ICSR reference, trial phase, investigational product, expectedness determination against current IB, causality assessment by sponsor and investigator, 7-day (fatal/life-threatening) or 15-day reporting clock, and submission status to authorities (FDA IND safety report, EMA SUSAR, MHRA, PMDA). SLA-critical: 7-day and 15-day expedited reporting deadlines with criminal liability for non-compliance.' .

ind:SaeReport rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Sae Report' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Serious Adverse Event report record capturing SAEs from clinical trials, post-market surveillance, and spontaneous sources. Stores SAE classification criteria (death, life-threatening, hospitalization, disability, congenital anomaly, medically important), time to onset, treatment given, dechallenge/rechallenge results, reporter information, site/investigator details, and reconciliation status with clinical trial EDC systems. Tracks the SAE from initial receipt through medical review, causality assessment, and regulatory submission. Supports reconciliation workflows between clinical database and PV safety database per ICH E2D guidance. SLA-critical: initial SAE notification within 24 hours of site awareness.' .

ind:PvSubmission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pv Submission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Regulatory submission record for all pharmacovigilance reports submitted to health authorities worldwide. Covers expedited individual case reports (7-day fatal/life-threatening, 15-day serious), periodic aggregate reports (PSUR, PBRER, PADER, DSUR), and ad-hoc safety communications. Stores submission type, target authority, submission date, acknowledgement status, error handling, submission format (E2B R2/R3 XML, eCTD), gateway/portal details, submission reference number, resubmission history, and compliance status. Supports all major regulatory gateways including EudraVigilance (EVWEB/gateway), FAERS (FDA), MHRA Sentinel, PMDA gateway, and NMPA. Tracks authority-specific technical requirements (E2B R3 for EMA, E2B R2 for some national authorities). SLA-critical: regulatory deadline compliance with automatic escalation.' .

ind:Psur rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Psur' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic aggregate safety report master record covering PSUR, PBRER (ICH E2C R2), PADER (FDA), and DSUR (development phase) for each product-indication combination. Captures data lock point, reporting interval, international birth date (IBD), cumulative exposure data, interval and cumulative case summaries, signal summary, benefit-risk evaluation conclusion, and submission status per applicable authority. Tracks preparation milestones, author assignments, medical review, QC, and approval workflow. Supports EU PSUR single assessment (PSUSA) process, FDA PADER requirements, and ICH DSUR for investigational products. Includes structured benefit-risk assessment sections. SLA-critical: fixed regulatory submission deadlines based on IBD.' .

ind:Rmp rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Rmp' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Risk Management Plan master record. Captures RMP version, scope (product, indication, population), safety specification (important identified risks, important potential risks, missing information), pharmacovigilance plan activities (routine and additional), risk minimization measures (routine and additional including REMS for US), effectiveness evaluation plan, and PASS commitments. Tracks RMP approval status per authority (EMA, MHRA) and version history. Supports EU GVP Module V template, FDA REMS requirements, and PMDA RMP format. Links to resulting PV actions and PASS study commitments.' .

ind:SafetySignal rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Safety Signal' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Safety signal record representing a new or evolving safety concern identified through signal detection activities. Captures signal source (spontaneous database, literature, clinical trial, real-world data), detection method (disproportionality analysis, clinical review, machine learning), MedDRA-coded term, signal strength metrics (PRR, ROR, EBGM, IC), and signal status lifecycle (new, under evaluation, validated, refuted, closed). Includes formal assessment records: methodology, data sources reviewed, benefit-risk impact evaluation, proposed label change recommendation, regulatory action required, PRAC/PSUR referral status, and final disposition. Each signal supports multiple assessment iterations. Tracks the full signal management workflow from detection through triage, validation, prioritization, assessment, and closure or regulatory action per GVP Module IX. SLA-critical: PRAC rapporteur notification timelines.' .

ind:PvProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pv Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Pharmacovigilance product master — the authoritative PV-domain view of medicinal products under safety surveillance. Captures product name, INN, ATC code, MAH (Marketing Authorization Holder), authorization numbers per country/region, formulation, route of administration, reference safety information document reference, international birth date (IBD), PSMF reference, QPPV assignment, and PV system governance metadata. Distinct from the commercial product catalog — this is the PV-specific product registration used for case processing, signal detection, PSUR scheduling, and regulatory reporting. Includes PSMF-level metadata: PV system description, organizational structure for pharmacovigilance, contracted party references, and compliance status per EU GVP Module II.' .

ind:SuspectDrug rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Suspect Drug' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Suspect and concomitant drug record within an ICSR. Captures drug name (verbatim and WHO Drug Dictionary coded), drug role (suspect, concomitant, interacting), dose, frequency, route, indication, start/stop dates, action taken (drug withdrawn, dose reduced, dose not changed, unknown), dechallenge result, rechallenge result, and batch/lot number. One ICSR may have multiple suspect and concomitant drugs. Enables product-level case aggregation for signal detection, line listing generation, and exposure-based analyses.' .

ind:Reporter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Reporter' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reporter master data — the individual or organization who submitted an adverse event report. Captures reporter type (healthcare professional, patient/consumer, lawyer, regulatory authority, literature), qualification (physician, pharmacist, nurse, dentist, consumer), country, institution, anonymized reporter identifier (per GDPR/HIPAA), contact preference for follow-up, and reporter reliability assessment. Enables reporter-level case aggregation, duplicate detection, follow-up management, and compliance with ICH E2B reporter data requirements. Distinct from HCP master — this is the PV-specific reporter identity used solely for case processing.' .

ind:PvAction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pv Action' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Pharmacovigilance action record capturing regulatory and safety actions taken in response to validated signals, PSUR findings, RMP updates, or authority requests. Action types include: labeling updates (CCDS, SmPC, USPI changes), DHPC (Dear Healthcare Professional Communication), restricted indication, market suspension/withdrawal, REMS modification, RMP update trigger, and PASS study initiation. Tracks action type, triggering event, responsible party, target completion date, authority notification requirement, implementation evidence, and effectiveness assessment. Links signals, PSURs, and RMPs to their downstream regulatory consequences.' .

ind:Rsi rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Rsi' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference Safety Information record — the authoritative document defining the expected adverse reaction profile for listedness/expectedness assessment. Captures RSI document type (Investigator\'s Brochure for trials, SmPC for EU, USPI for US, CCDS as company core), version, effective date, product scope, and the enumerated list of expected adverse reactions by MedDRA preferred term. Used in every ICSR to determine whether a reaction is listed (expected) or unlisted (unexpected), directly driving expedited reporting obligations and SUSAR determination. Version-controlled with effective dating to support point-in-time listedness assessment.' .

ind:PvAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pv Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Pharmacovigilance agreement record governing safety data exchange obligations between the MAH and partners. Covers SDEAs (Safety Data Exchange Agreements), PVAs (Pharmacovigilance Agreements), and co-vigilance arrangements with licensees, CROs, CMOs, co-promotion partners, and local affiliates. Captures agreement type, counterparty, effective/expiry dates, reporting timelines (days to exchange), product scope, responsible party designations (PSUR authorship, signal management, regulatory submission), and compliance monitoring status. Required under GVP Module I and ICH E2E for all outsourced PV activities.' .

ind:PassStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pass Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Post-Authorization Safety Study record tracking PASS commitments and execution. Captures study protocol reference, study type (non-interventional, registry-based, database study, active surveillance), regulatory category (imposed as condition of MA, or voluntary), ENCePP/EU PAS Register number, study objectives, primary safety endpoints, study population, data sources, key milestones (protocol submission, interim reports, final report), and authority approval/assessment status. Tracks PASS commitments arising from RMPs, PSUR recommendations, Article 20/31 referrals, and marketing authorization conditions. Supports both EU (EMA) and US (FDA PMR/PMC) post-marketing study requirements.' .

ind:AccessStrategy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Access Strategy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining the market access strategy for a pharmaceutical product in a given geography or payer segment. Captures overarching access objectives, value proposition, target formulary tier, reimbursement pathway, HTA strategy, launch sequencing plan, identified access barriers with severity and remediation actions, key access milestones with planned and actual dates, and milestone status tracking. Serves as the strategic anchor for all downstream access activities including HTA submissions, payer contracting, patient support programs, and systematic access gap management.' .

ind:PayerAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Payer Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for payer organizations including commercial health plans, government payers (Medicare, Medicaid, NHS, statutory health insurers), pharmacy benefit managers (PBMs), and group purchasing organizations (GPOs). Captures payer type, tier, covered lives, formulary influence, contracting authority, and geographic coverage. SSOT for payer identity within the market access domain.' .

ind:MarketFormularyPosition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Market Formulary Position' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the formulary placement status of a pharmaceutical product within a specific payer formulary at a point in time. Records formulary tier, prior authorization requirements, step therapy requirements, quantity limits, preferred/non-preferred status, and effective dates. Enables gross-to-net revenue modeling and access gap analysis across payer segments.' .

ind:HtaSubmission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Hta Submission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the full lifecycle of Health Technology Assessment (HTA) submissions to bodies such as NICE (UK), HAS (France), G-BA (Germany), CADTH (Canada), and PBAC (Australia). Captures submission planning, dossier preparation, submission date, HTA body, therapeutic indication, comparator, clinical evidence package, economic model type, submission status, and the resulting formal decision including recommendation type (positive, negative, restricted, conditional), benefit rating, added therapeutic benefit classification, recommended price range, and reimbursement conditions. Owns both the submission event and the decision outcome as lifecycle stages of a single HTA engagement. Drives downstream payer contracting and pricing decisions.' .

ind:ValueDossier rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Value Dossier' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the global value dossier (GVD) or payer value dossier developed to support market access negotiations. Captures therapeutic area, target indication, clinical evidence summary, HEOR evidence, comparator landscape, budget impact model reference, and version history. Serves as the evidentiary foundation for HTA submissions and payer negotiations.' .

ind:MarketPayerContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Market Payer Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all managed care contracts, rebate agreements, and performance-based contracts negotiated with payers, PBMs (Express Scripts, CVS Caremark, OptumRx), GPOs, and other contracting entities. Captures contract type (base rebate, performance rebate, outcomes-based, value-based, PBM formulary rebate, GPO commitment), contracted product, rebate tiers, performance metrics, administrative fees, data sharing provisions, book-of-business structure, PBM-specific formulary management mechanics, contract term, and payment schedule. Central to gross-to-net revenue management and rebate accrual calculations. Covers all payer types including PBM-specific contract structures.' .

ind:RebateClaim rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Rebate Claim' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of rebate claims submitted to or received from payers and PBMs under managed care contracts. Captures claim period, contracted product, eligible units, applicable rebate rate, calculated rebate amount, dispute status, and payment date. Feeds gross-to-net revenue deduction accounting and rebate liability accruals in the finance domain.' .

ind:GrossToNetAdjustment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Gross To Net Adjustment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all gross-to-net revenue deduction components applied to a pharmaceutical product\'s gross sales to arrive at net revenue. Captures adjustment type (base rebate, performance rebate, Medicaid best price, 340B, chargebacks, copay assistance, GPO fees, distribution fees, patient assistance), period, product, channel, and adjustment amount. For copay assistance adjustments, captures individual claim-level detail including dispensing pharmacy, claim date, patient identifier (de-identified), drug product, gross copay amount, assistance amount paid, and remaining patient liability. Enables net revenue reconciliation, deduction category analysis, copay program spend reporting, and patient affordability program financial tracking. SSOT for all GTN deduction records including copay assistance transactions.' .

ind:CoverageDecision rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Coverage Decision' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records national, regional, or plan-level coverage decisions for a pharmaceutical product by a payer or government health authority. Captures coverage status, covered indication, coverage restrictions, prior authorization criteria, step therapy requirements, and effective date. Distinct from formulary position in that it represents the formal coverage policy determination rather than the formulary tier placement.' .

ind:PatientAccessProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Patient Access Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all patient support, early access, and pre-approval access programs designed to improve access to pharmaceutical products. Covers copay assistance programs, free drug programs, patient assistance programs (PAP), hub services, specialty pharmacy support, named patient programs, compassionate use, expanded access, early access programs (EAP), and managed access agreements. Captures program type, eligibility criteria, benefit cap, funding source, enrollment channel, regulatory authorization reference, supply terms, country, patient population, and program status. Bridges pre-approval access through commercial reimbursement and ongoing affordability support across the full product lifecycle.' .

ind:PricingDecision rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Pricing Decision' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for formal pricing decisions, approved price corridors, and international reference pricing (IRP) management for pharmaceutical products across markets and channels. Captures list price (WAC/ex-factory), government reference price, IRP constraints, price change type, effective date, approving authority, pricing rationale, and approved price corridors including floor price, target price, ceiling price, IRP basket countries, monitoring frequency, and corridor breach alert thresholds. Serves as the authoritative record of approved prices and price bands, enabling proactive management of cross-country price erosion risk and launch sequencing optimization.' .

ind:MarketHeorStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Market Heor Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for Health Economics and Outcomes Research (HEOR) evidence assets including studies, models, and real-world data (RWD) datasets used to support market access, payer negotiations, and HTA submissions. Captures study type (budget impact model, cost-effectiveness analysis, cost-utility analysis, retrospective RWD study, PRO study, indirect treatment comparison), therapeutic indication, target payer audience, study status, model version, patient population assumptions, comparator costs, time horizon, model outputs, publication reference, and budget impact model-specific attributes (market share assumptions, treatment cost inputs). Also manages the inventory of RWD/RWE datasets including data source type (claims database, EHR, registry, patient-reported outcomes), data vendor, data vintage, and data use agreements. SSOT for all HEOR evidence assets and RWD/RWE inventory within the market access domain.' .

ind:RweDataset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Rwe Dataset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for real-world data (RWD) and real-world evidence (RWE) datasets used in payer negotiations, HTA submissions, and HEOR analyses. Captures data source type (claims database, EHR, registry, patient-reported outcomes), data vendor, therapeutic area, patient population, data vintage, and data use agreements. SSOT for RWD/RWE asset inventory within the market access domain.' .

ind:PayerEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Payer Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of formal and informal engagements between the market access team and payer organizations. Captures engagement type (formulary committee meeting, medical policy review, rebate negotiation session, outcomes-based contract discussion, advisory board), payer account, attendees, discussion topics, commitments made, and follow-up actions. Supports payer relationship management and negotiation tracking.' .

ind:ReimbursementPolicy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Reimbursement Policy' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for reimbursement policies and coverage decisions issued by payers, government health authorities, and formulary committees for pharmaceutical products. Captures policy type, coverage status, covered indications, excluded populations, prior authorization criteria, step therapy requirements, quantity limits, coverage restrictions, decision authority, decision date, appeal status, policy effective dates, and individual coverage determination records. Records both the ongoing policy framework governing reimbursement and specific point-in-time coverage decisions at national, regional, or plan level. SSOT for all coverage and reimbursement policy data within the market access domain. Enables access gap analysis, policy change monitoring, coverage landscape tracking, and coverage decision audit trails.' .

ind:TenderSubmission rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Tender Submission' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records pharmaceutical tender submissions made to government procurement authorities, hospital groups, and national health systems in tender-driven markets (e.g., EU, LATAM, APAC). Captures tender authority, product, submitted price, volume commitment, tender award status, contract duration, and tender reference number. Supports tender strategy management and awarded tender tracking.' .

ind:OutcomesBasedContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Outcomes Based Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for outcomes-based, value-based, or risk-sharing agreements negotiated with payers where rebates or payments are contingent on demonstrated real-world clinical or economic outcomes. Captures outcome metric definition, measurement methodology, data source, performance thresholds, rebate adjustment schedule, measurement period, and reconciliation process. Also records transactional outcome measurements including observed outcome rates per measurement period, patient cohort sizes, variance from thresholds, and resulting rebate adjustment triggers. Supports the growing portfolio of innovative contracting arrangements with full measurement-to-reconciliation traceability.' .

ind:GeneralLedger rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'General Ledger' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Central repository for all financial accounting entries across the enterprise, representing the authoritative chart of accounts, account balances, and period-end ledger positions. Captures account master data (account number, account type, account group, currency), period balances (opening, debit totals, credit totals, closing balance by period), company code, profit center allocations, cost center references, and currency translations as sourced from SAP FI module. Serves as SSOT for trial balance, balance sheet, income statement, and SOX-compliant period-end close processes across all legal entities in the pharmaceutical group. Supports consolidation eliminations, multi-GAAP reporting (US GAAP and IFRS), and financial close status tracking. Does NOT own individual postings (owned by journal_entry) — owns aggregate balances and account structure.' .

ind:JournalEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Journal Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual accounting transactions posted to the general ledger with full header and line-item detail, including tax-specific postings. Header captures posting date, document type, reference number, fiscal year/period, currency, and posting user. Line items capture GL account, cost center, profit center, debit/credit amounts in transaction and local currency, tax code, tax jurisdiction, taxable base amount, tax amount, withholding tax, assignment field, and line item text. Encompasses all subledger postings (AP, AR, asset, tax) and manual adjustments. Tax postings carry additional attributes: tax jurisdiction, tax return reference, VAT/sales tax/deferred tax classification, and indirect tax reporting period for multi-jurisdiction compliance. Supports audit trails required under SOX and 21 CFR Part 11, financial close processes, and granular P&L analysis by therapeutic area, brand, and geography.' .

ind:InternalOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Internal Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'SAP CO internal order used to collect, monitor, and settle costs for specific projects, R&D programs, clinical trials, or capital expenditure initiatives. Captures order type (R&D, capex, overhead), settlement rule, budget profile, actual costs, commitment values, responsible cost center, project/WBS reference, and order lifecycle status. References milestone_payment records for contractual obligations but does NOT own milestone payment terms or trigger events. Supports R&D capitalization tracking, ROI analysis for drug development programs, and CAPEX lifecycle governance.' .

ind:AccountsPayable rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Accounts Payable' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Vendor invoice, payment obligation, and payment execution records managed within SAP FI-AP module. Captures vendor invoice details (invoice number, date, due date, payment terms, gross amount, tax amount, withholding tax, payment block status), payment execution (payment document, payment date, payment method including ACH/wire/check, bank account, clearing document, payment run ID), and settlement status. Covers payables to CROs, CMOs, CDMOs, raw material suppliers, licensors (royalty and milestone payments), and service providers in the pharmaceutical supply chain.' .

ind:AccountsReceivable rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Accounts Receivable' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Customer invoice, collection, payment receipt, and revenue accrual records managed within SAP FI-AR module. Captures customer invoices (billing date, due date, payment terms, gross amount, tax, dunning level), incoming payments (receipt date, payment method, clearing document, bank account), and period-end revenue accruals (accrual type, product, customer segment, territory, accrual basis, recognized vs deferred revenue, recognition date, reversal date). Covers receivables from wholesalers, distributors, hospital networks, and government payers. Supports ASC 606 / IFRS 15 revenue recognition compliance for pharmaceutical product sales.' .

ind:Budget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Budget' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Annual and multi-year financial budget plans with granular line-item detail by cost center, profit center, GL account, cost element, and internal order. Captures budget version (original, revised, forecast), fiscal year, budget type (opex, capex, R&D), line-item breakdowns with planned amounts by period, currency, budget category, approval workflow status, and variance tracking. Supports P&L planning by therapeutic area, R&D program investment planning, clinical trial budget management, and detailed variance analysis between planned and actual spend for drug development, manufacturing, and commercial operations.' .

ind:FixedAsset rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Fixed Asset' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Enterprise fixed asset register with complete lifecycle transaction history managed in SAP FI-AA module, covering manufacturing equipment, laboratory instruments, IT infrastructure, and leasehold improvements. Captures asset master data (asset class, acquisition date, acquisition cost, accumulated depreciation, net book value, depreciation key, useful life, location, cost center assignment) and all lifecycle transactions (acquisitions, retirements, transfers, write-ups, impairments, and periodic depreciation postings with transaction type, posting date, amount, document reference, asset value date, and depreciation area). Supports CAPEX tracking, R&D equipment capitalization, and compliance with IAS 16 / US GAAP ASC 360.' .

ind:RdCapitalization rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Rd Capitalization' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the capitalization of R&D expenditures in accordance with IAS 38 and ASC 730, capturing the transition from expensed research costs to capitalized development costs upon meeting regulatory and technical feasibility criteria. Records drug program, milestone trigger (e.g., Phase III initiation, NDA filing), capitalized amount, amortization start date, useful life, and impairment assessments.' .

ind:CogsEntry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Cogs Entry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Cost of Goods Sold records by drug product, SKU, and manufacturing batch, capturing standard cost, actual cost, cost variance, material cost, labor cost, overhead absorption, and period. Sourced from SAP CO-PC (Product Costing) and PP modules. Enables COGS analysis by product, brand, therapeutic area, and geography to support gross margin reporting and pricing decisions.' .

ind:RoyaltyAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Royalty Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record and periodic accrual lifecycle for royalty and licensing agreements with external partners, universities, and IP licensors. Captures agreement terms (licensor/licensee, licensed compound, royalty rate structure including tiered rates, territory, effective dates, minimum payments, sublicensing rights, audit rights) and periodic accrual calculations (calculation period, net sales base, applicable rate tier, accrued royalty amount, currency, payment due date, settlement status). Serves as SSOT for royalty accounting obligations, IP cost tracking for in-licensed compounds, and royalty payment reconciliation across the pharmaceutical portfolio.' .

ind:IntercompanyTransaction rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Intercompany Transaction' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of financial transactions between legal entities within the pharmaceutical group, including intercompany loans, transfer pricing charges, management fee allocations, and intercompany product sales. Captures sending entity, receiving entity, transaction type, amount, currency, transfer price basis, and elimination status for consolidated financial reporting.' .

ind:TaxPosting rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Tax Posting' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tax-related financial postings including VAT, sales tax, withholding tax, and deferred tax entries managed in SAP FI-TX. Captures tax code, tax jurisdiction, taxable base amount, tax amount, tax account, reporting period, and tax return reference. Supports indirect tax compliance across multiple jurisdictions where pharmaceutical products are sold or manufactured.' .

ind:MilestonePayment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Milestone Payment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks contractual milestone-based payment obligations and receipts triggered by development, regulatory, or commercial events in pharmaceutical partnerships. Captures milestone type (e.g., IND filing, Phase II completion, NDA approval, first commercial sale, sales thresholds), triggering event date, contractual payment amount, currency, counterparty, associated internal order, payment status, and accounting treatment. Distinct from internal_order (which collects all costs for a program) — milestone_payment owns the individual contractual obligation record and its trigger-based lifecycle. Critical for R&D partnership financial management and contingent liability disclosure.' .

ind:TransferPrice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Finance ;
    rdfs:label 'Transfer Price' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transfer pricing master records governing the prices at which pharmaceutical products, APIs, and services are transacted between related legal entities across jurisdictions. Captures product or service, sending entity, receiving entity, transfer price method (CUP, cost-plus, TNMM), approved price, currency, effective date, and regulatory documentation reference. Supports OECD transfer pricing compliance and tax authority documentation.' .

ind:DemandPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Demand Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Statistical and consensus-based demand forecast for pharmaceutical SKUs across commercial and clinical supply chains. Captures baseline forecast, adjusted forecast, consensus-approved quantities, planning horizon, and demand signals from Kinaxis RapidResponse/Blue Yonder. Tracks forecast version, approval status, planning cycle, and demand classification (commercial, clinical, compassionate use). Serves as the authoritative demand signal for supply planning and inventory positioning.' .

ind:Plan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Constrained and unconstrained supply plan for drug substance (DS), drug product (DP), and finished dosage form (FDF) across manufacturing sites and CMOs/CDMOs. Captures planned production quantities, planned receipt dates, supply source, planning horizon, capacity constraints, and plan version. Integrates with Kinaxis RapidResponse/Blue Yonder and SAP PP. Tracks plan status (draft, approved, frozen) and supply type (make, buy, transfer).' .

ind:InventoryLot rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Inventory Lot' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Lot/batch-level inventory record for raw materials (APIs, excipients), packaging components, drug substance, drug product, and finished goods held at manufacturing sites, distribution centers, and 3PL locations. Captures lot number, NDC, SKU, material number, quantity on hand, quantity reserved, quantity available, storage location, storage condition (ambient, refrigerated, frozen), expiry date, retest date, lot status (unrestricted, quality hold, quarantine, rejected, released), and GDP compliance flags. SSOT for lot-level inventory traceability.' .

ind:WarehouseReceipt rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Warehouse Receipt' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of physical receipt of materials at a pharmaceutical manufacturing site, warehouse, or distribution center against a purchase order or inbound delivery. Captures GR document number, posting date, material, lot number, received quantity, storage location, vendor, CoA reference, GDP compliance check status, temperature excursion flag, and quarantine status. Aligns with SAP MM goods receipt (MIGO). Triggers quality inspection and lot creation in LIMS.' .

ind:GoodsIssue rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Goods Issue' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Record of material consumption or outbound movement from inventory including issuance to production orders, clinical trial supply kits, sample distribution, destruction, quality testing, or customer delivery. Captures GI document number, posting date, material, lot number, issued quantity, movement type (production consumption, sales delivery, sample, scrap, transfer posting), cost center or order reference, and issuing storage location. Aligns with SAP MM goods issue (MIGO). Reduces inventory on hand and triggers cost accounting entries. Supports GMP batch record material consumption documentation.' .

ind:StockTransferOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Stock Transfer Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Inter-site or inter-plant stock transfer order for pharmaceutical materials between manufacturing sites, distribution centers, and 3PL locations. Captures transfer order number, sending plant/storage location, receiving plant/storage location, material, lot number, transfer quantity, transfer type (one-step, two-step), GDP compliance requirements, cold-chain requirements, and transfer status. Aligns with SAP MM/WM stock transfer order management.' .

ind:Shipment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Shipment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Physical movement record and SSOT for all pharmaceutical goods movements including outbound customer deliveries, inter-site stock transfers (one-step and two-step), 3PL movements, and returns. Captures shipment number, origin and destination (plant, DC, 3PL, distributor, wholesaler, hospital, pharmacy, clinical trial site), carrier, mode of transport, transfer type, NDC, lot numbers, shipped quantity, shipment date, estimated/actual delivery date, incoterms, cold-chain requirements (temperature range, monitoring device ID), GDP compliance status, customs/import documentation, and stock transfer processing status. Subsumes stock transfer order functionality — inter-site transfers are modeled as shipments with transfer_type indicating one-step or two-step processing. Aligns with SAP SD shipment management and SAP MM stock transfer processing.' .

ind:DeliveryOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Delivery Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Outbound delivery document representing the fulfillment instruction for pharmaceutical finished goods against commercial orders or stock transfer requests. Captures delivery number, delivery type (outbound, returns, stock transfer), ship-to party, delivery date, material, lot number, delivery quantity, picking status, packing status, goods issue status, carrier assignment, and FEFO (First Expiry First Out) compliance flag. Aligns with SAP SD outbound delivery (VL01N). Represents the warehouse execution instruction — distinct from shipment which tracks the physical movement after goods issue.' .

ind:DistributionNetwork rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Distribution Network' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining the pharmaceutical distribution network topology including manufacturing sites, distribution centers, 3PL nodes, wholesalers, direct-to-pharmacy lanes, and warehouse storage zones with bin/rack/zone configuration. Captures node type, node name, geographic region, GDP authorization status, cold-chain capability (temperature zones: ambient, CRT, 2-8°C, -20°C, -80°C), controlled substance handling authorization, storage capacity, physical warehouse layout, lead times, and network lane definitions. Used for supply network planning in Kinaxis RapidResponse/Blue Yonder and SAP APO/IBP.' .

ind:ClinicalSupplyOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Clinical Supply Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Supply order for investigational medicinal products (IMPs), comparators, and ancillary supplies destined for clinical trial sites. Captures IMP material code, protocol number, study site, randomization kit number, ordered quantity, blinding requirements, expiry date, cold-chain requirements, import/export permit references, and order status. Distinct from commercial sales orders due to IND/CTA regulatory requirements, blinding, and randomization constraints.' .

ind:ProductRecall rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Product Recall' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Pharmaceutical product recall event record initiated by regulatory authority mandate or voluntary company action. Captures recall number, recall class (Class I, II, III per FDA), affected NDC, affected lot numbers, recall scope (market, distribution level), recall reason, regulatory agency notification date, press release date, customer notification status, quantity recovered, and recall closure date. Supports lot traceability and regulatory reporting obligations under 21 CFR Part 7.' .

ind:SerializationRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Serialization Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unit-level and case-level serialization record for pharmaceutical finished goods compliant with DSCSA (Drug Supply Chain Security Act) and EU FMD (Falsified Medicines Directive) requirements. Captures serial number, GTIN, NDC, lot number, expiry date, aggregation hierarchy (unit→case→pallet), commissioning event, decommissioning event, verification status, and trading partner transaction history. Enables end-to-end track-and-trace across the pharmaceutical supply chain.' .

ind:ServiceAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Commercial supply agreement with CMOs, CDMOs, and 3PLs governing contracted manufacturing or logistics services for pharmaceutical products. Captures agreement number, counterparty, agreement type (manufacturing, packaging, distribution, storage), contracted volumes, minimum order quantities, lead times, quality agreement reference, GDP compliance obligations, force majeure clauses, and agreement status. Distinct from procurement purchase orders — represents the strategic framework governing the supply relationship.' .

ind:LotTraceability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Lot Traceability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'End-to-end lot/batch traceability record linking raw material lots through drug substance, drug product, and finished goods lots across the pharmaceutical supply chain. Captures parent lot, child lot, material, transformation type (manufacturing, packaging, repackaging), site, transformation date, quantity in, quantity out, yield, and traceability chain status. Supports regulatory recall traceability, pharmacovigilance investigations, and GMP batch record linkage. Critical for 21 CFR Part 211 and EU GMP Annex 11 compliance.' .

ind:FulfillmentEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Fulfillment Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified event log capturing all supply chain milestones, exceptions, and deviations across the pharmaceutical distribution network. Includes shipment milestones (departed, in-transit, arrived, delivered), temperature and environmental excursions during cold-chain storage/transit (biologics, vaccines, APIs), GDP deviations (documentation gaps, unauthorized access, pest control), supply disruptions, allocation changes, and ATP exceptions. Captures event type, event timestamp, affected material, lot, shipment or storage location reference, temperature/humidity readings, monitoring device ID, excursion severity (minor, major, critical), GDP guideline reference, CAPA reference, regulatory reportability flag, event source system, and resolution status. Supports GDP compliance per EU GDP Guidelines 2013/C 343/01, WHO GDP guidelines, and cold-chain integrity assurance. SSOT for all supply chain event and exception tracking.' .

ind:Brand rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Brand' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for each pharmaceutical brand managed by the commercial organization. Captures brand identity, therapeutic area, lifecycle stage (pre-launch, launch, growth, mature, LOE), brand strategy, target patient population, approved indications, ATC classification, INN/USAN, and P&L ownership. Serves as the commercial anchor entity linking all brand-level activities, performance tracking, promotional spend, and market share measurement.' .

ind:Territory rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Territory' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines the geographic and organizational sales territories used to structure the field force. Captures territory code, name, geographic boundaries (zip codes, counties, states, regions), territory type (primary, secondary, specialty), alignment version, effective dates, and assigned district and region hierarchy. Used for call planning, target assignment, and performance attribution in Veeva CRM and Salesforce Health Cloud.' .

ind:SalesRep rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Sales Rep' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Commercial field force representative master record. Captures rep identity, employee ID, role (territory manager, specialty rep, MSL, KAM), assigned territory, district, region, business unit, hire date, certification status, Veeva CRM user ID, and current employment status. This is the commercial-specific view of the field force with CRM linkage, territory assignment, and credentialing — distinct from the workforce domain employee record which owns HR lifecycle data.' .

ind:HcpTarget rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Hcp Target' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Commercial targeting and call planning record linking an HCP (owned by the hcp domain) to a brand, territory, and sales rep for a given targeting/planning cycle. Captures target tier (A/B/C), planned call frequency, call type mix (face-to-face vs. remote), specialty segment, prescribing potential decile, targeting rationale, priority rank, effective period, plan approval status, and targeting status. Drives field force activity scheduling, call planning, and promotional resource allocation in Veeva CRM. Distinct from the HCP master (owned by hcp domain) — this is the commercial segmentation and planning layer.' .

ind:CallActivity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Call Activity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of each field force interaction (detail call) with an HCP or HCO, sourced from Veeva CRM. Captures call date, call type (face-to-face, remote, phone), HCP/HCO visited, products detailed, samples dropped, promotional materials presented, call outcome, next best action, signature captured flag, off-label discussion flag, and PhRMA code compliance status. Core to field force effectiveness measurement and Sunshine Act reporting.' .

ind:SampleManagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Sample Management' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified sample management product tracking sample inventory positions, all transaction movements (disbursements, receipts, transfers, adjustments, reconciliations), and PDMA compliance for each sales representative' .

ind:PromoMaterial rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Promo Material' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog, content lifecycle, and MLR approval workflow for all promotional materials managed in Veeva PromoMats. Captures material ID, title, material type (detail aid, leave-behind, patient brochure, digital asset, journal ad, video), brand, indication, distribution channel, and current approval status. Includes full Medical-Legal-Regulatory (MLR) review workflow tracking: submission date, review cycle number, reviewer assignments (medical, legal, regulatory), individual reviewer decisions, review comments, aggregate approval decision, approval date, expiry date, resubmission history, and version lineage. Ensures compliance with FDA promotional regulations (21 CFR Part 202) and internal PhRMA code. Only MLR-approved materials with valid expiry dates may be used in field force detailing.' .

ind:MlrReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Mlr Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the Medical-Legal-Regulatory (MLR) review and approval workflow for promotional materials and communications. Captures submission date, review cycle number, reviewer roles (medical, legal, regulatory), review status, comments, approval decision, approval date, expiry date, and resubmission history. Ensures compliance with FDA promotional regulations (21 CFR Part 202) and internal PhRMA code adherence.' .

ind:CommercialSpeakerProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Commercial Speaker Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record and full participation ledger for HCP speaker programs. Program header captures program type (dinner meeting, webinar, symposium, peer-to-peer), venue, date, budget, actual spend, compliance status, and PhRMA code adherence. Participation detail captures each HCP\'s engagement as speaker or attendee, including HCP ID, participation role, honorarium amount, travel reimbursement, meal value, attendance confirmation, fair market value assessment, and Sunshine Act reportable transfer of value flag. Feeds directly into Open Payments aggregate spend reporting and supports Sunshine Act compliance, speaker bureau management, speaker training tracking, and fair market value documentation.' .

ind:SpeakerEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Speaker Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of an individual HCP\'s participation in a speaker program, either as a speaker or attendee. Captures HCP ID, program ID, participation role (speaker, attendee), honorarium amount paid, travel and expense reimbursement, meal value, attendance confirmation, and Sunshine Act reportable transfer of value flag. Feeds directly into Open Payments aggregate spend reporting.' .

ind:SunshineDisclosure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Sunshine Disclosure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Aggregated annual disclosure record of transfers of value from the pharmaceutical company to HCPs and teaching hospitals, as required by the Physician Payments Sunshine Act (42 CFR Part 403). Captures reporting year, HCP/HCO NPI, payment category (consulting fees, honoraria, food and beverage, travel, education, research), amount, product associated, submission status, and CMS Open Payments submission ID.' .

ind:BrandPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Brand Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Annual or multi-year commercial brand plan serving as the unified planning, budgeting, and execution tracking entity for a brand\'s commercial strategy. Captures strategic objectives, positioning, competitive differentiation, promotional mix, channel strategy, and KPI targets. Includes detailed promotional spend tracking by tactic (personal promotion, non-personal, digital, samples, speaker programs, congress) with planned budget, actual spend, variance, cost center, and brand P&L line attribution. Also tracks launch activity milestones for new product/indication launches including activity name, launch phase (pre-launch, launch, post-launch), activity type (field force training, formulary pull-through, KOL engagement, patient support activation), planned/actual dates, owner, status, and dependencies on regulatory approval milestones. Serves as the single commercial planning, financial execution, launch management, and brand P&L entity.' .

ind:KolEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Kol Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks engagement activities with Key Opinion Leaders (KOLs) by the commercial and medical affairs teams. Captures KOL HCP ID, engagement type (advisory board, speaker training, publication review, congress presentation, consulting), engagement date, brand, therapeutic area, honorarium, compliance approval status, and strategic relationship tier. Distinct from speaker_engagement which is program-specific — this is the longitudinal KOL relationship management record.' .

ind:PatientSupportProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Patient Support Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record and enrollment ledger for patient support programs (PSPs). Program header captures program name, brand, program type (co-pay assistance, free drug, nurse navigator, adherence program, hub services), eligibility criteria, administering vendor, program KPIs, and vendor performance metrics. Enrollment detail captures individual patient enrollments including enrollment date, prescribing HCP, enrollment channel, eligibility verification status, benefit type granted (co-pay card, free drug voucher, nurse call), enrollment status, program exit reason, and adherence milestones. Supports access and adherence analytics, program ROI measurement, patient journey optimization, hub services vendor performance tracking, and HIPAA-compliant de-identified reporting.' .

ind:PspEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Psp Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of a patient\'s enrollment in a patient support program. Captures enrollment date, program ID, patient reference (anonymized or de-identified per HIPAA), prescribing HCP, enrollment channel, eligibility verification status, benefit type granted (co-pay card, free drug voucher, nurse call), enrollment status, and program exit reason. Supports access and adherence analytics and program ROI measurement.' .

ind:ContractAccount rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Account' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Commercial contract account master for institutional customers including hospital systems, IDNs (Integrated Delivery Networks), GPOs (Group Purchasing Organizations), specialty pharmacies, and retail pharmacy chains. Captures account name, account type, GPO affiliation, contract tier, account manager assignment, strategic classification, and key contact information. Supports institutional selling, account-based marketing, and field force account coverage planning. Distinct from hcp domain (individual practitioners) and market domain (payer contracts).' .

ind:SalesPerformance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Sales Performance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic (weekly/monthly/quarterly) sales performance record at the territory and rep level by brand. Captures period, territory ID, rep ID, brand, total prescriptions (TRx), new prescriptions (NRx), market share, call frequency achieved vs. target, sample drop rate, and attainment vs. quota. Sourced from CRM and Rx data integration. Supports incentive compensation calculation and field force management.' .

ind:IncentiveCompensation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Incentive Compensation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Incentive compensation calculation record for each sales representative per performance period. Captures rep ID, performance period, quota, attainment percentage, bonus tier achieved, calculated bonus amount, payout status, adjustment reason, and approval status. Supports field force motivation, HR payroll integration, and commercial operations governance.' .

ind:CopayProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Copay Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record and transactional redemption ledger for co-pay assistance and patient affordability programs. Program header captures program name, brand, program type (co-pay card, voucher, free trial), maximum annual benefit, eligibility rules, administering hub vendor, program status, and 340B exclusion rules. Redemption detail captures each individual co-pay card or voucher redemption including redemption date, pharmacy NPI, product NDC, patient out-of-pocket amount, manufacturer contribution, payer adjudication status, claim reference, and gross-to-net impact. Supports patient access strategy, program utilization analytics, brand P&L gross-to-net deduction reporting, and 340B program exclusion tracking.' .

ind:CopayRedemption rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Copay Redemption' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of each co-pay card or voucher redemption by a patient at a pharmacy. Captures redemption date, program ID, product NDC, pharmacy NPI, patient out-of-pocket amount, manufacturer contribution amount, payer adjudication status, and gross-to-net impact. Feeds into brand P&L gross-to-net deduction reporting and program utilization tracking.' .

ind:MedicinalProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Medicinal Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master entity representing an authorized or investigational medicinal product (branded drug, generic, biosimilar, vaccine, or consumer health product). Captures INN/USAN, brand name, ATC classification code, mechanism of action (MOA), therapeutic area, product type (NCE, NBE, biosimilar, vaccine, OTC), development stage, lifecycle status, and for biosimilar products: reference biologic product linkage (reference_product_id, originator BLA/MAA number, interchangeability designation, extrapolation status, analytical similarity assessment outcome). Aligned with ISO IDMP Medicinal Product concept. Serves as the top-level node in the pharmaceutical product hierarchy (medicinal product → drug product → SKU) referenced by manufacturing, commercial, regulatory, and supply chain domains.' .

ind:DrugSubstance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Drug Substance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the active pharmaceutical ingredient (API) or drug substance (DS) as defined in ICH Q7. Captures chemical name, molecular formula, molecular weight, CAS registry number, INN/USAN designation, pharmacopoeial monograph reference (USP/EP/JP), physical form, stereochemistry, polymorphic form, salt form, particle size specification, ADME profile summary, BCS classification, and regulatory Drug Master File (DMF) reference number. Represents the DS layer in the DS/DP hierarchy and is the single source of truth for API chemical identity referenced by manufacturing, quality, regulatory, and formulation records.' .

ind:DrugProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Drug Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the finished drug product (DP) or finished dosage form (FDF) derived from one or more drug substances. Captures dosage form (tablet, capsule, injection, etc.), route of administration, strength, formulation type, reference listed drug (RLD) linkage, shelf life, storage conditions, and CMC summary. Bridges the DS/DP hierarchy and is referenced by manufacturing batch records, regulatory submissions, and commercial SKUs.' .

ind:Formulation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Formulation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Detailed formulation record specifying the qualitative and quantitative composition (Q1/Q2) of a drug product, including all active and inactive ingredients, their pharmacopoeial grades, functional roles, and quantities per unit dose and per batch. Tracks formulation version history, Quality by Design (QbD) design space parameters, critical process parameters (CPP), and critical quality attributes (CQA). Supports CMC Module 3 documentation, scale-up, and technology transfer.' .

ind:FormulationIngredient rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Formulation Ingredient' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Line-level record within a formulation capturing each individual ingredient (API or excipient), its INN or INCI name, pharmacopoeial grade, function (binder, filler, preservative, etc.), quantity per unit dose, quantity per batch, and overages. Enables full bill-of-materials traceability for regulatory submissions and manufacturing execution.' .

ind:PackagingConfiguration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Packaging Configuration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the packaging configuration of a drug product, defining primary container (vial, blister, bottle), secondary packaging (carton, wallet), and tertiary/shipper packaging. Captures container closure system (CCS) specifications, pack size, fill volume, headspace, cold-chain requirements (2-8°C, -20°C, -80°C), and serialization/aggregation hierarchy for track-and-trace compliance (DSCSA, EU FMD). Referenced by supply chain, manufacturing, and commercial domains for SKU definition.' .

ind:Sku rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Sku' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stock Keeping Unit (SKU) master record representing the commercially sellable unit of a drug product at a specific strength, dosage form, and packaging configuration. Captures GTIN/EAN barcode, SAP material number, trade name, market (country/region), launch date, discontinuation date, commercial status (active, discontinued, withdrawn), and channel designation (retail, hospital, specialty pharmacy). Serves as the SSOT for commercial product identity referenced by supply chain, commercial, and finance domains. NDC codes for US-market SKUs are managed via regulatory_identifier.' .

ind:ProductNdcCode rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Product Ndc Code' ;
    rdfs:comment 'National Drug Code (NDC) registry record for each FDA-listed drug product. Captures the 10-digit NDC number (labeler, product, package segments), FDA listing status, listing date, application number linkage (NDA/ANDA/BLA), proprietary name, non-proprietary name, and DEA schedule. Serves as the authoritative NDC-to-product mapping for regulatory compliance, dispensing, and reimbursement.' .

ind:Lifecycle rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Lifecycle' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tracks the lifecycle stage and status transitions of a medicinal product from discovery through post-market, including pipeline stage (discovery, preclinical, Phase I/II/III, NDA/BLA submission, approved, launched, LOE, discontinued). Captures stage entry date, exit date, milestone events, responsible team, and lifecycle gate criteria. Provides the authoritative product lifecycle timeline referenced by portfolio planning and regulatory domains.' .

ind:RegulatoryIdentifier rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Identifier' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified catalog of regulatory product identifiers and listing codes assigned by health authorities across all jurisdictions. Captures NDA, ANDA, BLA, MAA, JNDA, EMA product numbers, PMDA approval numbers, NMPA registration numbers, and National Drug Codes (NDC — 10-digit labeler-product-package segments with FDA listing status, listing date, application number linkage, proprietary/non-proprietary names, and DEA schedule). Records identifier type, issuing authority, application number, approval date, approval status, jurisdiction, and listing metadata. Serves as the single source of truth for cross-jurisdiction regulatory identity, product listing, and dispensing/reimbursement code mapping for each drug product.' .

ind:Indication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Indication' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Association record linking a medicinal product to its approved or investigational therapeutic indications, capturing indication name, MedDRA preferred term, ICD-10 code, approval status by jurisdiction, approval date, patient population (adult, pediatric, geriatric), line of therapy, and label claim text. Tracks both approved and pipeline indications to support regulatory, medical affairs, and commercial strategies.' .

ind:Labeling rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Labeling' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the approved product label (prescribing information / SmPC / package insert) for each drug product by jurisdiction. Captures label version, effective date, label type (USPI, SmPC, PIL), regulatory approval reference, black box warning flag, REMS requirement flag, controlled substance schedule, and key label sections (indications, dosing, contraindications, warnings). Supports pharmacovigilance, medical affairs, and regulatory compliance.' .

ind:ProductChangeControl rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Product Change Control' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing post-approval changes and variations to drug product registrations, including Type IA/IB/II variations (EMA), Prior Approval Supplements (PAS), Changes Being Effected (CBE-30/CBE-0), Annual Reports (FDA), and PMDA partial change applications. Captures change description, change category (CMC, labeling, safety, manufacturing site), affected markets, submission numbers, implementation date, health authority notification/approval status, and impact assessment on product quality, safety, and efficacy. Bridges regulatory affairs and quality change management workflows.' .

ind:CombinationProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Combination Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for combination products that combine a drug with a device, biologic, or another drug (e.g., auto-injectors, prefilled syringes, inhalers, transdermal patches, drug-eluting stents). Captures combination type (drug-device, drug-biologic, drug-drug-device), constituent parts with their respective regulatory classifications, primary mode of action (PMOA), lead center designation (CDER/CDRH/CBER), combination product agreement number, device constituent specifications (design history file reference, human factors study status), and cross-labeling requirements. Supports 21 CFR Part 4 compliance, regulatory strategy, and CMC documentation.' .

ind:Master rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Master' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for individual healthcare professionals (HCPs) including physicians, pharmacists, nurses, and other licensed practitioners. Captures HCP identity (name, date of birth, gender), NPI number, professional credentials, all state medical licenses (license number, issuing authority, jurisdiction, issue/expiration dates, status, renewal history), DEA controlled substance registrations, board certifications, specialty classifications (primary/secondary, ATC/therapeutic area alignment), professional designations, practice addresses, and contact information. Authoritative single source of truth (SSOT) for HCP identity, credentials, licensing, and practice locations used across commercial, medical affairs, and clinical operations. Sourced from Veeva CRM, Salesforce Health Cloud, and third-party data providers (IQVIA OneKey, NPI Registry).' .

ind:HcoMaster rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Hco Master' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for healthcare organizations (HCOs) including hospitals, clinics, pharmacies, integrated delivery networks (IDNs), group purchasing organizations (GPOs), and academic medical centers. Captures organization name, type, accreditation status, NPI, DEA registration, bed count, magnet status, teaching hospital designation, and geographic footprint. SSOT for institutional identity used in commercial targeting and medical affairs.' .

ind:License rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'License' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Professional licenses and credentials held by each HCP, including state medical licenses, DEA controlled substance registrations, board certifications, and specialty credentials. Tracks license number, issuing authority, state/jurisdiction, issue date, expiration date, license status (active, suspended, revoked), and renewal history. Critical for compliance validation before any promotional or medical engagement.' .

ind:Affiliation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Affiliation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Relationship records linking HCPs to healthcare organizations (HCOs) and to other HCPs, capturing employment, admitting privileges, group practice membership, and referral relationships. Tracks affiliation type (employee, contractor, admitting, consulting), role, start and end dates, primary affiliation flag, and affiliation strength. Essential for account-based selling, network mapping, and understanding prescribing influence hierarchies.' .

ind:HcpKolProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Hcp Kol Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Key Opinion Leader (KOL) profile extending the base HCP record with scientific influence metrics, publication history, clinical trial investigator status, advisory board participation, congress speaking history, and KOL tier classification (national, regional, local). Tracks h-index, citation count, therapeutic area expertise, and KOL engagement strategy. Used by medical affairs for publication planning, advisory boards, and MSL targeting.' .

ind:HcpEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Hcp Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of all interactions between field personnel (sales representatives, MSLs, medical affairs) and HCPs or HCOs. Captures engagement type (detail visit, lunch-and-learn, congress meeting, advisory board, medical information request), channel (face-to-face, virtual, phone), date, duration, products discussed, materials shared, and outcome. Primary transactional record for HCP engagement history. Sourced from Veeva CRM.' .

ind:SampleRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Sample Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Drug sample requests and fulfillment records for HCPs under the Prescription Drug Marketing Act (PDMA) and FDA sample accountability requirements. Captures sample product, lot number, quantity requested, quantity dispensed, HCP signature, DEA number validation, sample drop date, and representative ID. Tracks sample inventory reconciliation and compliance with 21 CFR Part 203. Sourced from Veeva CRM sample management module.' .

ind:ConsentRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Consent Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified consent, opt-in/opt-out, do-not-contact (DNC), and no-see records governing all permissible and restricted communication with HCPs. Single source of truth for contact permissions and restrictions across all channels. Captures consent grants (promotional, medical, digital, email, phone), consent withdrawals, DNC requests, no-see restrictions, compliance-driven contact restrictions, legal holds, and channel-specific limitations. Tracks consent date, withdrawal date, restriction type, restriction reason, regulatory basis (GDPR, HIPAA, CCPA, state law), expiration, and enforcement status. Enforced across all field engagement systems including Veeva CRM, email platforms, and digital channels. Replaces any separate DNC or no-see lists as the single authoritative source.' .

ind:SunshineTransfer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Sunshine Transfer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Open Payments (Sunshine Act) reportable transfers of value from the pharmaceutical company to HCPs and HCOs, as required under 42 CFR Part 403. Captures payment type (consulting fee, speaker honorarium, meal, travel, research grant, royalty), amount, currency, date, product association, nature of payment, and CMS reporting status. Supports annual CMS Open Payments submission and anti-kickback compliance monitoring.' .

ind:PrescribingPattern rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Prescribing Pattern' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Aggregated prescribing behavior data for HCPs by product, therapeutic area, and time period, sourced from third-party prescription data providers (IQVIA, Symphony Health). Captures total prescriptions (TRx), new prescriptions (NRx), market share, brand vs. generic split, competitive prescribing, and prescribing trend. Used for HCP targeting, segmentation, and commercial performance management. Not patient-level data — aggregated at HCP level.' .

ind:HcpSpeakerProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Hcp Speaker Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Speaker bureau management and individual speaker program event records covering the full speaker lifecycle. Manages HCP enrollment in speaker bureau (speaker tier, therapeutic area, approved products, training completion, certification status, contract terms, honorarium rate, compliance certification), and individual program events (date, venue, format, audience size, spend, compliance approval, materials used). Tracks speaker training completion, programs delivered, speaker performance metrics, and generates Sunshine Act reportable transfers of value. Supports anti-kickback compliance monitoring for speaker fees and honoraria. Single source of truth for all speaker-related data. Managed in Veeva CRM.' .

ind:HcpAdvisoryBoard rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Hcp Advisory Board' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Advisory board and scientific advisory committee records capturing HCP participation in company-sponsored advisory activities. Captures board name, therapeutic area, meeting date, meeting format, HCP role (chair, member, consultant), honorarium paid, topics discussed, and medical affairs owner. Supports KOL engagement strategy, publication planning, and Sunshine Act reporting for consulting fees.' .

ind:MedInfoRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Med Info Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Medical information requests submitted by HCPs to the medical affairs or medical information team. Captures request channel (phone, email, congress, field), product or compound referenced, question category (clinical, safety, dosing, off-label), response provided, response date, HCP specialty, and escalation status. Supports pharmacovigilance signal detection (AE follow-up) and medical affairs reporting. Sourced from Veeva Vault MedComms.' .

ind:Contract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Contracts, agreements, and associated fair market value (FMV) rate cards between the pharmaceutical company and HCPs for services including consulting, advisory boards, speaker programs, clinical research, and medical education. Captures contract type, effective dates, scope of services, FMV rate ranges by specialty/service/region, FMV methodology, hourly rate min/max, annual caps, honorarium rate, payment terms, compliance approval status, legal review status, and debarment/exclusion screening results (OIG, GSA SAM, FDA Debarment List checks). Supports anti-kickback compliance validation (ensuring compensation within FMV bounds), exclusion screening before financial transfers, and Sunshine Act reporting for all contracted HCP payments.' .

ind:HcpPublication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Hcp Publication' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Scientific publications authored or co-authored by KOLs and HCPs relevant to the company\'s therapeutic areas. Captures publication title, journal name, publication date, PubMed ID, DOI, publication type (original research, review, case report, editorial), therapeutic area, product relevance, author order, and company-sponsored flag. Supports medical affairs publication planning, KOL influence mapping, and competitive intelligence.' .

ind:Investigator rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Investigator' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Clinical trial investigator records for HCPs serving as principal investigators (PIs) or sub-investigators on company-sponsored or investigator-initiated trials. Captures investigator role, GCP training status, CV on file, financial disclosure (Form FDA 3455), IRB approval status, site affiliation, therapeutic area expertise, enrollment performance metrics, and trial participation history. Provides the HCP-domain view of investigator identity and qualifications; clinical trial operational data (protocol, enrollment, visits) resides in the clinical domain. Supports regulatory submissions (Form FDA 1572) and clinical operations planning.' .

ind:Vendor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all external suppliers, vendors, CROs, CMOs, and CDMOs engaged by the organization. Captures vendor identity, classification (API supplier, excipient supplier, packaging supplier, service provider, CRO, CMO, CDMO), tax identifiers, business registration details, GMP certification status, preferred vendor flag, vendor tier, payment terms, currency, incoterms, lifecycle status, and associated manufacturing/warehouse/laboratory sites with their GMP/GDP certification scope and regulatory registration numbers. SSOT for vendor identity and site topology within the procurement domain.' .

ind:VendorSite rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Site' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Physical manufacturing, warehouse, or service delivery sites associated with a vendor. Captures site address, site type (manufacturing, distribution, laboratory, office), GMP certification scope, GDP certification status, country of origin, site capacity, site qualification status, and regulatory registration numbers (FDA establishment ID, EMA site number). A single vendor may operate multiple qualified sites.' .

ind:VendorQualification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Qualification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records the formal qualification lifecycle of a vendor or vendor site against GMP, GDP, and supplier quality requirements. Tracks qualification type (initial, re-qualification, for-cause), qualification status (pending, approved, conditionally approved, suspended, disqualified), qualification date, expiry date, responsible quality owner, applicable material categories, and reference to the qualifying audit or assessment. Supports 21 CFR Part 211 and ICH Q10 supplier qualification requirements.' .

ind:SupplierAudit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Audit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of GMP and GDP audits conducted at vendor locations, including all individual findings, observations, and CAPA tracking through to closure. Captures audit metadata (type, date range, lead auditor, team, scope, overall outcome), individual findings with classification (critical/major/minor/observation), regulatory references (e.g., 21 CFR 211.68, EU GMP Annex 11), root cause categories, proposed CAPAs, CAPA owners, due dates, verification status, and closure dates. References audit reports in Veeva Vault QualityDocs. Supports regulatory inspection readiness and supplier quality oversight.' .

ind:AuditFinding rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit Finding' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual observations and findings raised during a supplier GMP or GDP audit. Captures finding reference number, finding classification (critical, major, minor, observation), finding description, regulatory reference (e.g., 21 CFR 211.68, EU GMP Annex 11), root cause category, proposed CAPA, CAPA owner at vendor, CAPA due date, CAPA verification status, and finding closure date. Linked to the parent supplier_audit record.' .

ind:SupplierQualityAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Quality Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal quality agreements (SQAs) executed between the organization and its GMP suppliers, CROs, CMOs, and CDMOs. Captures agreement version, effective date, expiry date, scope of supply (materials, services, manufacturing steps), GMP responsibilities matrix, change notification requirements, audit rights clause, CoA requirements, deviation notification obligations, and signatory details. Mandated under 21 CFR 211.84 and EU GMP Chapter 7 for outsourced activities.' .

ind:SourcingEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Sourcing Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Strategic sourcing events (RFI, RFP, RFQ) managed through SAP Ariba, including all vendor bid responses and evaluation outcomes. Captures event metadata (type, title, commodity category, business unit, status, deadline, evaluation criteria/weightings, invited vendors) and complete bid detail per vendor (quoted prices, lead times, MOQ, payment terms, technical/commercial scores, total evaluated cost, bid status, evaluator comments). Enables end-to-end competitive sourcing from event publication through bid evaluation to vendor award decision.' .

ind:SourcingBid rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Sourcing Bid' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Vendor responses and bids submitted in response to a sourcing event (RFI/RFP/RFQ). Captures bid submission date, vendor quoted price, quoted lead time, minimum order quantity (MOQ), payment terms offered, technical compliance score, commercial score, total evaluated cost, bid status (submitted, under evaluation, shortlisted, rejected, awarded), and evaluator comments. Enables competitive bid comparison and supplier selection decisions.' .

ind:SupplyContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Supply Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Commercial contracts and framework agreements with suppliers covering supply of APIs, excipients, packaging materials, laboratory supplies, and outsourced services. Captures contract terms (type, value, currency, dates, auto-renewal, payment terms, incoterms, price escalation, volume commitments, termination notice) and complete tiered pricing schedules (price per unit, volume breaks, price validity periods, price basis including fixed/indexed/cost-plus, index references, approved price change history). Integrates with SAP MM outline agreements and Ariba contract workspace. Enables accurate PO pricing and landed cost calculations.' .

ind:ContractPriceSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Price Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Tiered pricing schedules and price validity periods attached to procurement contracts. Captures material or service code, price per unit, unit of measure, currency, volume break thresholds, price validity start and end dates, price basis (fixed, indexed, cost-plus), index reference (e.g., CPI, PPI chemical index), and approved price change history. Enables accurate PO pricing and landed cost calculations for COGS reporting.' .

ind:PurchaseRequisition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Purchase Requisition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Internal purchase requisitions (PRs) raised by business units requesting procurement of materials or services. Captures requisition number, requesting plant or cost center, material or service description, required quantity, unit of measure, required delivery date, estimated value, requisition status (created, approved, sourced, PO created, cancelled), approval workflow stage, and preferred vendor if specified. Source document for purchase order creation in SAP MM (ME51N).' .

ind:PurchaseOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Purchase Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Legally binding purchase orders issued to vendors for supply of raw materials (APIs, excipients), packaging materials, laboratory supplies, and services. Captures complete PO document including header (PO number, type, vendor, plant, delivery address, dates, payment terms, incoterms, total value, currency, GMP-relevant flag, status), all line items (material, quantities ordered/confirmed/delivered/invoiced, pricing, storage location, batch management flag), and delivery schedule lines for blanket orders and scheduling agreements. Core transactional entity in SAP MM (ME21N/ME22N). Supports three-way matching with goods_receipt and vendor_invoice.' .

ind:PoLineItem rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Po Line Item' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual line items within a purchase order, each representing a distinct material or service being procured. Captures line item number, material number (SAP material master), material description, material type (API, excipient, packaging, laboratory reagent, service), ordered quantity, unit of measure, confirmed quantity, delivered quantity, invoiced quantity, net price, total line value, storage location, batch management flag, GMP-relevant flag, and delivery schedule. Enables granular tracking of multi-material POs.' .

ind:GoodsReceipt rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Goods Receipt' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of physical receipt of materials against purchase orders at manufacturing plants, warehouses, or laboratories. Captures goods receipt document number, posting date, delivery note number, vendor batch number, received quantity, unit of measure, storage location, receiving plant, GR status (unrestricted, quality inspection, blocked), CoA received flag, temperature excursion flag (for cold-chain materials), and SAP material document reference (MIGO). Triggers quality inspection and inventory posting in SAP MM/QM.' .

ind:IncomingInspection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Incoming Inspection' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Quality inspection records for incoming materials received from vendors, covering API, excipient, packaging, and laboratory supply receipts. Captures inspection lot number (SAP QM), inspection type (skip-lot, reduced, normal, tightened per sampling plan), material batch number, inspection start and completion dates, number of samples drawn, test methods applied (USP, EP, JP compendial), CoA review status, identity test result, assay result, impurity profile, microbiological test result, overall inspection decision (approved, rejected, conditionally released), and disposition reason. Supports 21 CFR 211.84 incoming material testing and ICH Q7 Section 7 requirements. Triggers material release or rejection workflow.' .

ind:VendorInvoice rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Invoice' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Vendor invoices received for goods and services procured, processed through three-way matching (PO, GR, invoice) in SAP MM/FI. Captures complete invoice document including header (invoice number, dates, total amount, currency, tax, payment terms, match status, approval status) and all line items (material/service, quantities, unit prices, PO/GR references, tax codes, account assignments including cost center, WBS element, G/L account, and line-level match status). Enables granular three-way matching and spend analytics at both document and line level for AP processing and COGS reporting.' .

ind:InvoiceLineItem rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Invoice Line Item' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual line items on a vendor invoice, each corresponding to a PO line item or service entry sheet. Captures invoice line number, material or service description, invoiced quantity, unit of measure, unit price, line total, PO reference line, GR reference, tax code, account assignment (cost center, WBS element, G/L account), and match status. Enables granular three-way matching and spend analytics at the material and cost center level.' .

ind:VendorPerformance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Performance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Periodic supplier performance scorecards, KPI tracking, quality complaints, and non-conformance records for qualified vendors. Captures performance metrics (OTIF, CoA compliance, quality complaints count, deviation attribution, audit scores, responsiveness, CAPA closure rate, overall rating, trend), and detailed complaint/non-conformance records (type including OOS result/foreign matter/mislabelling/documentation error/delivery damage/temperature excursion, affected material/batch, severity, dates, root cause, corrective action, resolution status, financial claims). Supports strategic supplier relationship management, re-qualification triggers, and continuous improvement programs.' .

ind:VendorComplaint rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Complaint' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal quality complaints and non-conformance records raised against vendors for material or service failures. Captures complaint reference number, complaint type (OOS result, foreign matter, mislabelling, documentation error, delivery damage, temperature excursion), affected material and batch, complaint severity, complaint date, vendor notification date, vendor response date, root cause provided by vendor, corrective action committed, complaint resolution status, and financial claim amount if applicable. Feeds into vendor performance scoring and re-qualification triggers.' .

ind:ApprovedVendorList rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Approved Vendor List' ;
    rdfs:comment 'The Approved Vendor List (AVL) — the authoritative register of vendors and vendor-material combinations that are qualified and approved for procurement of GMP-relevant materials and services. Captures material or service category, vendor, vendor site, approval status (approved, conditionally approved, suspended, delisted), approval date, next re-qualification due date, approval scope (e.g., API grade, excipient grade, packaging component), and quality system reference. Mandatory control under 21 CFR 211.84 and EU GMP Chapter 7.' .

ind:CroCmoEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Cro Cmo Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master records for formal engagements with Contract Research Organizations (CROs), Contract Manufacturing Organizations (CMOs), and CDMOs covering outsourced clinical, development, and manufacturing activities. Captures engagement type (clinical CRO, bioanalytical CRO, CMO drug substance, CMO drug product, CDMO integrated), scope of work summary, engagement start and end dates, technical agreement reference, quality agreement reference, technology transfer status, regulatory filing impact flag (IND/NDA/BLA/MAA), primary technical contact, governance meeting cadence, and engagement status (active, on-hold, winding-down, terminated). Distinct from the commercial supply_contract — this captures the operational and technical relationship including technology transfer milestones.' .

ind:SourcingMaterial rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Sourcing Material' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Procurement-specific attributes for raw materials, APIs, excipients, packaging components, and laboratory supplies managed within the procurement domain. Captures SAP material number, purchasing group, purchasing organization, GMP-relevant flag, controlled substance flag (DEA schedule), cold-chain requirement, reorder point, safety stock level, standard lead time, and preferred vendor. SSOT BOUNDARY: This product owns ONLY procurement-specific attributes (purchasing parameters, sourcing preferences, procurement lead times). The enterprise material master in the masterdata domain owns material identity, classification, and base attributes. Cross-reference via SAP material number.' .

ind:DeliverySchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Delivery Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Planned and confirmed delivery schedules for materials under blanket purchase orders and scheduling agreements with vendors. Captures schedule line number, scheduled delivery date, confirmed delivery date, scheduled quantity, confirmed quantity, delivery tolerance percentage, shipping notification (ASN) received flag, actual delivery date, and schedule adherence status. Enables supply planning integration with Kinaxis RapidResponse and proactive management of supply continuity risks.' .

ind:ProductionOrder rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Production Order' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core manufacturing execution record representing a discrete production order for drug substance (DS), drug product (DP), or packaging/labeling operations. Captures order type (process order, production order, packaging order), planned/actual quantities, scheduled and actual start/finish dates, production facility, manufacturing line, order status (created, released, confirmed, technically complete), priority, batch size, unit of measure, material/SKU, NDC code (for packaging), reconciliation data, and linkage to master batch record. Central transactional entity for all manufacturing execution aligned with SAP PP module.' .

ind:BatchRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Batch Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Electronic batch record (eBR) representing the complete manufacturing history of a specific batch of drug substance or drug product, as required under 21 CFR Parts 210/211 and cGMP. Captures batch number, product code, batch size, manufacturing date, expiry date, retest date, manufacturing site, batch status (in-process, released, rejected, quarantine), master batch record reference, yield data (theoretical vs actual, yield percentage, reconciliation status), disposition decision (release/reject with approver and rationale), material consumption actuals, parent/child batch genealogy links, and campaign reference. Serves as the primary cGMP compliance document and SSOT for batch lifecycle from production through disposition. Sourced from MES and SAP PP/QM.' .

ind:MasterBatchRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Master Batch Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'The approved master batch record (MBR) template defining the standard manufacturing instructions, formulation, process steps, critical process parameters (CPPs) with target values and acceptance criteria, critical quality attributes (CQAs), in-process control specifications, equipment requirements, and expected yields for a specific product and batch size. Represents the recipe or master formula from which individual batch records are generated. Tracks version number, approval status, effective date, superseded date, product code, dosage form, batch size range, and regulatory approval linkage. Serves as the SSOT for all parameter specifications — parameter names, types, target values, control limits (upper/lower), specification limits, and acceptance criteria. Actual measured values during execution are recorded in process_parameter_result, not here. Managed in Veeva Vault QualityDocs or MasterControl.' .

ind:Site rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Site' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master data for physical manufacturing facilities including owned sites and CMO/CDMO contract sites. Captures site name, site code, address, country, site type (API manufacturing, formulation, fill-finish, packaging, combination), GMP certification status, regulatory approval status (FDA, EMA, PMDA registered), site capacity, site owner (internal vs CMO/CDMO), ERP plant code, and operational status. Serves as the SSOT for manufacturing location master data within the manufacturing domain.' .

ind:Line rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Line' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master data for individual production lines, suites, or manufacturing units within a site. Captures line code, line name, line type (granulation, blending, compression, coating, filling, lyophilization, packaging), associated site, capacity (units/hour or kg/batch), equipment train composition, cleanroom classification, validated status, current operational status (available, in-use, under maintenance, decommissioned), and qualification expiry date. Enables production scheduling and capacity planning at the line level.' .

ind:Equipment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Equipment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master data for manufacturing equipment assets including reactors, blenders, granulators, tablet presses, filling machines, lyophilizers, autoclaves, and packaging lines. Captures equipment ID (tag number), equipment name, equipment type, manufacturer, model, serial number, installation date, qualification status (IQ/OQ/PQ), next qualification due date, calibration status, next calibration due date, associated manufacturing line and site, current status (operational, under maintenance, quarantined, decommissioned), and SAP PM equipment number. Supports equipment scheduling and GMP compliance.' .

ind:EquipmentQualification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Equipment Qualification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of equipment qualification activities including Installation Qualification (IQ), Operational Qualification (OQ), and Performance Qualification (PQ) as required under cGMP and 21 CFR Part 211. Captures qualification type, equipment reference, qualification protocol number, execution date, qualification outcome (pass/fail), next requalification date, approver, and associated validation report reference. Tracks the qualification lifecycle for each piece of equipment to ensure GMP compliance and readiness for production use.' .

ind:ProductionSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Production Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Planned production schedule for manufacturing lines and sites over a defined planning horizon. Captures schedule version, planning period (start/end date), site, manufacturing line, scheduled production orders, planned batch quantities, scheduled downtime windows, campaign plan, and schedule status (draft, approved, frozen, executed). Integrates with SAP PP capacity planning and Kinaxis RapidResponse supply chain planning. Enables capacity utilization analysis and production campaign management.' .

ind:ProcessParameter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Process Parameter' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Defines and records Critical Process Parameters (CPPs) and non-critical process parameters for manufacturing processes, including both the specification (target values, control limits, specification limits) from the master batch record and the actual measured values recorded during batch execution from MES, PAT instruments, or manual entry. Captures parameter name, type (CPP vs non-critical), process step, target value, control/specification limits, unit of measure, measurement frequency, PAT indicator, and per-batch actual measurements with timestamps, instrument IDs, and pass/fail status. Supports QbD principles, process validation, CPV trending, and regulatory inspection readiness per ICH Q8/Q9/Q10.' .

ind:ProcessParameterResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Process Parameter Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Actual measured values of critical process parameters (CPPs), non-critical process parameters, and in-process control (IPC) results recorded during batch manufacturing execution. Captured from MES, PAT instruments, SCADA systems, or manual entry in the electronic batch record. Captures batch reference, process step, parameter name, parameter type (CPP, non-critical, IPC), measured value, unit of measure, measurement timestamp, measurement method, instrument ID, operator ID, pass/fail evaluation against specification limits defined in the master batch record, deviation flag, and PAT indicator. This entity is the sole SSOT for all in-process parameter measurements — parameter specifications (targets, control limits, acceptance criteria) are owned by master_batch_record while this entity owns all actuals. Provides the complete CPP/CQA data trail for each batch, supporting QbD principles, process validation (Stage 2/3), continued process verification (CPV) trending, statistical process control, and regulatory inspection readiness per ICH Q8/Q9/Q10 and 21 CFR 211.188.' .

ind:ManufacturingDeviation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Manufacturing Deviation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records unplanned departures from approved manufacturing procedures, specifications, or batch records during production. Captures deviation number, batch reference, deviation type (process, equipment, material, environmental, documentation), description, severity (critical, major, minor), detection date, detection phase (in-process, packaging, QC testing), root cause category, immediate containment actions, impact assessment, CAPA reference, closure date, and regulatory reportability flag. Integrates with MasterControl/TrackWise QMS. Distinct from quality CAPA records owned by the quality domain.' .

ind:BillOfMaterials rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Bill Of Materials' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Manufacturing bill of materials (BOM) defining the complete list of raw materials, APIs, excipients, and packaging components required to produce a specific drug product at a defined batch size, including individual component line items. Captures BOM version, product code, batch size, BOM status (active, superseded), and for each component: sequence number, item code, description, category (DS, excipient, solvent, packaging, label), required quantity, unit of measure, overage allowance, substitution flag, GMP grade requirement, and approved supplier reference. Aligned with SAP PP BOM and master batch record formulation. Supports MRP calculations, material traceability, and procurement.' .

ind:ProcessValidation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Process Validation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of process validation studies conducted to demonstrate that a manufacturing process consistently produces a product meeting its predetermined specifications and quality attributes, per FDA Process Validation Guidance (2011) and ICH Q8/Q10. Covers all validation types including process validation (Stages 1-3), cleaning validation (dirty hold time, clean hold time, swab/rinse recovery), and computer system validation (CSV/CSA for MES, SCADA, LIMS). Captures validation protocol number, product, process step or system, validation stage (Stage 1 prospective, Stage 2 process qualification, Stage 3 continued process verification), validation type (process, cleaning, computerized system, analytical method transfer), number of validation batches or runs, acceptance criteria, validation outcome (pass/fail/conditional), approval date, revalidation triggers, and next periodic review date. Supports lifecycle approach to validation per ICH Q12.' .

ind:EnvironmentalMonitoring rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Environmental Monitoring' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records of environmental monitoring (EM) results for cleanrooms and controlled manufacturing areas, capturing microbial and particulate data as required under cGMP for sterile and non-sterile manufacturing. Captures monitoring location, cleanroom classification (ISO 5/6/7/8, Grade A/B/C/D), monitoring type (viable air, surface, personnel, non-viable particulate), sample date/time, organism identified, colony forming units (CFU), action limit, alert limit, pass/fail status, and trend flag. Supports contamination control strategy per Annex 1 (EMA) and 21 CFR 211.42.' .

ind:CmoOversight rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Cmo Oversight' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master data and performance tracking for Contract Manufacturing Organizations (CMOs) and CDMOs engaged to manufacture drug substances or drug products on behalf of the company. Captures CMO/CDMO name, site reference, contracted product(s), contract type (DS manufacturing, DP manufacturing, fill-finish, packaging), quality agreement reference, technical agreement reference, audit status, last audit date, next audit due date, approved vendor list (AVL) status, performance scorecard metrics (on-time delivery, batch success rate, deviation rate), and relationship manager. Distinct from procurement supplier master.' .

ind:QualityCapa rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Quality Capa' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Corrective and Preventive Action records managing the full CAPA lifecycle from initiation through effectiveness verification. Captures root cause analysis methodology (5-Why, Fishbone, FMEA), assigned owner, due dates, action plan details, regulatory commitment flag, effectiveness check criteria, closure status, and linkage to originating QMS events. Integrates with MasterControl/TrackWise CAPA module and SAP QM.' .

ind:QualityDeviation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Quality Deviation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Planned and unplanned deviation records capturing departures from approved procedures, specifications, or GMP requirements during manufacturing, laboratory, or clinical operations. Tracks deviation category (planned/unplanned), GMP impact classification, affected batch/lot, process step, immediate containment actions, disposition recommendation, regulatory notification requirement, and linkage to CAPA. Sourced from SAP QM and TrackWise.' .

ind:OosInvestigation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Oos Investigation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Out-of-Specification (OOS) investigation records for laboratory test results that fall outside established acceptance criteria. Captures Phase I (laboratory investigation) and Phase II (full-scale investigation) findings, assignability determination, retesting authorization, invalidation justification, final disposition, regulatory reporting obligation, and linkage to affected batch and test result. Governed by FDA OOS guidance and 21 CFR 211.192.' .

ind:QualityChangeControl rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Quality Change Control' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Change control records managing all proposed changes to processes, equipment, materials, facilities, systems, and documents under GMP. Captures change type (minor/major/critical), change rationale, risk assessment, regulatory impact assessment (requires prior approval vs. notification), validation/qualification requirements, implementation plan, affected products and markets, approval workflow status, and post-implementation review. Sourced from MasterControl/TrackWise and SAP QM.' .

ind:Audit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for quality audits and regulatory inspections including internal GMP audits, supplier/CMO qualification audits, and regulatory agency inspections (FDA PAI, EMA GMP, MHRA). Captures audit type, scope, lead auditor, audit team, site/facility audited, audit dates, pre-audit preparation status, audit agenda, overall audit outcome, and individual findings with classification (critical/major/minor/observation), cited regulation, response commitments, response due dates, and closure verification. Integrates with MasterControl and Veeva Vault QualityDocs.' .

ind:LabTestResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Lab Test Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Laboratory quality control test results from LIMS (LabWare/SampleManager) capturing analytical testing of raw materials, in-process samples, drug substance, drug product, and stability samples. Records test method, instrument used, analyst, test date, raw result value, unit of measure, specification limit (lower/upper), pass/fail determination, OOS/OOT flag, reviewed/approved status, and CoA inclusion flag. Primary source for OOS and OOT investigations.' .

ind:StabilityStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Stability Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stability study records managing ICH-compliant long-term, accelerated, intermediate, and stress stability programs including study design, scheduling, and individual time-point test results. Captures study protocol number, ICH storage conditions (25°C/60%RH, 30°C/65%RH, 40°C/75%RH), container-closure system, study type (registration, commitment, ongoing, photostability), pull-point schedule with actual pull dates, individual test results per time point (assay, degradation products, dissolution, appearance, pH, viscosity), result values against specification limits, pass/fail status, OOT flags, statistical trend analysis, shelf-life determination, and regulatory submission reference. Governed by ICH Q1A-Q1F and WHO stability guidelines. Sourced from LIMS stability module.' .

ind:MethodValidation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Method Validation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Analytical method validation records demonstrating that a test method is fit for its intended purpose per ICH Q2(R1). Captures method type (assay, identification, impurity, dissolution), validation parameters assessed (specificity, linearity, accuracy, precision, LOD, LOQ, robustness), validation protocol number, validation report reference, regulatory submission inclusion flag, method transfer status, and compendial method flag. Sourced from LIMS and Veeva Vault.' .

ind:Coa rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Coa' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Certificate of Analysis (CoA) records issued for released batches of drug substance, drug product, excipients, and raw materials. Captures CoA number, issuing site, product name, batch/lot number, manufacturing date, expiry date, test parameters with results and specifications, overall release decision, authorized signatory, customer/recipient, and regulatory market applicability. Integrates with SAP QM and LIMS for automated CoA generation.' .

ind:BatchDisposition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Batch Disposition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Batch release and disposition decision records capturing the formal quality unit decision to release, reject, reprocess, rework, or retest a manufactured batch per 21 CFR 211.22 and EU GMP Annex 16. Records disposition type, Qualified Person (QP) or quality unit approver, disposition date, disposition rationale, regulatory hold flag, market applicability (US, EU, JP, ROW), quarantine status, and linkage to batch record, CoA, and any open deviations or OOS investigations that must be resolved prior to release. Sourced from SAP QM.' .

ind:Complaint rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Complaint' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Product quality complaint records from healthcare professionals, patients, distributors, and regulatory agencies regarding marketed pharmaceutical products. Captures complaint source, category (efficacy, safety, quality defect, packaging/labeling), affected product and lot number, market of origin, initial risk assessment, investigation findings, root cause, regulatory reportability determination (MedWatch, MHRA Yellow Card), corrective action taken, response communication, trend flag, and closure status. Integrates with pharmacovigilance domain for safety-related complaints and SAP QM for quality complaints. Sourced from TrackWise/Veeva Vault.' .

ind:Validation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Validation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified validation records managing the complete lifecycle of process, equipment, cleaning, and computer system validation under GMP — from protocol definition through execution to final report. Captures validation type (IQ/OQ/PQ, process validation stages 1-3, cleaning validation, CSV/21 CFR Part 11), protocol number, acceptance criteria, validation team, execution dates, individual test step results, deviations observed during execution, overall outcome (pass/fail/conditional), validation report reference, and linkage to change control. Supports continued process verification (CPV) as a validation type. Governed by ICH Q8/Q9/Q10, EMA Annex 15, FDA Process Validation Guidance, and GAMP 5. Sourced from MasterControl/Kneat and SAP QM.' .

ind:Specification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Specification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Product and material quality specification records defining acceptance criteria for drug substances, drug products, raw materials, excipients, packaging components, and in-process controls. Captures specification type (release, shelf-life, in-process), test parameter, acceptance criterion (numeric limit or qualitative), analytical method reference, pharmacopoeial standard (USP, EP, JP), specification version, effective date, and regulatory approval status. Sourced from SAP QM and LIMS.' .

ind:SupplierQualification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Supplier Qualification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Quality qualification, agreement, and ongoing oversight records for approved suppliers, CMOs, CDMOs, and CROs providing materials or services under GMP. Captures supplier qualification status (approved/conditional/disqualified), qualification type (audit-based, questionnaire, CoA review), approved material/service scope, quality agreement details (GMP responsibilities matrix, regulatory market coverage, agreement type, effective/expiry dates, review cycle, counterparty obligations), re-qualification schedule, risk tier classification, performance metrics, and approval workflow. Serves as the single quality record for supplier relationships — distinct from procurement vendor master. Sourced from MasterControl/TrackWise and Veeva Vault QualityDocs.' .

ind:Employee rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Employee' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all personnel at Pharmaceuticals including full-time, part-time, contract, and CRO-seconded staff. Captures personal details, employment status, job classification, department assignment, site location, hire date, termination date, employment type, regulatory role flags (GCP/GMP/GLP-qualified), manager reference, HR system identifiers, and complete lifecycle movement history (promotions, transfers, site relocations, secondments, role changes, organizational restructuring events with effective dates, reason codes, and approver audit trail). Serves as the SSOT for workforce identity and career history across all domains and the anchor entity for training compliance, access control, and regulatory inspection queries.' .

ind:Department rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Department' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Organizational unit hierarchy master representing departments, divisions, cost centers, and functional groups within Pharmaceuticals. Captures unit name, unit type (department, division, function, site), parent unit, cost center code, site location, therapeutic area alignment, and effective dates. Supports organizational reporting and workforce planning. Aligns with SAP S/4HANA organizational management.' .

ind:Position rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Position' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Authorized position master and job profile catalog defining all approved roles, headcount slots, and standardized role requirements within the organizational structure. Captures position title, job family, job level, grade band, FTE allocation, reporting line, site, department, GMP/GCP/GLP qualification requirement flags, regulated role indicator, position status (filled, vacant, frozen), required competencies, mandatory training curricula, applicable SOPs, and job profile reference data including competency expectations, required qualifications, and regulatory role classifications. Serves as the single template for recruitment requisitions, training compliance determination, performance evaluation criteria, and organizational design. Distinct from employee — a position can be vacant or shared.' .

ind:JobProfile rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Job Profile' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference catalog of standardized job profiles defining role requirements, competency expectations, required qualifications, GCP/GMP/GLP training mandates, and regulatory role classifications. Each job profile maps to a job family, job level, and applicable SOPs. Used as the template for position creation and performance evaluation. Distinct from position (which is a headcount slot) and employee (who fills it).' .

ind:EmploymentContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Employment Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of employment agreements between Pharmaceuticals and individual employees. Captures contract type (permanent, fixed-term, CRO secondment), start date, end date, notice period, probation period, working hours, salary grade, contract status, governing jurisdiction, and amendment history reference. Supports HR compliance, audit readiness, and regulatory inspection documentation.' .

ind:GxpTrainingRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Gxp Training Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record managing the full GxP training lifecycle for regulated personnel — from assignment through completion and requalification. Captures training assignments (due dates, assignment reasons such as role change, SOP update, new hire, periodic requalification, assigned-by reference, escalation flags), completion records (date, method, assessment score, pass/fail, trainer, SOP version), expiry dates, and qualification status. Covers GCP, GMP, and GLP training for FDA/EMA inspection readiness and 21 CFR Part 11 compliance. Sourced from MasterControl or TrackWise QMS.' .

ind:TrainingCourse rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Training Course' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master catalog of all training courses available to Pharmaceuticals employees including GMP, GCP, GLP, SOPs, safety, and professional development courses. Captures course code, title, course type, regulatory classification (GxP/non-GxP), delivery method, duration, passing score threshold, requalification frequency, owning department, and version. Serves as the SSOT for training curriculum definitions used in MasterControl or TrackWise.' .

ind:TrainingAssignment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Training Assignment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record linking employees to mandatory or elective training courses based on their role, job profile, site, or regulatory requirement. Captures assignment date, due date, assignment reason (role change, SOP update, new hire, periodic requalification), completion status, escalation flag, and assigned-by reference. Enables training compliance tracking and overdue training reporting for GxP-regulated roles.' .

ind:Qualification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Qualification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record of professional qualifications, certifications, regulatory competencies, and system access authorizations held by employees. Captures qualification type (GMP qualification, GCP certification, analytical method qualification, auditor certification, DEA handler authorization), system role assignments (SAP, LIMS, MES, Veeva, EDC access with role name, access level, system name), issuing body, assignment/issue date, expiry date, renewal/review status, business justification, approver, and supporting document reference. Serves as the single source of truth for all personnel authorizations — both professional and system-level. Supports 21 CFR Part 11 electronic records compliance, SOX access controls, periodic access review, and personnel qualification packages for FDA/EMA inspections.' .

ind:PerformanceReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Performance Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of formal employee performance evaluations conducted on annual or mid-year cycles. Captures review period, overall rating, competency ratings, individual and team goal definitions with weights and achievement scores, development feedback, reviewer identity, calibration status, and final approval date. Includes cascaded goal-setting from corporate strategy to individual contributors. Supports talent management, promotion decisions, compensation planning, and succession readiness assessment.' .

ind:CompensationPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Compensation Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record defining total rewards structures and tracking employee benefit enrollments at Pharmaceuticals. Covers base salary bands, bonus targets, long-term incentive (LTI) eligibility, merit increase parameters by grade band, and comprehensive benefit program enrollments (health, dental, vision, life insurance, pension/401k, FSA, employee assistance programs). Captures plan definitions, geographic market differentials, individual employee enrollment records including coverage tier, effective dates, dependent count, employee/employer contribution amounts, enrollment status, and open enrollment lifecycle. Supports workforce cost planning, annual compensation cycles, open enrollment, pay equity analysis, and benefits administration in SAP SuccessFactors.' .

ind:PayrollRun rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Payroll Run' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of payroll processing cycles and individual employee payslips for Pharmaceuticals. Captures payroll period, run date, payroll area (country/entity), run status (simulated, posted, reversed), total gross/net pay aggregates, and individual employee-level pay details (payslips) including base salary, overtime, bonuses, allowances, tax deductions, social security, pension contributions, net pay, and payment method. Supports financial reconciliation with SAP S/4HANA FI module, employee self-service pay statements, statutory reporting, and payroll audit per jurisdiction.' .

ind:Payslip rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Payslip' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of individual employee payslips generated per payroll cycle. Captures employee reference, payroll period, gross pay, net pay, base salary, overtime pay, bonus payment, allowances, tax deductions, social security contributions, pension contributions, and payment method. Supports employee self-service, payroll audit, and statutory compliance reporting per jurisdiction.' .

ind:BenefitEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Benefit Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of employee enrollment in benefit programs including health insurance, dental, vision, life insurance, pension/401k, employee assistance programs, and flexible spending accounts. Captures benefit plan type, coverage tier, enrollment date, effective date, dependent count, employee contribution amount, employer contribution amount, and enrollment status. Sourced from SAP HCM Benefits module.' .

ind:LeaveRequest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Leave Request' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of employee leave requests and absences including annual leave, sick leave, parental leave, study leave, and unpaid leave. Captures leave type, requested start date, end date, duration in days, approval status, approver identity, reason code, and balance impact. Supports workforce availability planning, payroll deductions, and compliance with local labor regulations across Pharmaceuticals global sites.' .

ind:RecruitmentRequisition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Recruitment Requisition' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of approved headcount requisitions initiating the talent acquisition process. Captures requisition number, position reference, hiring manager, department, site, job profile, required qualifications, GxP role flag, target start date, requisition status (draft, approved, open, filled, cancelled), sourcing channel, and budget approval reference. Supports workforce planning and talent pipeline management.' .

ind:Candidate rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Candidate' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for job applicants in the talent acquisition pipeline, including their complete application history to specific requisitions. Captures candidate identity, contact details, source channel, qualifications, therapeutic area expertise, GxP experience flag, visa/work authorization, and per-application transactional details including application date, application source, screening status, interview stage, assessment scores, offer status, rejection reason, background check status, pre-employment medical clearance for GxP roles, and hiring decision. Supports end-to-end recruitment tracking from sourcing through offer acceptance across multiple requisitions.' .

ind:JobApplication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Job Application' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of a candidate\'s application to a specific recruitment requisition. Captures application date, application source, screening status, interview stage, assessment scores, offer status, rejection reason, and hiring decision. Links candidate to requisition and tracks the full selection workflow including background check status and pre-employment medical clearance for GxP roles.' .

ind:HeadcountPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Headcount Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record of strategic workforce planning, headcount management, and succession planning for Pharmaceuticals. Captures planning period, org unit, approved FTE count, current FTE count, open positions, attrition assumptions, hiring plans, budget envelopes, plan status, and scenario modeling for clinical/manufacturing/commercial scale-up. Also captures detailed succession plans for critical and regulated roles (Qualified Person, Responsible Pharmacist) including target position, incumbent, successor candidates with readiness levels (ready now, 1-2 years, 3-5 years), development gap assessments, retention risk ratings, GxP qualification readiness, therapeutic area criticality, and plan review dates. Supports annual workforce planning cycles, business continuity for regulated roles, and regulatory continuity planning.' .

ind:SystemAccess rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'System Access' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of system role and access rights assignments for employees in quality-critical and regulated functions. Captures system name (SAP, LIMS, MES, Veeva, EDC), role name, access level, assignment date, expiry date, business justification, approver, and review status. Supports 21 CFR Part 11 electronic records compliance, SOX access controls, and periodic access review for GxP systems.' .

ind:EmployeeMovement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Employee Movement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of all employee lifecycle movements including promotions, lateral transfers, site relocations, secondments to CROs/CMOs, role changes, and organizational restructuring events. Captures movement type, effective date, previous position, new position, previous org unit, new org unit, previous grade, new grade, reason code, and approver. Provides a complete audit trail of workforce changes for HR and regulatory inspection readiness.' .

ind:SuccessionPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Succession Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record of succession planning for critical and regulated roles at Pharmaceuticals. Captures target position, incumbent employee, successor candidates (multiple per position), readiness level (ready now, 1-2 years, 3-5 years), development gap assessment, retention risk rating, GxP qualification readiness, therapeutic area criticality, and plan review date. Supports talent pipeline management, business continuity for Qualified Person and Responsible Pharmacist roles, and regulatory continuity planning.' .

ind:LegalEntity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Legal Entity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all legal entities within the pharmaceutical enterprise including subsidiaries, affiliates, joint ventures, and holding companies. Captures legal name, registration number, jurisdiction of incorporation, entity type (operating company, holding, JV), tax identification numbers, registered address, functional currency, consolidation group, and SAP company code mapping. Serves as the organizational backbone for financial consolidation, regulatory submissions, and cross-system entity resolution.' .

ind:OrgUnit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Org Unit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for organizational units within the enterprise hierarchy including business units, divisions, departments, and functional groups. Captures unit name, unit type (business unit, division, department, function, team), parent unit reference for hierarchy traversal, effective dates, responsible manager, geographic location, headcount, and SAP organizational element mapping. Supports HR organizational structure, operational reporting hierarchies, and management accountability across SAP S/4HANA, Veeva, and LIMS.' .

ind:CostCenter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Cost Center' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for SAP cost centers used in management accounting and financial controlling. Captures cost center code, description, cost center category (production, administration, R&D, sales), responsible person, valid-from and valid-to dates, controlling area, profit center assignment, and functional area classification. Serves as the primary financial dimension for cost allocation across manufacturing, clinical, and R&D operations.' .

ind:ProfitCenter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Profit Center' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for SAP profit centers representing autonomous business segments for internal profitability reporting. Captures profit center code, name, hierarchy node, responsible manager, segment classification (therapeutic area, product line, geography), controlling area, and dummy profit center flag. Enables P&L reporting by therapeutic area (oncology, immunology, rare diseases) and product portfolio.' .

ind:ChartOfAccounts rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Chart Of Accounts' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record defining all general ledger account codes used across the pharmaceutical enterprise. Captures GL account number, description, account type (asset, liability, equity, revenue, expense), account group, P&L vs balance sheet classification, tax category, reconciliation account indicator, IFRS/US-GAAP mapping, R&D capitalization eligibility flag, and controlling integration settings. Governs financial reporting consistency across all company codes, enabling compliant reporting under multiple accounting standards and supporting pharma-specific accounting requirements (R&D expense vs capitalization, milestone revenue recognition, royalty accruals).' .

ind:Material rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Material' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Central master record for all materials managed within the pharmaceutical enterprise including APIs (Active Pharmaceutical Ingredients), excipients, drug substances (DS), drug products (DP), finished dosage forms (FDF), packaging materials, laboratory reagents, and raw materials. Captures material number, INN (International Nonproprietary Name), USAN, material type, base unit of measure, material group, gross/net weight, shelf life, storage conditions, hazardous material classification, GMP classification, and cross-system identifiers (SAP material number, LIMS material code). SSOT for material identity across SAP MM, LIMS, and MES.' .

ind:Plant rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Plant' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for manufacturing plants, packaging sites, distribution centers, and R&D facilities within the pharmaceutical enterprise. Captures plant code, plant name, plant type (manufacturing, packaging, distribution, R&D, QC laboratory), address, country, GMP certification status, regulatory authority registrations (FDA establishment registration, EMA site number), capacity class, and SAP plant code. Supports manufacturing network planning, regulatory site management, and supply chain operations.' .

ind:StorageLocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Storage Location' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for storage locations within pharmaceutical manufacturing and distribution plants. Covers warehouses, cold rooms (2-8°C, -20°C, -80°C), controlled substance vaults (DEA Schedule II-V), quarantine zones, QC sampling areas, returns processing areas, and hazardous material storage. Captures storage location code, plant assignment, temperature range, humidity control requirements, DEA license number (for controlled substances), GMP zone classification (Grade A-D), GDP compliance status, capacity in storage units, and WMS integration flag. Critical for batch traceability, cold-chain integrity, controlled substance accountability, and regulatory inspection readiness.' .

ind:UnitOfMeasure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Unit Of Measure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for units of measure used across pharmaceutical operations including mass (mg, g, kg), volume (mL, L), concentration (mg/mL, %w/v), potency (IU, mcg), packaging (vial, ampoule, blister, tablet, capsule), and analytical units (ppm, ppb, CFU/mL). Captures UOM code, UOM description, UOM category, ISO unit code, SAP internal UOM, conversion factors to SI base units, and applicable regulatory standards. Ensures consistent measurement across SAP, LIMS, and MES.' .

ind:Country rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Country' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for countries and territories relevant to pharmaceutical operations, regulatory submissions, and commercial activities. Captures ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 and alpha-3 codes, country name, region, sub-region, regulatory authority (FDA, EMA, MHRA, PMDA, NMPA), ICH region membership, currency code, language, and pharmaceutical market classification (regulated, semi-regulated, unregulated). Supports regulatory submission routing, market access planning, and supply chain geography.' .

ind:AtcClassification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Atc Classification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for the WHO Anatomical Therapeutic Chemical (ATC) classification system used to classify pharmaceutical substances by organ/system and therapeutic, pharmacological, and chemical properties. Captures ATC code at all five levels (anatomical main group, therapeutic subgroup, pharmacological subgroup, chemical subgroup, chemical substance), ATC level description, DDD (Defined Daily Dose), DDD unit, and administration route. Serves as the global standard for drug classification across regulatory submissions, pharmacovigilance, and commercial analytics.' .

ind:MasterdataNdcCode rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Masterdata Ndc Code' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for National Drug Codes (NDC) assigned to pharmaceutical products marketed in the United States. Captures NDC number (10-digit or 11-digit format), labeler code, product code, package code, proprietary name, nonproprietary name (INN/USAN), dosage form, route of administration, strength, labeler name, marketing status, application number (NDA/ANDA/BLA), and DEA schedule. Serves as the US product identifier for commercial, supply chain, and pharmacovigilance operations.' .

ind:InnRegistry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Inn Registry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for International Nonproprietary Names (INN) as assigned by the WHO for pharmaceutical substances. Captures INN name, USAN (United States Adopted Name), recommended INN status, substance class (small molecule, biologic, vaccine, gene therapy), pharmacological class, CAS registry number, molecular formula, and WHO INN publication reference. Serves as the global nonproprietary naming standard for drug substances across regulatory submissions, labeling, and scientific communications.' .

ind:SystemCrosswalk rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'System Crosswalk' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Cross-system identifier mapping table maintaining authoritative golden-record mappings between master data entity identifiers across the pharmaceutical technology landscape. Maps materials, business partners, sites, compounds, and organizational units between SAP S/4HANA, Veeva Vault, LIMS, MES, Argus Safety, and Medidata Rave. Captures source system, target system, entity type, source identifier, target identifier, mapping direction, mapping status (active, deprecated, pending validation), effective/expiry dates, confidence score, and last reconciliation timestamp. Enables MDM golden record resolution, system integration reconciliation, merger/acquisition data harmonization, and audit trail for identifier lifecycle.' .

ind:Address rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Address' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for standardized physical and postal addresses used across pharmaceutical operations including manufacturing sites, distribution centers, clinical trial sites, vendor locations, and customer ship-to/bill-to addresses. Captures address line 1-3, city, state/province, postal code, country, address type (registered, operational, shipping, billing), geocoordinates, address validation status, and standardization source (USPS, Royal Mail, Deutsche Post). Serves as the cross-domain address SSOT referenced by vendor, customer, plant, and site entities.' .

ind:BusinessPartner rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Business Partner' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified master record and Single Source of Truth (SSOT) for ALL external business partners in the pharmaceutical enterprise, following the SAP S/4HANA Business Partner model. Encompasses all vendor/supplier roles (API suppliers, CMOs, CDMOs, CROs, excipient suppliers, packaging suppliers, laboratory reagent vendors) and all customer roles (wholesalers, distributors, hospital networks, pharmacy chains, GPOs, government health agencies) under a single authoritative identity. Captures BP number, BP category (person, organization, group), BP role(s) (supplier, customer, carrier, CMO, CRO, distributor), legal name, tax identification numbers, GMP certification status, qualification status, approved vendor list (AVL) flag, DEA registration number, HIN (Health Industry Number), GLN (Global Location Number), payment terms, credit limits, bank details, sales organization assignment, distribution channel, currency, and cross-system identifiers (SAP BP number, Veeva account ID, LIMS supplier code). Role-specific attributes maintained per role assignment. This is the sole authoritative product for external party identity — no other product in this domain masters vendor or customer identity.' .

ind:Patient rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Patient' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Core master entity representing a patient or clinical trial participant. Single source of truth for patient identity across clinical trials, pharmacovigilance, and market access programs. Captures demographics (date of birth, sex, gender, race, ethnicity), contact information, primary language, nationality, country of residence, patient status (active, deceased, lost-to-follow-up), global patient identifier (GPID), cross-system identifiers (CTMS subject number, EDC ID, PV case patient ID, specialty pharmacy ID, EHR MRN), pseudonymization token for HIPAA/GDPR compliance, master patient index (MPI) linkage, consent status flag, data privacy classification, and audit metadata. Authoritative record for all downstream patient-linked data products.' .

ind:PatientEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Patient Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing a participant\'s enrollment into a clinical trial, patient support program, or patient registry, including full disposition lifecycle. Tracks enrollment type (clinical_trial, support_program, registry), enrollment date, randomization date/number, assigned treatment arm, site/investigator identifiers, enrollment status lifecycle (screened, enrolled, randomized, completed, withdrawn, screen-failed), screen failure reason, protocol/ICF version at enrollment. Disposition tracking: disposition event type (completed, withdrawn, lost-to-follow-up, death, screen failure, protocol deviation withdrawal), disposition date, primary and secondary reason codes (standardized per CDISC CT), last dose date, last contact date, and analysis population assignment flags (ITT, mITT, PP, safety). Single source of truth for both enrollment and disposition — serves as authoritative source for CDISC SDTM DM/DS domain derivation and CSR population summaries.' .

ind:InformedConsent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Informed Consent' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Unified consent lifecycle management covering clinical informed consent (ICF), re-consent events, consent withdrawals, and all data privacy authorizations. Clinical consent: ICF version, consent/withdrawal dates, consenting investigator, witness, method (paper, eConsent), language, sub-study consent flags (genetic, biomarker, future use). Privacy consent: GDPR Article 6/9 lawful basis, HIPAA authorization, consent purpose (data processing, research, marketing, data sharing), data subject rights requests (access, erasure, portability, rectification), request/fulfillment dates, jurisdiction (EU, US, UK, JP), consent channel (web, paper, verbal). Captures consent category (clinical_icf, re-consent, withdrawal, privacy_gdpr, privacy_hipaa, data_sharing), LAR/caregiver reference for pediatric populations, and full audit trail. Single source of truth for ALL consent types — clinical and privacy. Mandatory for GCP compliance, regulatory inspection readiness, HIPAA/GDPR compliance, and data subject rights fulfillment.' .

ind:ConcomitantMedication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Concomitant Medication' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records all concomitant medications taken by a participant during a study or program period. Captures WHO Drug-coded medication name, ATC classification code, dose, dose unit, route of administration, frequency, start date, stop date, ongoing flag, indication for use, and whether the medication is a prohibited concomitant per protocol. Critical for safety assessment, drug-drug interaction analysis, and pharmacovigilance case narratives.' .

ind:AdverseEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Adverse Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures all adverse events (AEs) and serious adverse events (SAEs) reported by or for a participant during a clinical trial or post-market surveillance program. Records MedDRA-coded preferred term (PT) and system organ class (SOC), onset date, resolution date, severity grade (CTCAE), seriousness criteria (death, hospitalization, life-threatening, etc.), causality assessment, action taken with study drug, outcome, SAE flag, SUSAR flag, and reporting timeline compliance status. Feeds into Argus Safety / Oracle AERS for regulatory reporting.' .

ind:TreatmentExposure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Treatment Exposure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Longitudinal record of a participant\'s actual exposure to investigational medicinal product (IMP) or approved therapy. Captures drug name, INN, lot number, dose administered, planned dose, dose unit, route of administration, administration date and time, cycle number, visit number, dose modification flag, dose modification reason, cumulative dose, and treatment compliance percentage. Supports PK/PD analysis, dose-response modeling, and safety signal assessment.' .

ind:ClinicalObservation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Clinical Observation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Consolidated clinical findings and measurements collected from participants across all observation categories. Covers laboratory results (LOINC-coded tests, specimen type, toxicity grade), vital signs (blood pressure, heart rate, temperature, weight, BMI, respiratory rate, SpO2), biomarker/genomic results (CDx, TMB, PD-L1, MSI, PGx panels, gene mutations), and clinical endpoint assessments (RECIST 1.1, iRECIST, DAS28, ECOG PS, Karnofsky). Captures measurement category, test/assessment name, coding (LOINC, assay type), specimen type, collection date/time, visit name, result value, result unit, reference range, out-of-range flag, toxicity grade (CTCAE), result interpretation, assessor, assessment method, laboratory/assay identifier, and delta-from-prior flag. Aligned with OMOP CDM measurement table and CDISC findings-class domains (LB, VS, MB, TR). Sourced from EDC (Medidata Rave), LIMS (LabWare), central labs, and molecular diagnostics vendors.' .

ind:ReportedOutcome rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Reported Outcome' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Captures structured patient-reported outcome (PRO) and quality of life (QoL) data collected via validated instruments (e.g., EQ-5D, FACT-G, SF-36, PROMIS). Records instrument name, instrument version, domain/subscale name, item identifier, response value, total score, subscale score, completion date, completion method (ePRO, paper), visit name, and compliance flag. Supports QoL endpoints, HEOR submissions, and market access dossiers.' .

ind:Registry rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Registry' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for patient registries maintained or sponsored by the organization. Covers disease registries (e.g., rare disease natural history studies), pregnancy registries, post-authorization safety studies (PASS), and REMS-mandated registries. Captures registry name, type, therapeutic area, indication, sponsoring organization, regulatory mandate flag, start and planned end dates, target and current enrollment counts, data collection frequency, governing regulatory authority, and registry protocol version. Supports pharmacovigilance commitments, post-marketing requirements (PMRs), and market access evidence generation.' .

ind:SupportProgram rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Support Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for patient support programs (PSPs) and hub services including copay assistance, adherence monitoring, nurse educator support, reimbursement/prior authorization support, and specialty pharmacy coordination. Master attributes: program name, type, associated product (NDC/brand), eligibility criteria, program dates, maximum benefit amount, operational vendor, program status. Copay assistance transactions: claim date, pharmacy identifier, NDC dispensed, quantity, days supply, gross cost, patient OOP amount, assistance amount applied, remaining benefit balance, payer eligibility (commercial only — government patients ineligible), rejection reason code. Adherence monitoring: prescribed regimen, actual doses, MPR, PDC, adherence tier, data source (specialty pharmacy, ePRO, connected device), intervention triggered flag. This is the single source of truth for ALL PSP activity including copay claims formerly tracked separately. Supports commercial access strategy, patient retention, and HEOR real-world evidence.' .

ind:ProtocolDeviation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Protocol Deviation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Documents protocol deviations and violations identified for a participant during a clinical trial. Captures deviation type (inclusion/exclusion criteria, dosing, visit window, prohibited medication, consent), deviation date, discovery date, severity classification (major/minor), impact on participant safety, impact on data integrity, corrective action taken, CAPA reference, and regulatory reportability flag. Sourced from Veeva Vault QualityDocs and Medidata Rave. Critical for GCP compliance and regulatory inspection readiness.' .

ind:BiomarkerResult rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Biomarker Result' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Stores biomarker and genomic/molecular profiling results for participants, including companion diagnostic (CDx) results, tumor mutation burden (TMB), PD-L1 expression, microsatellite instability (MSI) status, gene mutation panels, pharmacogenomic (PGx) markers, and protein biomarker assay results. Captures biomarker name, assay type, specimen type, collection date, result value, result unit, result interpretation (positive/negative/indeterminate), assay laboratory, assay kit version, and CDx regulatory approval status. Supports precision medicine and patient stratification.' .

ind:Diagnosis rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Diagnosis' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Longitudinal record of all patient conditions encompassing pre-existing medical history, prior diagnoses, surgical history, family history, and study-relevant primary/secondary diagnoses. Captures condition type (pre-existing, primary, secondary, comorbidity, surgical, family_history), ICD-10 code, MedDRA-coded term, onset date, resolution date, ongoing flag, severity, diagnosis method (histological, clinical, radiological), disease stage (TNM, ECOG PS), histology type, biomarker-defined subtype, relationship to study indication, and source (self-reported, medical record, investigator assessment). Subsumes the former medical_history concept — all pre-existing conditions and surgical/family history are stored here with appropriate type discriminators. Supports eligibility determination, safety signal contextualization, stratification, pharmacovigilance case assessment, and CDISC SDTM MH/CM domain derivation.' .

ind:EndpointAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Endpoint Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records clinical efficacy and safety endpoint assessments performed on participants, including tumor response assessments (RECIST 1.1, iRECIST), disease activity scores (DAS28, CDAI), functional assessments (ECOG PS, Karnofsky), and imaging-based assessments. Captures assessment type, assessment date, visit name, assessor identifier, result value, result category (CR, PR, SD, PD for oncology), prior assessment reference, and assessment method. Supports primary and secondary endpoint derivation for regulatory submissions.' .

ind:Caregiver rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Caregiver' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for caregivers and legally authorized representatives (LARs) associated with participants, critical for pediatric trials, rare disease programs, and patients lacking capacity to consent. Captures caregiver name, relationship to participant (parent, spouse, legal guardian, healthcare proxy), contact information, LAR designation flag, authority documentation reference, effective date, and end date. Required for informed consent validity in pediatric/incapacitated populations and for patient support program communications.' .

ind:TimeAttendance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Workforce ;
    rdfs:label 'Time Attendance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record of employee time and attendance entries including clock-in/clock-out, shift assignments, overtime hours, break periods, and absence codes for manufacturing, laboratory, and clinical operations staff. Captures date, shift pattern, scheduled hours, actual hours, overtime category, cost center allocation, and approval status. Critical for GMP manufacturing compliance where personnel presence during batch production must be documented, and for labor cost allocation to production orders in SAP S/4HANA.' .

ind:TechnologyTransfer rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Technology Transfer' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Records technology transfer activities for moving manufacturing processes between sites, from R&D to commercial manufacturing, or to/from CMO/CDMO partners. Captures transfer protocol number, source site, receiving site, product code, transfer type (site-to-site, R&D-to-commercial, CMO onboarding, CMO offboarding), transfer stage (initiation, knowledge transfer, process demonstration, qualification batches, regulatory submission, approval, closure), key deliverables checklist (analytical methods, process parameters, cleaning procedures, stability data), readiness assessment status, regulatory change control reference, transfer team members, planned/actual completion dates, and transfer outcome. Critical for CMO/CDMO lifecycle management and multi-site manufacturing networks per ICH Q10 pharmaceutical quality system requirements.' .

ind:Biospecimen rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Biospecimen' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for each biological specimen (tissue biopsy, blood draw, urine, CSF) collected from a trial subject at protocol-defined timepoints. Captures specimen type, collection date, collection visit, tube/container type, volume/quantity, processing method, storage temperature, biobank location, shipment tracking to central lab, LOINC/SNOMED coding, chain-of-custody audit trail, and associated assay results reference. Critical for oncology trials requiring RECIST tumor assessments, pharmacogenomic stratification, companion diagnostic validation, and translational research endpoints. Sourced from LIMS integration with Medidata Rave EDC.' .

ind:MonitoringVisit rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Monitoring Visit' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for each monitoring visit conducted by a Clinical Research Associate (CRA) at an investigational site. Captures visit type (routine, triggered, close-out), visit date, CRA name, source data verification (SDV) completion percentage, critical findings, follow-up letter date, CAPA items raised, site risk score update, and confirmation of GCP compliance observations. Tracks resolution status of prior visit findings. Core operational record for GCP oversight per ICH E6 R2 section 5.18 and supports risk-based monitoring (RBM) strategies.' .

ind:Allocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Allocation and Available-to-Promise (ATP) decision record for constrained pharmaceutical products including biologics, orphan drugs, and launch products. Captures allocation rule, allocated customer/channel, allocated quantity, allocation period, constraint reason (capacity, raw material shortage, regulatory hold), priority tier (contractual obligation, government contract, compassionate use, commercial), approval status, and allocation effective/expiry dates. Supports fair-share allocation algorithms, government contract compliance (340B, VA/DoD), and launch sequencing. Critical for managing product scarcity scenarios common in specialty pharma and biologics.' .

ind:ProductQualityReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Product Quality Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Annual Product Quality Review (APQR) / Product Quality Review (PQR) records aggregating quality performance data for each marketed product on an annual cycle as required by ICH Q10, EU GMP Chapter 1, and 21 CFR 211.180(e). Captures review period, product scope, batch analysis summary, deviation/CAPA/OOS trends, stability trending, change control summary, complaint trends, recall history, process capability metrics, revalidation needs, management review conclusions, and approved action items. Serves as the primary input to management review and continual improvement decisions.' .

ind:TherapeuticArea rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Therapeutic Area' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference master for therapeutic areas (oncology, immunology, rare diseases, neuroscience, etc.) used to classify products, trials, and research programs' .

ind:DeviceComponent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Device Component' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for drug-device combination product device components (auto-injectors, inhalers, prefilled syringes) with design history and specifications' .

ind:Excipient rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Excipient' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for pharmaceutical excipients used in drug product formulations, capturing functional category, grade, compendial status, and supplier qualification' .

ind:BioequivalenceStudy rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Bioequivalence Study' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for bioequivalence and bioavailability studies required for generic drug approvals and formulation changes, tracking study design and results' .

ind:GxpObligation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Gxp Obligation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for all GxP regulatory obligations applicable to the enterprise, including GMP, GCP, GLP, GDP, and GPvP requirements. Captures the obligation source (regulation, guideline, directive), applicable jurisdiction, scope (site, function, product), effective date, obligation owner, and current compliance status. Serves as the authoritative register of what the organization is required to do under GxP frameworks including 21 CFR Parts 210/211, EU GMP Annex 1-20, ICH Q10, and equivalent global standards.' .

ind:Program rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Program' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for enterprise-wide compliance programs managed by the compliance function, including GxP compliance programs, SOX internal controls programs, data integrity programs, GDPR/privacy programs, anti-bribery and corruption (ABAC) programs, and Sunshine Act/HCP transparency programs. Captures program name, regulatory framework, program owner, scope, governance structure, program charter, risk tier, and lifecycle status. Each program is a distinct, managed compliance initiative with its own governance, budget, and reporting cadence.' .

ind:InternalControl rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Internal Control' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for internal controls established to satisfy regulatory requirements, SOX obligations, and GxP compliance mandates. Captures control ID, control name, control type (preventive, detective, corrective), control category (IT general control, business process control, entity-level control), control owner, frequency (continuous, daily, monthly, annual), testing method, and SOX applicability flag. Links to regulatory requirements and compliance programs. Serves as the authoritative control inventory for SOX Section 302/404 and GxP compliance assurance.' .

ind:ControlAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Control Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing the periodic testing and assessment of internal controls. Covers SOX control testing, GxP compliance assessments, and IT general control (ITGC) evaluations. Captures assessment period, assessor identity, testing approach (walkthrough, sample testing, full population), sample size, test results (effective, ineffective, not tested), deficiency classification (control deficiency, significant deficiency, material weakness), and remediation status. Feeds SOX 404 management assessment and external auditor reliance programs.' .

ind:InspectionReadiness rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Inspection Readiness' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for regulatory inspection readiness programs and activities at the site, function, or product level. Captures readiness program scope (FDA PAI, EMA GMP inspection, MHRA, WHO PQ), target inspection window, readiness coordinator, mock inspection schedule, readiness score, identified gaps, remediation actions, and final readiness determination. Tracks the enterprise\'s preparedness posture for announced and unannounced regulatory inspections across all GxP-regulated functions.' .

ind:RegulatoryInspection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Regulatory Inspection' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for regulatory inspections conducted by health authorities at company sites, CRO/CMO partners, or clinical investigational sites. Captures inspection type (GMP, GCP, GLP, GDP, pharmacovigilance, pre-approval), inspecting agency, inspection dates, lead inspector, scope, site inspected, inspection outcome (no action indicated, voluntary action indicated, official action indicated, warning letter), and follow-up status. Distinct from quality.audit (which covers internal and supplier audits) — this is the authoritative record for external regulatory authority inspections.' .

ind:InspectionObservation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Inspection Observation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Individual observation, finding, or citation raised during a regulatory inspection. Captures observation reference number, observation text (verbatim from inspector), observation classification (critical, major, minor, informational), CFR/GMP citation, assigned response owner, proposed corrective action, response due date, health authority response submission date, and closure status. Each inspection generates multiple observations that must be tracked and responded to independently. Feeds the inspection response and CAPA workflow.' .

ind:InspectionResponse rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Inspection Response' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Formal written response submitted to a health authority in reply to inspection observations, warning letters, or untitled letters. Captures response document reference, response type (483 response, warning letter response, establishment inspection report response), submission date, response author, regulatory affairs liaison, commitments made, timeline for corrective actions, and health authority acknowledgment status. Tracks the complete response lifecycle from drafting through health authority closure.' .

ind:Part11System rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Part11 System' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for computerized systems subject to 21 CFR Part 11 (FDA) and EU Annex 11 (EMA) electronic records and electronic signatures regulations. Captures system name, system owner, GxP criticality classification, validation status, audit trail capability, electronic signature implementation, access control configuration, system category (infrastructure, laboratory, manufacturing, clinical), and Part 11/Annex 11 compliance determination. Serves as the authoritative inventory of regulated computerized systems requiring Part 11/Annex 11 compliance management.' .

ind:EsignatureEvent rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Esignature Event' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing each electronic signature event executed within GxP-regulated computerized systems subject to 21 CFR Part 11 and EU Annex 11. Captures signer identity, signer role, system ID, record being signed, signature meaning (reviewed, approved, authored, verified), timestamp, authentication method (biometric, username/password), and non-repudiation confirmation. Provides the audit trail of electronic signature events required for regulatory compliance and inspection readiness.' .

ind:PrivacyObligation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Privacy Obligation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for privacy and data protection obligations applicable to the enterprise under GDPR, CCPA, HIPAA, and other applicable privacy regulations. Captures the regulation, jurisdiction, obligation type (consent management, data subject rights, breach notification, data retention, cross-border transfer), applicable data categories (personal data, sensitive health data, clinical trial data), obligation owner, and compliance status. Distinct from gxp_obligation — this specifically covers privacy law obligations rather than GxP regulatory requirements.' .

ind:PrivacyImpactAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Privacy Impact Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for Data Protection Impact Assessments (DPIAs) and Privacy Impact Assessments (PIAs) conducted for new or changed processing activities involving personal data. Captures processing activity description, data categories processed, data subjects affected, necessity and proportionality assessment, risk identification, risk mitigation measures, DPO consultation outcome, and supervisory authority consultation requirement. Required under GDPR Article 35 for high-risk processing activities including clinical trial data and patient health data.' .

ind:Incident rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Incident' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for compliance incidents, violations, and potential breaches identified across all compliance program areas including GxP violations, SOX control failures, privacy breaches, anti-bribery violations, and Sunshine Act reporting failures. Captures incident description, discovery date, discovery source (self-identified, audit, inspection, whistleblower), incident category, severity, affected regulation, root cause, immediate containment actions, and escalation status. Distinct from quality.deviation (manufacturing/lab deviations) — this covers compliance-specific incidents across all regulatory domains.' .

ind:ComplianceCapa rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Compliance Capa' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Corrective and Preventive Action records specific to the compliance domain, managing remediation of compliance incidents, control deficiencies, inspection observations, and audit findings that fall outside the quality management system scope. Captures CAPA ID, triggering event, root cause analysis methodology, root cause determination, corrective action plan, preventive action plan, action owner, target completion date, effectiveness check criteria, and closure verification. Distinct from quality.capa (which manages GxP manufacturing/lab CAPAs) — this covers compliance-function-owned CAPAs for regulatory, SOX, and privacy remediation.' .

ind:SoxControlTest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Sox Control Test' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for SOX Section 404 internal control over financial reporting (ICFR) test executions performed by management and internal audit. Captures control reference, test period, tester identity, testing approach (inquiry, observation, inspection, re-performance), population size, sample selection methodology, exceptions identified, deficiency classification (control deficiency, significant deficiency, material weakness), and management conclusion. Feeds the annual SOX 404 management assessment and supports external auditor reliance.' .

ind:MonitoringActivity rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Monitoring Activity' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for proactive compliance monitoring activities conducted by the compliance function across business units and functions. Covers HCP engagement monitoring (Sunshine Act), promotional materials compliance monitoring, clinical trial compliance monitoring, and GxP process compliance monitoring. Captures monitoring activity type, scope, period, monitored function/site, monitoring methodology, findings, risk rating, and recommended actions. Supports the enterprise compliance monitoring program and provides early warning of compliance risks before they become incidents.' .

ind:RiskRegister rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Risk Register' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the enterprise compliance risk register tracking identified compliance risks across all regulatory domains (GxP, SOX, GDPR, ABAC, Sunshine Act). Captures risk description, risk category, risk owner, inherent risk rating (likelihood × impact), existing controls, residual risk rating, risk appetite alignment, risk treatment decision (accept, mitigate, transfer, avoid), and risk review cadence. Serves as the authoritative compliance risk inventory for the Chief Compliance Officer and Board Audit Committee reporting.' .

ind:PolicyDocument rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Policy Document' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the enterprise compliance policy and procedure document library including SOPs, policies, guidelines, and work instructions governing GxP, SOX, GDPR, ABAC, and other compliance obligations. Captures document title, document type (policy, SOP, guideline, work instruction), document owner, applicable regulation, version number, effective date, review cycle, approval status, and distribution scope. Distinct from quality SOPs managed in the QMS — this covers compliance-function-owned policies governing enterprise-wide compliance behavior.' .

ind:Disclosure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Disclosure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for mandatory compliance disclosures and regulatory filings managed by the compliance function, including Sunshine Act / Open Payments annual aggregate disclosures, EFPIA Disclosure Code submissions, anti-bribery declarations, conflict of interest disclosures, and beneficial ownership filings. Captures disclosure type, reporting period, submitting entity, regulatory body, submission date, disclosure amount or content, submission status, and acknowledgment receipt. Distinct from commercial.sunshine_disclosure (which is the commercial HCP-level transfer of value record) — this is the aggregate regulatory filing record.' .

ind:ConflictOfInterest rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Conflict Of Interest' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master and transactional record for conflict of interest (COI) declarations submitted by employees, investigators, advisory board members, and HCPs engaged by the company. Captures declarant identity, declaration date, relationship type (financial interest, employment, family relationship, personal relationship), counterparty, declared value or nature of interest, review outcome (no conflict, managed conflict, prohibited conflict), management plan, and annual recertification status. Supports ABAC compliance, clinical trial integrity, and HCP engagement governance.' .

ind:ThirdPartyDueDiligence rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Third Party Due Diligence' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for compliance due diligence assessments conducted on third parties (HCPs, CROs, CMOs, distributors, agents, consultants) prior to engagement and periodically thereafter. Covers anti-bribery and corruption (ABAC) due diligence, sanctions screening, debarment checks (FDA debarment list, OIG exclusion list, OFAC), and reputational risk assessment. Captures third-party identity, engagement type, due diligence tier (simplified, standard, enhanced), screening results, risk rating, approval decision, and periodic re-screening schedule.' .

ind:DebarmentCheck rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Debarment Check' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for individual debarment, exclusion, and sanctions screening checks performed against regulatory exclusion lists including FDA Debarment List (21 CFR Part 312), OIG List of Excluded Individuals and Entities (LEIE), GSA System for Award Management (SAM) exclusions, OFAC Specially Designated Nationals (SDN) list, and EU sanctions lists. Captures individual or entity screened, screening date, lists checked, match status, match details, adjudication outcome, and re-screening trigger. Required for GCP compliance and federal healthcare program participation.' .

ind:Attestation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Attestation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record for formal compliance attestations and certifications submitted by employees, managers, and executives confirming adherence to compliance policies, codes of conduct, and regulatory obligations. Covers annual code of conduct certifications, SOX sub-certifications (CEO/CFO 302 certifications), GxP compliance declarations, and GDPR data handling attestations. Captures attestor identity, attestation type, attestation period, attestation content version, submission date, and any disclosed exceptions or qualifications.' .

ind:WarningLetter rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Warning Letter' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for FDA Warning Letters, Untitled Letters, and equivalent formal enforcement communications received from health authorities. Captures letter reference number, issuing agency, issue date, receiving site or entity, cited violations (CFR citations), product or process scope, response deadline, response submission date, and closure status. Tracks the full lifecycle from receipt through response, commitment fulfillment, and health authority closure. Distinct from inspection_observation (individual findings) and inspection_response (formal response) — this is the authoritative record of the enforcement action itself.' .

ind:DataManagementPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Data Management Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the clinical data management plan (DMP) defining data collection standards, edit checks, coding dictionaries (MedDRA, WHO Drug), database lock criteria, and CDISC SDTM/ADaM mapping specifications for each trial' .

ind:RandomizationSchedule rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Randomization Schedule' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Master record for the randomization scheme and treatment allocation schedule for a clinical trial, including stratification factors, block sizes, randomization ratio, and IWRS/IRT system configuration' .

ind:ColdChainRecord rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Cold Chain Record' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Transactional record capturing temperature monitoring data points and excursion events for cold-chain pharmaceutical products during storage and transit, including sensor readings, excursion duration, and disposition decisions' .

ind:PharmaceuticalProduct rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Pharmaceutical Product' ;
    rdfs:comment 'IDMP ISO 11616 entity representing the administrable pharmaceutical product form — the product as administered to the patient, distinct from the manufactured drug product. Captures administrable dose form, route of administration, unit of presentation, and reference to constituent active ingredients. Bridges drug_product (manufactured form) to clinical usage.' .

ind:SpecifiedSubstance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Specified Substance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'IDMP ISO 11238 entity representing a substance with a specified level of detail including strength, reference strength, and substance role (active, excipient). Links formulation_ingredient to the global substance reference and enables precise regulatory substance identification per IDMP requirements.' .

ind:CdiscDomainMap rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Cdisc Domain Map' ;
    rdfs:comment 'Reference mapping entity linking clinical trial data collection instruments (CRF forms, subject observations) to CDISC standard domains (SDTM, ADaM, SEND). Captures CDISC domain code, version, variable mappings, and controlled terminology references to ensure clinical data submissions conform to FDA/EMA electronic submission requirements.' .

ind:SupplyAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Supply Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the contractual supply relationship between a business partner (in supplier role) and a material. It captures the Approved Vendor List (AVL) qualification, pricing, lead times, and GMP compliance requirements mandated by pharmaceutical regulations. Each record links one business partner to one material with supplier-specific terms that exist only in the context of this supply relationship. Critical for procurement, quality assurance, and regulatory compliance in pharmaceutical supply chain management.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical supply chain operations, a single material (e.g., an API or excipient) is routinely sourced from multiple qualified suppliers to ensure supply continuity, competitive pricing, and regulatory compliance. Conversely, each supplier provides multiple different materials to the pharmaceutical manufacturer. The Approved Vendor List (AVL) is a regulatory requirement under GMP that mandates qualification and ongoing monitoring of each supplier-material combination, with relationship-specific data including pricing, lead times, qualification dates, audit schedules, and GMP certification status that cannot be stored on either the business partner or material entity alone.' .

ind:EntityRegistration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Entity Registration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the country-specific registration and regulatory compliance record for a legal entity operating in a particular jurisdiction. It captures registration numbers, tax identifiers, regulatory licenses, and compliance status that exist only in the context of a specific legal entity operating in a specific country. Each record links one legal entity to one country with jurisdiction-specific regulatory and tax attributes.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical operations, a single legal entity (e.g., Pfizer Inc.) operates in multiple countries with country-specific registrations, tax IDs, and regulatory licenses in each jurisdiction. Conversely, each country hosts multiple legal entities from different pharmaceutical companies. The business actively manages these country-specific registrations as distinct compliance records with jurisdiction-specific attributes (registration numbers, tax IDs, regulatory status, license expiry dates) that cannot be stored on either the legal entity or country master alone.' .

ind:MaterialPlantData rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Material Plant Data' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the plant-specific configuration and planning parameters for materials in pharmaceutical manufacturing operations. It captures MRP settings, quality inspection procedures, storage locations, and procurement rules that exist only in the context of a specific material-plant combination. Each record links one material to one plant with operational parameters that govern how that material is managed at that specific facility.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical manufacturing operations, materials are managed across multiple plant facilities with plant-specific operational parameters, and each plant manages thousands of different materials with unique MRP settings, quality procedures, and storage configurations. Material Plant Data is a foundational SAP MM business concept that captures the intersection of material master data and plant master data, representing how a specific material is procured, planned, stored, and quality-controlled at a specific manufacturing site. This is a textbook many-to-many relationship where the association itself carries rich operational configuration data that belongs to neither the material nor the plant alone.' .

ind:MaterialStorageLocationData rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Masterdata ;
    rdfs:label 'Material Storage Location Data' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the storage configuration and inventory management parameters for a specific material at a specific storage location within pharmaceutical operations. It captures bin assignments, reorder points, stock limits, handling strategies, and environmental monitoring requirements that exist only in the context of a material being stored at a particular location. Each record links one material to one storage location with operational parameters required for SAP WM/EWM, cold-chain integrity, controlled substance accountability, and GMP compliance.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical operations, a single material (e.g., an API or finished drug product) is routinely stored across multiple storage locations (e.g., main warehouse, cold room, quarantine zone, controlled substance vault) to support manufacturing, quality control, and distribution processes. Conversely, a single storage location houses many different materials. Each material-storage location combination requires specific operational parameters including bin assignments, reorder points, stock limits, putaway strategies, and environmental monitoring requirements that are unique to that combination and cannot be stored on either the material master or storage location master alone.' .

ind:PvAgreementProductScope rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Pv Agreement Product Scope' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Coverage relationship between pv_agreement and pv_product. It captures the specific safety data exchange obligations, reporting timelines, and responsible party designations that apply when a particular product falls under a particular pharmacovigilance agreement. Each record links one pv_agreement to one pv_product with attributes that exist only in the context of this relationship - the same agreement may have different exchange timelines or responsible parties for different products, and the same product may be governed by multiple agreements with different counterparties across different territories.. Existence Justification: In pharmacovigilance operations, a single PV agreement routinely covers multiple products (e.g., a CRO agreement covering an entire therapeutic portfolio), and a single product is frequently governed by multiple agreements simultaneously (e.g., different co-promotion agreements in different territories, or a manufacturing agreement plus a licensing agreement). The business actively manages this relationship through agreement negotiation, product scope amendments, and compliance monitoring - tracking which products are covered under which agreements, with what reporting timelines, and which party is responsible for what activities.' .

ind:CommercialFormularyPosition rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Commercial Formulary Position' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formulary placement contract between a pharmaceutical brand and a payer account. It captures the negotiated coverage terms, restrictions, and rebate arrangements that govern how the payer will cover the brand for its members. Each record links one brand to one payer account with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific formulary placement relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical market access operations, each brand must secure formulary placement with multiple payers to ensure patient access across different health plans, and each payer maintains formularies covering hundreds of brands across therapeutic areas. The formulary position is an actively managed business entity where market access teams negotiate tier placement, utilization management restrictions, and rebate terms with each payer for each brand. This relationship has substantial relationship-specific data including tier, restrictions, rebates, and coverage dates that belong to neither the brand nor the payer alone.' .

ind:ImpAdministration rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Imp Administration' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the administration event between investigational_product and visit. It captures each instance of IMP dispensation to a trial subject during a clinical visit, documenting regulatory-required accountability data per ICH E6 R2 and 21 CFR Part 312. Each record links one investigational product (specific batch/lot) to one patient visit with administration-specific attributes including timestamp, dose, route, and deviation tracking that exist only in the context of this administration event.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical trials, investigational medicinal product (IMP) administration is a core regulatory-mandated business process. A single IMP batch can be administered across multiple patient visits (different subjects, different timepoints), and a single patient visit can involve administration of multiple IMPs (combination therapies, dose escalation, or comparator plus active treatment). Each administration event is a distinct regulatory record with its own timestamp, dose, route, lot traceability, and deviation tracking per ICH E6 R2 and 21 CFR Part 312.' .

ind:PatientEnrollment2 rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Patient Enrollment2' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the enrollment relationship between a patient and a patient support program (PSP). It captures the complete lifecycle of a patient\'s participation in a specific support program, including enrollment dates, eligibility verification, benefit tracking, and disenrollment. Each record links one patient to one support program with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific enrollment relationship. This is the operational record that enables tracking of copay assistance utilization, adherence monitoring participation, and program-specific patient outcomes.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical patient services operations, patients routinely enroll in multiple patient support programs simultaneously (e.g., copay assistance for one brand, adherence monitoring for another, nurse educator support for a third therapeutic area). Conversely, each support program serves thousands of patients concurrently. The enrollment relationship is a recognized operational business entity with its own lifecycle, managed actively by patient services teams, hub vendors, and specialty pharmacies.' .

ind:CompoundSupplyAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Compound Supply Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the supply contract between a discovery compound and a procurement vendor. It captures vendor-specific sourcing terms, pricing, quality specifications, and procurement logistics that exist only in the context of this compound-vendor relationship. Each record links one compound to one vendor with commercial and quality attributes negotiated for that specific supply arrangement.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical operations, a single compound can be sourced from multiple vendors to ensure supply security, optimize costs, and maintain regulatory redundancy (multi-sourcing strategy). Conversely, each vendor supplies multiple compounds across the discovery library. The business actively manages these supply relationships as distinct agreements, each with vendor-specific pricing, lead times, purity specifications, catalog numbers, and preferred vendor designations that cannot be stored on either the compound or vendor entity alone.' .

ind:Prescription rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Prescription' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the prescription event between a medicinal product and a patient. It captures the commercial/post-market relationship where a specific medicinal product is prescribed to a specific patient, including prescriber information, dosage instructions, therapy timeline, adherence tracking, and discontinuation details. Each record represents one prescription instance linking one medicinal product to one patient with attributes that exist only in the context of this prescribing relationship. Distinct from clinical trial exposure (protocol-driven) and represents real-world evidence for patient support programs, adherence monitoring, and pharmacovigilance.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical commercial operations, patients routinely receive multiple medicinal products simultaneously (polypharmacy for chronic conditions, combination therapies) or sequentially (treatment switches, dose escalations), and each medicinal product is prescribed to thousands of patients across diverse indications and patient populations. Patient support programs, specialty pharmacies, and real-world evidence teams actively manage prescription-level records as operational entities, tracking adherence metrics, refill patterns, discontinuation reasons, and therapy outcomes for each patient-product combination. This is distinct from clinical trial exposure (which is protocol-mandated) and represents the post-market commercial relationship where prescription records are created, monitored, and analyzed as core business data.' .

ind:ApprovedVendorMaterial rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Approved Vendor Material' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the regulatory approval and quality agreement between a vendor and a specific material they are authorized to supply. It captures vendor-material-specific approval status, quality agreements, DMF references, audit history, and risk classifications that exist only in the context of this specific supply relationship. Each record links one vendor to one material with regulatory and quality attributes that govern the supply of that specific material by that specific vendor.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical operations, a vendor can be approved to supply multiple materials (APIs, excipients, packaging materials), and a material can be sourced from multiple approved vendors to ensure supply continuity and competitive pricing. The approval relationship is actively managed by procurement and quality teams through vendor qualification, audits, quality agreements, and regulatory filings (DMF references). Each vendor-material combination has its own approval status, quality agreement, pricing terms, lead times, and audit history that cannot be stored on either the vendor or material master alone.' .

ind:KolEngagementPlan rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Kol Engagement Plan' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the strategic engagement plan between a market access strategy and a Key Opinion Leader (KOL). It captures the specific role, engagement tier, activity targets, and effectiveness metrics for each KOL\'s participation in a given access strategy. Each record links one access_strategy to one hcp_kol_profile with attributes that exist only in the context of this strategic engagement relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical market access operations, a single access strategy (e.g., launch strategy for a new oncology drug in Germany) engages multiple KOLs across different roles (advisory board members, HTA expert witnesses, publication authors, congress speakers), and each prominent KOL participates in multiple access strategies across different products, indications, and geographies. The business actively manages these engagements as \'KOL Engagement Plans\' with specific roles, activity targets, budgets, and effectiveness tracking for each strategy-KOL combination.' .

ind:ApplicationIndication rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Application Indication' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the regulatory approval pursuit between a regulatory application and a therapeutic indication. It captures the approval status, designation flags, exclusivity dates, and label claims that exist only in the context of a specific application seeking approval for a specific indication. Each record links one application to one indication with jurisdiction-specific approval data, supporting regulatory tracking of multi-indication applications and multi-jurisdiction indication pursuits.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical regulatory operations, a single regulatory application (NDA, BLA, MAA) can seek approval for multiple therapeutic indications, either in the original submission or via supplemental applications (sNDAs). Conversely, a single indication can be pursued across multiple applications in different jurisdictions (US NDA, EU MAA, Japan PMDA) or via different regulatory pathways. Regulatory affairs teams actively manage application-indication pairs, tracking approval status, designation flags, exclusivity dates, and label claims that are specific to each application-indication-jurisdiction combination.' .

ind:ProgramObligationScope rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Compliance ;
    rdfs:label 'Program Obligation Scope' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the assignment of specific GxP regulatory obligations to compliance programs. It captures which obligations are actively managed under which programs, the compliance status of each obligation within the program context, assessment schedules, and risk levels. Each record links one compliance_program to one gxp_obligation with attributes that exist only in the context of this program-obligation relationship, enabling compliance teams to track program effectiveness by obligation and manage regulatory coverage systematically.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical compliance operations, a single compliance program (e.g., GMP Compliance Program) actively manages multiple GxP obligations (e.g., batch record review, equipment qualification, cleaning validation), and conversely, a single GxP obligation (e.g., 21 CFR 211.192 production record review) is often covered by multiple compliance programs across different sites or business units. Compliance teams actively create, update, and manage these program-obligation assignments to ensure comprehensive regulatory coverage, track compliance status per program-obligation pair, and report on program effectiveness by obligation.' .

ind:Engagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational relationship between healthcare professionals and pharmaceutical company employees (MSLs, medical directors, clinical scientists) in medical affairs field operations. It captures the ongoing professional engagement relationship including therapeutic area focus, interaction patterns, relationship strength metrics, and territory assignments. Each record links one HCP to one employee with attributes that exist only in the context of this professional engagement relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical medical affairs operations, multiple employees (MSLs, medical directors, clinical scientists) simultaneously maintain distinct professional engagement relationships with the same HCP across different therapeutic areas, territories, and functional roles. Conversely, each employee manages ongoing relationships with multiple HCPs as part of their territory assignment. The business actively manages these relationships as operational entities with specific attributes (relationship type, therapeutic area focus, engagement frequency, strength scoring, territory assignment, primary contact designation) that belong to neither the HCP nor the employee alone but to the relationship itself.' .

ind:SpeakerProgramPresentation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Hcp ;
    rdfs:label 'Speaker Program Presentation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Event between hcp_speaker_program and medicinal_product. It captures individual speaker program events where an HCP presents on a specific medicinal product. Each record links one speaker program event to one medicinal product with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific presentation: venue details, audience metrics, honorarium paid, materials used, and compliance approvals. Supports Sunshine Act reporting and anti-kickback compliance monitoring.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical speaker bureau operations, HCPs are enrolled to present on multiple medicinal products, and each medicinal product is presented by multiple speakers across different events. The business actively manages individual speaker program presentations as distinct operational entities, tracking venue, audience, honorarium, performance ratings, and MLR-approved materials for each speaker-product-event combination. This is a true operational M:N relationship recognized as \'Speaker Program Presentations\' or \'Program Events\' in the business.' .

ind:DrugDispensation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Drug Dispensation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the dispensation event between inventory_lot and patient in clinical trials. It captures the operational record of investigational product or commercial drug being dispensed from a specific lot to a specific trial participant. Each record links one inventory_lot to one patient with attributes that exist only in the context of this dispensation transaction, including dispense date, quantity, location, status, and return information for GDP compliance and clinical trial accountability.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical trials, drug dispensation represents a true operational many-to-many relationship. A single inventory lot is dispensed to multiple patients over the course of a trial (one lot serves many participants across visits), and a single patient receives drug from multiple lots throughout their trial participation (across visits, cycles, or dose adjustments). The dispensation event is actively managed by clinical supply teams and site pharmacists as a distinct business process with its own lifecycle, attributes, and regulatory requirements.' .

ind:SiteImpAccountability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Site Imp Accountability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the accountability relationship between investigational sites and inventory lots of Investigational Medicinal Product (IMP). It captures the regulatory-mandated tracking of IMP receipt, dispensation, return, and storage at each clinical site. Each record links one investigational site to one inventory lot with attributes that exist only in the context of this site-specific lot accountability. Required under ICH GCP E6 and GDP regulations for clinical trial material traceability.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical trials, investigational sites receive multiple IMP lots over the trial duration due to resupply cycles, different batch releases, and enrollment progression. Each IMP lot is distributed to multiple sites based on enrollment forecasts and geographic distribution. Site-level IMP accountability is a regulatory-mandated business process under ICH GCP E6 and GDP, where Clinical Research Associates actively create, monitor, and reconcile site-lot accountability records during monitoring visits.' .

ind:SiteAffiliation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Site Affiliation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the affiliation relationship between investigational sites and healthcare professionals. It captures the operational reality that HCPs hold privileges, credentials, and roles at multiple clinical sites, and sites maintain rosters of affiliated physicians for trial enrollment capacity planning. Each record links one investigational site to one HCP with attributes that govern the HCP\'s ability to serve as investigator, enroll patients, and perform protocol procedures at that specific site.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical trials, investigational sites maintain rosters of multiple affiliated physicians with varying roles (Principal Investigator, Sub-Investigator, site staff), and healthcare professionals hold privileges and credentials at multiple sites simultaneously. Site feasibility assessments require understanding which HCPs can enroll patients at which sites, and HCPs leverage multi-site affiliations for patient referral networks. This is an operational relationship actively managed through credentialing workflows, delegation of authority documentation, and site activation processes.' .

ind:TrialInvestigator rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Investigator' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the investigator assignment relationship between clinical trials and healthcare professionals. It captures the operational assignment of HCPs to trials in investigator roles (Principal Investigator, Sub-Investigator, Study Coordinator), including GCP training compliance, financial disclosure status, site-specific responsibilities, delegation of authority, and enrollment accountability. Each record links one trial to one HCP with role-specific attributes that exist only in the context of this investigator assignment. Authoritative SSOT for investigator rosters required for regulatory submissions (IND, NDA, BLA, MAA) and eTMF documentation in Veeva Vault.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical trial operations, a single trial requires multiple investigators across sites (Principal Investigators, Sub-Investigators, Study Coordinators), and a single HCP routinely serves as investigator on multiple concurrent trials. The investigator assignment is an operational business entity actively managed by clinical operations teams: assignments are created during site activation, updated as roles/responsibilities change, and tracked throughout the trial lifecycle. The relationship carries substantial operational data (role, GCP training status, financial disclosures, delegation logs, enrollment counts) that belongs to neither the trial nor the HCP alone, but to the specific assignment.' .

ind:AuditSiteInspection rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Quality ;
    rdfs:label 'Audit Site Inspection' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the inspection event between audit and vendor_site. It captures the specific audit activities conducted at each vendor site, including audit outcomes, findings classification, CAPA requirements, and follow-up schedules. Each record links one audit to one vendor site with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific site inspection within a broader audit program.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical supplier quality management, a single audit program can encompass multiple vendor sites (e.g., a CMO with manufacturing facilities in three countries), and each vendor site undergoes multiple audits over time (initial qualification, annual surveillance, for-cause investigations, pre-approval inspections). The business actively manages each audit-site inspection as a distinct quality event with its own findings, CAPA requirements, and follow-up schedules.' .

ind:CompoundExposure rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Discovery ;
    rdfs:label 'Compound Exposure' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the treatment exposure event between a discovery compound and a clinical trial patient. It captures the investigational use of a compound in a patient, including dosing regimen, treatment duration, clinical response, and discontinuation details. Each record links one compound to one patient in the context of a specific treatment episode within a clinical trial. This is the authoritative source for compound-patient exposure history across the discovery-to-clinical continuum.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical development, one compound is tested in many patients across multiple trials and trial phases, and one patient may receive multiple investigational compounds either sequentially (across different trials) or simultaneously (in combination therapy trials). The business actively manages compound-patient exposure records as operational entities with treatment-specific data including dosing regimen, treatment duration, clinical response, and discontinuation reasons. This is a recognized business concept called \'compound exposure\' or \'treatment exposure\' that is critical for pharmacovigilance, efficacy analysis, and regulatory submissions.' .

ind:DistributionServiceAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Distribution Service Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the contractual service agreement between a distribution network node and a payer account. It captures the operational service level commitments, delivery parameters, and cold-chain capabilities that govern how pharmaceutical products flow from specific distribution nodes to specific payer organizations. Each record links one distribution_network node to one payer_account with service-level attributes that exist only in the context of this distribution relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical supply chain operations, a single distribution network node (e.g., a regional distribution center in Frankfurt) serves multiple payer accounts (commercial insurers, PBMs, specialty pharmacies) with potentially different service level agreements, delivery lead times, and cold-chain requirements for each payer. Conversely, a single payer account (e.g., a national PBM like Express Scripts) receives pharmaceutical products from multiple distribution nodes across different geographic regions to ensure supply redundancy, optimize delivery speed, and source products with different temperature requirements. The business actively manages these distribution service agreements as operational contracts with specific service levels, carriers, and capabilities per node-payer pair.' .

ind:FormularyListing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Formulary Listing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the formulary listing relationship between drug_product and payer_account. It captures the specific terms under which a payer covers a drug product on their formulary, including tier placement, authorization requirements, rebate agreements, and coverage dates. Each record links one drug_product to one payer_account with attributes that exist only in the context of this payer-product coverage relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical market access operations, each drug product is listed on multiple payer formularies (commercial plans, Medicare Part D, Medicaid, regional health plans), and each payer account maintains formularies covering hundreds to thousands of drug products. Market access teams actively manage these formulary listings as operational business entities, negotiating tier placement, rebate terms, and access restrictions for each drug-payer combination. The formulary listing is a recognized business concept with its own lifecycle, managed through P&T committee reviews, contract negotiations, and ongoing monitoring.' .

ind:ApprovedVendor rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Approved Vendor' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the qualification and approval relationship between an excipient and a vendor authorized to supply it. It captures vendor-specific qualification status, audit history, compliance verification, and supply agreement terms that exist only in the context of this specific excipient-vendor pairing. Each record represents one approved source for one excipient.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical manufacturing, excipients are routinely multi-sourced from multiple qualified vendors to ensure supply continuity, manage risk, and meet regulatory requirements for alternative sources. Each excipient-vendor pairing requires independent qualification activities including site audits, sample testing, quality agreement execution, and ongoing compliance monitoring. The approved vendor list is an operational business entity actively managed by procurement and quality teams, with vendor-specific and material-specific attributes including qualification status, audit dates, pricing terms, lead times, and risk classifications.' .

ind:StudyDataSourcing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Market ;
    rdfs:label 'Study Data Sourcing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the data sourcing relationship between HEOR studies and RWE datasets. It captures which real-world evidence datasets are used in which HEOR studies, including the role of the dataset in the study, the specific data vintage used, and the contribution characteristics. Each record links one HEOR study to one RWE dataset with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific data sourcing relationship, enabling tracking of dataset reuse across studies and supporting regulatory compliance requirements for model reproducibility.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical market access operations, HEOR studies routinely integrate multiple RWE datasets (claims, EMR, registries) to generate comprehensive evidence, and strategic RWE datasets are reused across multiple studies to maximize ROI on expensive data acquisition costs. The business actively manages this relationship as \'Study Data Sourcing\' with specific attributes (dataset role, contribution type, vintage used, patient counts) that belong to neither the study nor the dataset alone but to each specific study-dataset pairing. This is an operational relationship that HEOR teams create, track, and query for regulatory compliance and model reproducibility.' .

ind:ContractFulfillmentAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Supply ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Fulfillment Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational allocation and fulfillment tracking between inventory lots and payer contracts in pharmaceutical supply chain operations. It captures the business process of allocating specific inventory lots (with their lot numbers, expiry dates, and quality status) to fulfill contracted obligations with payers, PBMs, and GPOs. Each record links one inventory lot to one payer contract with allocation quantities, fulfillment priorities, and contract period tracking that exist only in the context of this lot-to-contract allocation relationship. Critical for gross-to-net revenue management, rebate accrual calculations tied to actual shipped inventory, and GDP-compliant lot traceability to contracted entities.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical supply chain operations, a single inventory lot (batch) can be allocated across multiple payer contracts during shortage scenarios, multi-contract fulfillment strategies, or when optimizing expiry date management across contracted entities. Conversely, a single payer contract is fulfilled by multiple inventory lots over time due to replenishment cycles, batch production schedules, and the need to maintain continuous supply. The business actively manages these lot-to-contract allocations with specific quantities, fulfillment priorities, and contract period tracking.' .

ind:SiteProtocolActivation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Site Protocol Activation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the activation and operational lifecycle of a specific protocol version at a specific investigational site. It captures the regulatory, training, enrollment, and compliance milestones that exist only when a protocol is activated at a site. Each record links one investigational site to one protocol version with attributes tracking activation dates, site-specific enrollment targets, training completion, protocol deviations, and closure dates that belong to neither the site nor the protocol alone but to their operational relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical trial operations, investigational sites participate in multiple clinical trials (each with its own protocol), and each protocol is activated at multiple investigational sites globally. Site Protocol Activation is a recognized operational entity in CTMS systems, tracking the regulatory, training, enrollment, and compliance lifecycle of each protocol version at each site. This relationship carries substantial operational data (activation dates, site-specific enrollment targets, training completion, deviation counts, closure dates) that belongs to neither the site nor the protocol alone.' .

ind:InvestigationalProductSupply rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Manufacturing ;
    rdfs:label 'Investigational Product Supply' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the supply allocation and usage tracking between master batch records (manufacturing specifications for investigational products) and clinical trial investigators. It captures trial-specific supply chain planning, dosing regimens, approved indications, and regulatory traceability requirements per ICH GMP Annex 13. Each record links one master batch record to one investigator with attributes that exist only in the context of this clinical supply relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical operations, a single master batch record (manufacturing specification) is used to produce investigational product that is supplied to multiple investigators across different trials, phases, and sites. Conversely, each investigator typically receives investigational product from multiple master batch records representing different formulations, strengths, or product variants across their portfolio of trials. The business actively manages these supply allocations as distinct operational records with trial-specific attributes.' .

ind:MedicalAdvisoryBoardMembership rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Medical Advisory Board Membership' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the membership relationship between Key Opinion Leaders and Medical Advisory Boards. It captures the formal appointment, participation terms, compensation arrangements, and engagement metrics for each KOL serving on each advisory board. Each record links one KOL to one advisory board with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific membership relationship, including role designation, tenure dates, honorarium details, meeting attendance tracking, and compliance documentation.. Existence Justification: Advisory board membership is a formally managed business relationship in pharmaceutical medical affairs. A single KOL can serve on multiple advisory boards simultaneously (e.g., an oncology KOL may sit on boards for different therapeutic indications or development programs), and each advisory board has multiple KOL members by design (typical member counts range from 8-15 experts). Medical affairs teams actively create, manage, and track these memberships with formal contracts, honoraria, meeting attendance, and compliance documentation.' .

ind:ProductPayerContract rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Product Payer Contract' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the commercial contract between a medicinal product and a payer account. It captures the negotiated terms, rebate agreements, formulary placement, and performance metrics that govern market access and reimbursement. Each record links one medicinal product to one payer account with contract-specific attributes including pricing terms, formulary tier, effective dates, and contract status. This is the operational SSOT for pharmaceutical market access contracting.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical commercial operations, each medicinal product is contracted with multiple payers (commercial insurers, Medicare Part D plans, Medicaid programs, PBMs, GPOs) simultaneously, and each payer maintains active contracts for hundreds to thousands of products in their formulary. The payer contract is a recognized operational entity managed by market access teams, with contract-specific attributes including rebate terms, formulary tier placement, utilization targets, and outcomes metrics that belong to neither the product nor the payer alone.' .

ind:RegistryEnrollment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Patient ;
    rdfs:label 'Registry Enrollment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the enrollment of a medicinal product in a patient registry for post-marketing surveillance, safety monitoring, or regulatory commitment fulfillment. It captures product-specific enrollment data including enrollment dates, treatment context, and outcome tracking. Each record links one medicinal product to one registry with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific product-registry enrollment relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical operations, medicinal products are enrolled in multiple patient registries simultaneously (e.g., a checkpoint inhibitor may be tracked in an oncology disease registry, a pregnancy exposure registry, and a REMS-mandated safety registry). Conversely, each registry monitors multiple medicinal products within its therapeutic scope (e.g., a rare disease registry tracks all approved therapies for that condition). Registry enrollment is an operational business process managed by pharmacovigilance and regulatory affairs teams, with specific enrollment dates, data collection protocols, and outcome tracking for each product-registry combination.' .

ind:KolProductEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Kol Product Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the operational engagement relationship between a Key Opinion Leader and a medicinal product. It captures the specific role, engagement history, indication focus, and compliance-relevant data for each KOL-product pairing. Each record links one medical_kol_profile to one medicinal_product with attributes that exist only in the context of this therapeutic area engagement, advisory relationship, or clinical trial leadership role.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical medical affairs operations, Key Opinion Leaders engage with multiple medicinal products across their therapeutic expertise areas (e.g., an oncology KOL may serve on advisory boards for multiple cancer drugs), and each medicinal product has relationships with multiple KOLs for advisory boards, speaker bureaus, clinical trial leadership, and publication planning. The business actively manages these engagements as distinct operational entities with specific roles, engagement histories, indication focuses, and compliance-tracked transfer-of-value data.' .

ind:ContractPricing rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Contract Pricing' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the commercial pricing contract between a medicinal product and an institutional contract account (GPO, IDN, hospital system, specialty pharmacy). It captures negotiated pricing terms, rebate structures, volume commitments, and contract periods that exist only in the context of this specific product-account relationship. Each record links one medicinal product to one contract account with pricing and terms that are unique to that combination. Supports contract pricing administration, rebate management, and institutional account management business processes.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical commercial operations, institutional contract accounts (GPOs, IDNs, hospital systems, specialty pharmacies) negotiate pricing agreements for multiple medicinal products, and each medicinal product has separate pricing contracts with multiple institutional accounts. The relationship represents a real operational business process: contract pricing administration and rebate management. Commercial teams actively create, negotiate, approve, and manage these contract pricing agreements as distinct business entities with product-account-specific terms.' .

ind:CongressAttendance rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Medical ;
    rdfs:label 'Congress Attendance' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the attendance event between MSL profiles and congress events. It captures the operational record of MSL deployment to medical and scientific congresses, including attendance logistics, engagement activities, and post-congress outcomes. Each record links one MSL to one congress with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific attendance instance.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical medical affairs operations, MSLs are deployed to multiple congresses throughout the year based on therapeutic area alignment, strategic importance, and territory coverage. Each congress hosts multiple MSLs from the same organization performing different roles (presenters, booth staff, attendees). Congress attendance is an actively managed operational process involving planning, approval workflows, budget allocation, logistics coordination, and post-event reporting. The business explicitly tracks attendance as a distinct entity with its own lifecycle and attributes.' .

ind:PatentLicense rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Patent License' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the licensing relationship between a patent and a licensing agreement. It captures the specific terms, scope, and financial arrangements under which each patent is licensed within a broader agreement. Each record links one patent to one licensing agreement with attributes that exist only in the context of this specific patent-agreement pairing, such as territory-specific exclusivity, field-of-use restrictions, and patent-specific royalty rates that may differ from the agreement-level defaults.. Existence Justification: Patent licensing in pharmaceuticals is operationally many-to-many. A single patent (e.g., a composition-of-matter patent covering a blockbuster compound) is routinely licensed through multiple agreements—an exclusive license to Partner A for oncology indications in North America, a co-exclusive license to Partner B for autoimmune indications in Europe, and a non-exclusive license to Partner C for diagnostic use globally. Conversely, a single licensing agreement typically bundles multiple patents—composition patents, formulation patents, method-of-use patents, and process patents—to provide comprehensive IP coverage for a product or platform. Business development teams actively manage these patent-agreement pairings, negotiating patent-specific terms (territory, exclusivity, royalty rates, field-of-use restrictions) that vary within the same agreement.' .

ind:BlockingPatentAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Intellectual ;
    rdfs:label 'Blocking Patent Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the evaluation of third-party patents that may block commercialization of company products or technologies. Each record links one third-party patent to one FTO analysis, capturing the IP counsel\'s assessment of infringement risk, claim mapping, design-around strategies, and licensing recommendations specific to that patent-analysis combination. This is a core operational entity in pharmaceutical IP risk management, actively created and maintained by patent attorneys during FTO assessments.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical IP risk management, FTO analyses routinely evaluate multiple third-party patents that may block commercialization, and each third-party patent may be assessed across multiple FTO analyses for different products or technologies. IP counsel creates blocking patent assessment records that capture patent-specific risk levels, claim mappings, design-around strategies, and licensing recommendations that exist only in the context of a specific patent-analysis combination. This is a recognized operational entity actively managed by patent attorneys.' .

ind:ClinicalAdvisoryBoardMembership rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Clinical Advisory Board Membership' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the membership relationship between principal investigators and medical advisory boards. It captures the formal appointment of a PI to serve on a specific advisory board, including their role, term dates, participation metrics, compensation, and conflict of interest disclosures required for regulatory compliance and transparency reporting. Each record links one principal investigator to one medical advisory board with attributes that exist only in the context of this membership relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical medical affairs operations, principal investigators serve on multiple advisory boards across different therapeutic areas, compounds, and strategic topics, while each advisory board has multiple PI members with diverse expertise. The business actively manages these memberships as formal appointments with specific roles (Chair, Member, Observer), term dates, attendance tracking, FMV-compliant honoraria, and conflict of interest disclosures required for regulatory transparency reporting (Sunshine Act, EFPIA). This is an operational relationship that Medical Affairs creates, monitors, and reports on as a distinct business process.' .

ind:ProductListedness rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Product Listedness' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the regulatory listedness determination between a PV product and its approved therapeutic indications. It captures jurisdiction-specific approval metadata, label claim text, and listedness status used for SUSAR classification and causality assessment in pharmacovigilance case processing. Each record links one pv_product to one product_indication with regulatory approval attributes that exist only in the context of this specific product-indication pairing per jurisdiction.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical pharmacovigilance operations, a single PV product (e.g., ibuprofen 200mg tablet) has multiple approved therapeutic indications across different jurisdictions (pain relief, fever reduction, inflammation), and each indication can apply to multiple PV products (same API in different formulations or strengths). The business actively manages listedness determination records per product-indication-jurisdiction combination for SUSAR classification during adverse event case processing, with each record carrying jurisdiction-specific approval dates, label claim text, and regulatory metadata that belong to neither the product nor the indication alone.' .

ind:RmpReview rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Rmp Review' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the expert review relationship between Risk Management Plans (RMPs) and Healthcare Professionals (HCPs). It captures the formal review process where qualified HCPs (medical reviewers, therapeutic area specialists, external consultants) evaluate RMP documents for regulatory compliance, scientific accuracy, and clinical appropriateness. Each record links one RMP version to one reviewing HCP with attributes documenting the review scope, findings, and approval status required for regulatory audit trails and quality assurance.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical regulatory operations, Risk Management Plans (RMPs) undergo formal expert review by multiple qualified healthcare professionals serving in different roles (medical reviewers, therapeutic area specialists, external consultants). Each RMP version requires review by multiple HCPs with relevant expertise, and each HCP reviews multiple RMPs throughout their engagement with the organization. The review process generates relationship-specific data (review dates, reviewer roles, sections reviewed, comments, approval status) that belongs to neither the RMP nor the HCP alone, but to the specific review event.' .

ind:SignalIndicationAssessment rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Signal Indication Assessment' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the indication-specific safety signal assessment between safety_signal and product_indication. It captures the stratified analysis of how a particular safety signal manifests differently across approved or investigational indications for the same medicinal product. Each record links one safety signal to one product indication with indication-specific signal strength metrics, case distribution, causality assessment, and regulatory action recommendations (label changes, restrictions, contraindications) required for GVP Module IX signal validation and PRAC reporting. Supports the pharmacovigilance requirement that signal validation must be performed with indication-level stratification, as the same adverse event may have different risk profiles, causality, and benefit-risk balance across different therapeutic uses of the product.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical pharmacovigilance operations, a single safety signal (e.g., hepatotoxicity) must be assessed separately for each approved or investigational indication of a medicinal product, because the same adverse event may have different risk profiles, causality, case distributions, and benefit-risk implications across different therapeutic uses. Conversely, each product indication accumulates multiple concurrent safety signals over its lifecycle that require ongoing monitoring and indication-specific regulatory action decisions. This is an operational M:N relationship mandated by GVP Module IX signal validation requirements.' .

ind:SignalExpertConsultation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Pharmacovigilance ;
    rdfs:label 'Signal Expert Consultation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the expert consultation engagement between safety signals and healthcare professional subject matter experts. It captures the formal involvement of HCP experts (KOLs, advisory board members, external consultants) in safety signal evaluation and validation activities. Each record links one safety signal to one HCP expert with consultation-specific attributes including expert opinion, causality assessment, risk evaluation contribution, meeting participation details, and compensation tracking required for regulatory documentation per GVP Module IX and transparency reporting requirements.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical safety signal management, a single safety signal is routinely evaluated by multiple HCP experts (KOLs, advisory board members, therapeutic area specialists) to obtain diverse clinical perspectives for regulatory validation per GVP Module IX requirements. Conversely, each HCP expert consultant evaluates multiple safety signals across different therapeutic areas and products throughout their engagement with the pharmaceutical company. The business actively manages these consultation engagements as discrete operational records with consultation dates, expert opinions, causality assessments, meeting types, and honorarium tracking required for regulatory submissions and transparency reporting.' .

ind:SupplyAllocation rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Supply Allocation' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the supply relationship between a Stock Keeping Unit (SKU) and a manufacturing/packaging plant. It captures the multi-sourcing strategy for each SKU across the pharmaceutical manufacturing network, including primary and secondary supply designations, allocation percentages, lead times, and supply priority. Each record links one SKU to one plant with attributes that exist only in the context of this supply relationship. Critical for supply chain planning, available-to-promise (ATP) calculations, demand allocation during capacity constraints, and supply continuity management during plant shutdowns or regulatory events.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical supply chain operations, SKUs are routinely sourced from multiple manufacturing and packaging plants to ensure supply continuity, balance capacity utilization, and comply with regulatory requirements for multi-site approval. Each plant can produce multiple SKUs across different therapeutic areas and dosage forms. The business actively manages these supply allocations with plant-specific data including allocation percentages, primary/secondary designations, lead times, supply priority rankings, and regulatory approval status for each plant-SKU combination.' .

ind:ImpAccountability rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Imp Accountability' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the accountability record between clinical trials and inventory lots of investigational medicinal products (IMPs). It captures the dispensation, return, and destruction of specific drug product lots used in clinical trials, ensuring full traceability and regulatory compliance per GCP and 21 CFR Part 312. Each record links one trial to one inventory lot with quantities, dates, and accountability status that exist only in the context of this trial-lot relationship. This is the authoritative SSOT for IMP accountability reconciliation required for regulatory inspections and CSR appendices.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical operations, trials consume multiple inventory lots over their lifecycle due to resupply needs, dose escalation cohorts, and multi-site distribution, while individual lots (especially in Phase I or multi-indication studies) are allocated across multiple concurrent trials. IMP accountability is a regulated operational process where clinical teams actively create, monitor, and reconcile dispensation records for each trial-lot combination, tracking quantities dispensed, returned, and destroyed per GCP requirements.' .

ind:TrialVendorEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Clinical ;
    rdfs:label 'Trial Vendor Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Contract between trial and vendor. It captures the formal engagement of external vendors (CROs, central labs, IMP manufacturers, SMOs, imaging vendors, CDMOs) to deliver specific services or materials for a clinical trial. Each record links one trial to one vendor with contractual terms, service scope, performance metrics, and deliverables that exist only in the context of this engagement relationship. This is the authoritative SSOT for vendor-trial service agreements consumed by procurement, clinical operations, and trial management systems.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical clinical trial operations, trials routinely engage multiple vendors simultaneously (CRO for trial management, central lab for sample analysis, CMO for IMP manufacturing, imaging vendor for endpoint assessment, SMO for site recruitment), and vendors serve multiple trials concurrently across the sponsor\'s portfolio. The business actively manages these vendor-trial engagements as distinct operational entities with contractual terms, service scopes, performance metrics, and deliverables tracked per engagement.' .

ind:VendorGxpQualification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Procurement ;
    rdfs:label 'Vendor Gxp Qualification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the qualification and compliance relationship between a vendor and a specific GxP regulatory obligation. It captures the vendor\'s qualification status, audit history, and compliance evidence for each applicable GxP requirement (GMP, GDP, GCP, GLP, GPvP). Each record links one vendor to one GxP obligation with attributes that exist only in the context of this vendor-obligation qualification pair. Essential for supplier oversight, inspection readiness, and regulatory compliance tracking.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical operations, vendors must be qualified against multiple specific GxP obligations depending on the materials or services they supply (e.g., an API supplier must meet GMP requirements, a distributor must meet GDP requirements, a CRO must meet GCP requirements). Conversely, each GxP obligation applies to multiple vendors across the supply chain. The business actively manages this as a \'Vendor GxP Qualification Matrix\' with obligation-specific qualification statuses, audit schedules, and compliance evidence that cannot reside on either the vendor master record or the obligation master record alone.' .

ind:ApplicationSiteAuthorization rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Application Site Authorization' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the regulatory authorization relationship between a regulatory application and a manufacturing site. It captures the site-specific role in the application (API manufacturer, drug product manufacturer, fill-finish, packaging, testing laboratory), the manufacturing step performed at each site, the regulatory approval status of that specific site for that specific application, qualification dates, and capacity allocation. Each record links one application to one manufacturing site with attributes that exist only in the context of this regulatory authorization relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical regulatory operations, a single regulatory application (NDA, BLA, MAA) routinely lists multiple manufacturing sites performing different roles in the supply chain (API synthesis at one site, drug product formulation at another, fill-finish at a third, packaging at a fourth, and testing laboratories). Conversely, a manufacturing site typically supports multiple regulatory applications across different drug products. The business actively manages these authorizations as distinct regulatory compliance artifacts, tracking site-specific approval statuses, qualification dates, manufacturing step assignments, and capacity allocations for each application-site pairing.' .

ind:ServiceEngagement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Service Engagement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the Contract between application and vendor. It captures the engagement of external vendors (CROs, CMOs, regulatory consultants) to support specific regulatory applications with defined services, timelines, and deliverables. Each record links one application to one vendor with attributes that exist only in the context of this service engagement relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical regulatory operations, a single regulatory application (IND, NDA, BLA, MAA) routinely engages multiple external vendors simultaneously: CROs conduct clinical trials, CMOs manufacture drug substance and drug product, regulatory consultants provide strategic guidance, and medical writing firms prepare dossier modules. Conversely, each vendor (especially CROs and CMOs) supports multiple applications across the company\'s portfolio. The business actively manages these engagements as distinct operational entities, tracking service type, contract value, deliverable status, and engagement timelines for each application-vendor pair.' .

ind:PayerCoverage rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Regulatory ;
    rdfs:label 'Payer Coverage' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the coverage contract between a regulatory approval and a payer account. It captures the specific terms under which a payer agrees to cover an approved drug product, including formulary placement, utilization management requirements, and contract economics. Each record links one approval to one payer account with attributes that exist only in the context of this payer-specific coverage relationship.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical market access operations, a single regulatory approval (e.g., an oncology drug approved by FDA) is independently negotiated with dozens or hundreds of payer organizations (Medicare, UnitedHealthcare, Aetna, Anthem, etc.), each resulting in distinct coverage terms including formulary tier placement, prior authorization requirements, rebate agreements, and utilization management policies. Conversely, a single payer account covers hundreds of approved drug products across multiple therapeutic areas, each with payer-specific coverage terms. The business actively manages these payer coverage agreements as operational entities with lifecycle tracking, contract renewal cycles, and performance monitoring.' .

ind:DrugProductAssaySpecification rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Product ;
    rdfs:label 'Drug Product Assay Specification' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the quality control testing specification between a drug product and an assay. It captures the regulatory and operational requirements for testing each drug product using specific assays. Each record links one drug product to one assay with attributes that define the testing protocol, acceptance criteria, and regulatory commitments that exist only in the context of this specific product-assay combination.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical quality control operations, a single drug product requires multiple assays for comprehensive testing (potency, purity, dissolution, stability, impurities, content uniformity), and a single validated assay is reused across multiple drug products (platform assays, compendial methods like USP dissolution). The business actively manages these specifications as regulatory commitments with product-specific acceptance criteria, testing frequencies, and validation protocols that cannot reside on either the assay or drug product alone.' .

ind:BrandSupplyAgreement rdf:type rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf ind:Commercial ;
    rdfs:label 'Brand Supply Agreement' ;
    rdfs:comment 'This association product represents the supply contract between a pharmaceutical brand and its approved vendors. It captures the qualification status, approved material categories, risk assessment, and spend allocation for each brand-vendor relationship. Each record links one brand to one vendor with attributes that exist only in the context of this supply relationship, enabling supply chain risk management, multi-sourcing strategy, and procurement planning at the brand level.. Existence Justification: In pharmaceutical operations, brands require materials from multiple vendors across different categories (API suppliers, excipient suppliers, packaging vendors, CMOs), and vendors supply materials for multiple brands in their portfolio. Procurement teams actively manage brand-vendor supply agreements as operational entities, tracking qualification status, approved material categories, risk tier, and spend allocation for each brand-vendor pair. This is a core supply chain management process, not an analytical correlation.' .

